title: jello-cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix dry jello into small curd cottage cheese.
Drain mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Add both fruits and small container of Cool Whip into cottage cheese.
Chill.

title: spinach salad
directions: Top with mayonnaise, not too thick, and grated Jack cheese to top and chill.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then blend in shortening.
Beat egg, vinegar and water together.
Add to dry ingredients.
Form into 4 balls and wrap with wax paper.
Chill for 15 minutes.
Makes two double pie crust.
(If you do not use all the balls, it can be placed in the freezer for use at another time.)

title: sunday baked chicken
directions: Spray casserole dish with no-stick spray.
Rub chicken liberally with seasoned salt.
Place in dish.
Surround chicken with carrots and potatoes.
Sprinkle carrots and potatoes with onions and bouillon.
Do not add any liquid.
Put covered, in a 300° oven before you leave for Sunday school.
It will be done after church.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: ella dunn's cookies
directions: Drop and roll in oatmeal.
Bake at 375° until done.
(Add nuts if desired.)

title: "vasilopita" - new year's cake
directions: Separate eggs; beat whites until stiff and put aside.
Put butter and sugar together; beat until fluffy, 20 minutes.
Add yolks and continue mixing for 5 minutes.
Add whites, milk, flour, baking powder and almonds.
Mix well.
Pour in buttered 12-inch round pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: ham and cream cheese pickles
directions: Dry juice from pickle and spread cream cheese all over it. Wrap in ham slice.
Slice crosswise into pieces.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together.
Add chopped green onions and garlic salt to taste.
Spread mix onto flour tortillas and roll up.
Cut in 1/2-inch pieces.
Serve with picante sauce for dipping.

title: one dish meal
directions: Put a layer of sliced potatoes in greased baking dish, then add vegetables and layer of hamburger.
Top with a layer of potatoes.
Heat the two soups in water.
Add salt and pepper. Pour over casserole.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are done in 350° oven.

title: hot borscht
directions: In soup pot, combine water and tomato juice and bring to boil. Add vegetables; cover and simmer 30 minutes until tender.
Remove 2 cups soup from pot and puree in blender of food processor. Return pureed soup to pot and stir in honey and lemon juice. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve with yogurt for garnish.

title: chilled fruit cups
directions: In a large bowl, prepare pineapple juice concentrate according to package directions.
Add orange juice concentrate, water, sugar, lemon juice and fruit.
Spoon 3/4 cupful into each plastic cup.
Place cups in a pan and freeze.
Remove from the freezer 40 - 50 minutes before serving.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt margarine in a cake pan.
Add rice, then lay chicken pieces on top of rice.
Sprinkle soup mix on top of chicken. Add water. Cover with foil and bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: 1-2-3 cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350 for 25 to 35 minutes.
Test for doneness at the 25 minute point.
Use sheet cake, 9 X 13 inch, or 2 to 3
9 inch pans.
Items should be room temperature so cake will rise higher.
Freezes very well.
You can substitute flavorings such as almond or butter for the vanilla flavoring.

title: parsley soup with danish dumplings(make soup ahead of dumplings)
directions: Slice thinly equal amounts of onion and carrots.
Heat margarine in pan.
Stir onion and carrots for 6 minutes.
Add thinly sliced potato and stir 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour in heated stock and salt.
Simmer covered 35 minutes.
Add parsley and reheat. This is good without the dumplings.

title: goulash
directions: Grease baking dish.
Chop tomatoes. Brown hamburger and drain. Cook macaroni until tender.
Mix all ingredients and shake Romano cheese in mixture.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: my favorite butterscotch pudding dessert
directions: Cook sugar and butter in heavy skillet until a chocolate brown.
Add water and boil until dissolved.
Combine egg yolks, flour and milk; stir well.
Add to sugar mixture and cook until thick.
Let cool, then add peanuts and sliced bananas.

title: super special strawberry salad
directions: Cook almonds and sugar in small skillet over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar is melted and almonds are coated. Cool and break apart.
Store at room temperature.
Place remaining ingredients in a large salad bowl and toss thoroughly with sweet and sour dressing.
Garnish with additional strawberries. Delicious!

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions; add sour cream and Cool Whip to pudding and mix well.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture until all ingredients are used.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss together lightly the cooked chicken, American cheese, diced celery, pineapple, almonds or walnuts, paprika, salt and mayonnaise.
Before serving, add whipped cream and 1/4 cup mayonnaise, if needed.
This will serve 4 to 5 persons.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix together butters, juice, milk, flour, yolks and rind.
Beat egg whites with salt until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into first mixture.
Pour into pastry lined pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: coke chicken
directions: Pour Coke on top of a cut up chicken.
Sprinkle soup mix on top.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Baste once or twice during cooking.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and put in pie shell.
Top with brown sugar, then butter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in an 8 x 11-inch pan.
Mix until blended cream cheese, vanilla pudding and milk.
Stir in pineapple and coconut.
Spread on cooled cake; cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with cherries and nuts.

title: bee sting cake
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
Add brown sugar, corn syrup and water.
Stir over moderate heat until mixture simmers and sugar dissolves.
Pour 1/2 of syrup into each of the two greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans lined with wax paper.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Mix cake according to package directions and divide in each pan.
Bake according to package.
Cool 5 minutes and remove from pans.
Scrape any topping off and spread on cake.
Cool completely.
Beat Cool Whip, pudding and milk until thick.
Spread on both layers.
Top with second layer.
Spread frosting on top.
Refrigerate.

title: jello salad
directions: Heat sugar and pineapple to boiling.
Remove from heat; add Jell-O which has been dissolved in 1/2 cup cold water.
Let stand until congealed (put in refrigerator).
Add cheese and Cool Whip.

title: jalapeno cheese cornbread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into buttered baking dish and
bake
at 425° for about 25 minutes or until done.
This is particularly good with chicken, pork and any vegetable.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain all canned veggies.
Mix all ingredients together; set aside.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Slightly thaw frozen vegetables.
Mix ingredients (except saltines and melted butter) and put in casserole.
Cover with saltines and 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: smoked sausage rice skillet
directions: Saute carrots and zucchini in margarine in skillet over medium heat 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes with juice, water, basil, thyme and sausage.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat; let stand 8 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.
Yields 5 servings.

title: almond roca
directions: Boil sugar, water, butter and salt until it burns and darkens in color.
Add vanilla.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bottom with 1/2 of shaved almonds.
Then add 1/2 of the shaved Hershey bar.
Pour hot mixture over the nuts and chocolate.
Cover mixture with chocolate and remaining shaved almonds.

title: meatball casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Form into small balls; roll in flour and brown in oil.
Then, remove from skillet and alternate with potatoes and carrots in casserole dish.
Add 1 tablespoon flour to pan where meatballs were browned.
Add tomatoes and let come to boil.
Pour over meatballs in casserole.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cinnamon pretzels
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together and put in an empty salt shaker.
Wet one soft pretzel.
Sprinkle on both sides with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake in microwave 30 seconds on both sides each, one pretzel at a time.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add beaten egg, coconut flavoring, instant potatoes and Bix-Mix.
Mix it all together. Drop 1/2 teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: fudge cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa in pot.
Set aside.
Beat 4 eggs.
Add sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Sift flour into eggs and sugar.
Add vanilla, pecans, melted butter and cocoa.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and lined with wax paper.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix mustard, mayo and vinegar well, then add all other ingredients.
You can add more vinegar, if desired.
Once it is mixed, use on any meats desired. Can be stored at room temperature.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine cream cheese, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip. Beat well.
Pour into the 2 pie crusts and chill. Top with cherry pie filling before serving.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and add picante sauce and corn (also add Ranch Style beans). Mix and place in baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Pour prepared corn bread mix on top and bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve with salad.

title: beef stew
directions: Cook beef cubes in water until soft, or use leftover beef and broth.
Add everything but peas.
Cook until all is soft.
Then add peas.
Simmer 20 minutes or longer.
(The longer it simmers, the better it tastes!)

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, sugar and egg together. Add vanilla. Mix together the flour, soda and salt and gradually add to creamed mixture. Shape into balls and roll in 1/4 cup of sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Remove from oven and press a chocolate "Kiss" in each cookie so cookie cracks around the edges. Return to oven and continue to bake for 2 or 3 minutes. Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: chicken-brown rice dish
directions: Brown chicken in pan prior to starting this recipe.

title: chocolate caramel candy crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread crackers on a large cookie sheet, salt side up.
On stove, melt brown sugar and butter in saucepan on high heat until boiling.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour brown sugar over crackers and bake in oven for exactly 5 minutes. Take out of oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over entire pan and spread.
Refrigerate a few hours, then break into pieces.

title: barbecue pork chops(easy and delicious)
directions: Mix together all ingredients except pork chops.
Spread over pork chops in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 2 hours, or until deep brown.
Serve with rice.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Boil juice of pineapple and cherries.
Pour over jello; mix and let cool.
Mix other ingredients and chill for 24 hours before serving.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mash cranberries with fork and add.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened, then add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until set in mold.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, flour, milk, vanilla and coconut. Melt 1/2 stick of butter. Pour divided butter into 2 pie pans (9-inch pie pan). Pour excess into pie mixture. Mix well and pour into pans. Cook about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: speedy lamaze sauce
directions: Chill for 1 hour.
Add 1 to 1 1/2 pounds medium to large shrimp and enjoy.
Good party fare.

title: muscleman medley
directions: In medium skillet, heat oil. Add chopped onion and saute 4 to 5 minutes until softened. Add spinach and cook another 3 minutes. Distribute mixture evenly on crust of your choice (pizza or pie crust, etc.). Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until spinach is cooked and cheese is melted. Serves 2 to 4.

title: chocolate cloud delight
directions: Mix flour, oleo and chopped walnuts.
Spread in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° about 20 minutes or until golden.
Cool well.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1 (8 ounce) Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Spread on top of baked crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Pour on top of cream cheese mixture.
Cool until set.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Sprinkle ground walnuts on top of Cool Whip.
Chill well.

title: favorite pecan pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar and corn syrup.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Let cool slightly. Add eggs, vanilla and salt to mixture; mix well.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, then combine rest of ingredients and stir only until moistened.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: crust for fried pies
directions: Mix all together and knead to hold together. Roll some dough out the size of a saucer. Fill 1/2 of the dough with sweetened dried fruit or fresh fruit. Dot with butter. Fold the other half over on top of fruit and crimp the edge. Fry in oil. Let one side get brown, then turn over. This dough keeps well in freezer.

title: spanish steak
directions: Rub meat with salt and pepper.
Pound all the flour possible into the steaks.
Sear in hot fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover.
Simmer slowly about 3 hours, or until meat is tender.
If desired, peas, celery, celery salt, spice and 1/2 cup finely diced salt pork may be added to give variety in flavor.
Makes 12 servings.

title: brown sugar peach pie
directions: Combine brown sugar and flour.
Add syrup, lemon juice and butter; cook over low heat until sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly.
Arrange peaches in pastry lined 9-inch pie plate.
Pour brown sugar mixture over peaches.
Place lattice topping over peaches; flute edge.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 35 minutes, or until done.

title: hot peppers in tomato sauce
directions: Mix and boil for 1 minute.
Have peppers cut in rings.
Drop peppers into sauce and cook approximately 5 minutes.
Put into jars and seal.

title: crusty tomato scallop(easy rv recipe)
directions: Combine tomatoes, bread crumbs and onion.
Melt butter.
Add flour, seasonings and mustard.
Combine with tomato mixture and pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cut bread slices into cubes and sprinkle over tomatoes.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: tomato soup
directions: Pressure cook the first 4 ingredients.
Cook tomato soup, tomato sauce and fresh tomatoes for 30 minutes.
Add salt and parsley flakes.
Strain soup, then add sour cream last.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine fruit cocktail and Jell-O.
Add cottage cheese, marshmallows and pecans. Fold into Cool Whip. Gently stir in coconut; chill.

title: breakfast egg dish
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard. Layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch greased dish.
Pour egg mixture over this; refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: wonder salad
directions: Mix jello, water and marshmallows; stir until dissolved. Cool.
Stir in all others, except the cream.
When partly thickened, add whipped cream.
Good!

title: corn maquechou(serves 4)
directions: Shuck, silk and rinse corn thoroughly.
Cut corn from cobs (make one cut if kernels are small, two if large).
Scrape cob if you like creamy maquechou.
Place cooking oil in bottom of heavy pot.
Add all other ingredients and cook slowly on low heat.
Stir occasionally, until onions are transparent.
If corn is dry, add a small amount of water to reach desired consistency.
Season to taste.
If you like, throw a handful of freshly peeled butter beans into maquechou.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients. Bake 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw, rinse and drain spinach.
Chop green onions.
Mix into bowl and chill until ready to serve.
Best served with a vegetable tray and vegie crackers.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together and set aside.
Cream together shortening, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Blend in flour mixture gradually.
Shape dough into small balls; roll each ball in sugar and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and top each with a Hershey's Kiss, pressing down firmly so cookie cracks around the edge.
Return to oven and bake about 2 or 3 minutes longer.

title: squash and zucchini casserole
directions: Boil squash and zucchini in small amount of water seasoned with onion flakes, salt and pepper.
Cook until tender-crisp. Drain thoroughly.
Melt butter; mix with cheese and sour cream. Put drained squash and zucchini in a casserole and pour butter mixture over.
Sprinkle bread crumbs all over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of boiling, salted water, just until tender and drain.
Combine eggs, milk, soup, mayonnaise and cheese.
Stir in cooked broccoli.
Pour mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole dish and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Cook 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In dish, put melted margarine and milk.
Sprinkle bottom of dish with 1/2 bag of dressing; set aside.
Saute onion and pepper. Combine chicken, both cans of soup, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper together.
Mix well.
Pour on top of set aside dressing. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 bag of dressing over top of chicken mixture and dot with pats of margarine.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Layer and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pour into unbaked pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: easy welsh rarebit
directions: Heat tomato soup, without diluting, over a low flame in a small (1-quart) saucepan or double boiler for approximately two minutes.
Stir in the mustard, Worcestershire sauce, parsley and onions.
Next, add the grated cheese and stir until melted and well blended.
To serve, spoon over toast.

title: greek spinach pie
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Add 1/4 cup melted butter to spinach.
Mix eggs, onion and cheeses together and combine with spinach.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter bottom of 11 x 17 pan. Place 8 pastry sheets in pan 2 at a time, brushing every second sheet with melted butter.
Distribute spinach mixture evenly over pastry sheets.
Repeat process with 8 more pastry sheets.
With sharp knife cut through top to mark into squares.
Bake for 1 hour or until golden brown.
When cooled can be stored in refrigerator or frozen.
Reheat in 350° oven.

title: baked peaches
directions: Cut peaches in half; remove pits.
Place, cut side up, on heavy-duty aluminum foil large enough to be folded and sealed.
In bowl, combine sour cream, brown sugar, spices and vanilla.
Top peach halves with mixture.
Bring together sides of foil, sealing all edges well to make an airtight packet.
Place packet of peaches over coals of a grill or in a preheated 375° oven; bake for 20 to 30 minutes, until peaches are soft and sugar in topping has melted.
Open foil packet; let peaches cool slightly.
Serve warm.
Makes 4 servings.

title: any fruit cobbler
directions: Cream butter or margarine with 1 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour and mix well.
Spoon batter into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle fruit on top.
Add boiling water (don't worry, it works).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve while warm.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter.
Add flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Add syrup. Beat eggs and mix with other ingredients.
Add chopped nuts and vanilla.
Pour into uncooked pie shell and bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: french fillet of sole
directions: Cut each fillet in half, making the cut across the width. Place several shrimp in the center of each and roll fillet around them.
In a buttered saucepan, add the shallots and the wine. Carefully lay the fillet rolls in the saucepan and cover with buttered round of wax paper and cook covered.
Poach gently about 10 minutes.
Remove dish to heated serving dish, reserving the liquid.
Reduce poaching liquid by 1/3.
In another saucepan, combine egg yolks and cream and a little of the hot poaching liquid.
Stir into the remaining poaching liquid, add dill and correct seasonings.
Stir in sweet butter and pour over the fillet rolls.
Sprinkle with parsley and more dill if desired.

title: peach torte
directions: Soften gelatin in 7/8 cup peach syrup.
Mash the peaches. Place peaches and syrup in pan.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and the softened gelatin.
Stir over low heat until the gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in Amaretto.
Chill until peach mixture begins to thicken.
Split ladyfingers and place them around sides and bottom of spring-form pan.
Sprinkle almonds over bottom of pan.
Whip the cream and sweeten with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Fold into peach mixture.
Spoon into spring-form pan.
Chill for several hours.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Simmer clams and lemon juice for 10 minutes.
Saute onion until brown.
Add onions, oregano, parsley, garlic, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella to clams.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until creamy; add milk and beat 2 minutes.
Add lemon juice and vanilla; beat 1 minute.
Pour into crust and cool for 2 hours.
Top with your choice of fruit pie filling.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender with sliced onion.
After potatoes are done, drain and pour into glass baking dish.
Add margarine by dots over potatoes.
Top with cheese, torn into small pieces.
Add milk and lightly mix altogether.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until cheese is lightly browned.

title: pineapple ice
directions: Combine water and sugar in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Cool.
Combine syrup, pineapple juice and orange juice.
Divide among cups.
Cover and freeze until firm, stirring occasionally.
Shave frozen mixture; scoop into small cups.
Serve with a spoon or straw.
Garnish with fresh mint or orange rind.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Squish cookies and 1/3 cup butter in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Next spread softened ice cream.
Combine powdered sugar, milk, 2 tablespoons butter and chocolate chips in saucepan. Bring to a boil and pour over ice cream.
Freeze overnight.

title: susie's chicken pot pie
directions: Put bottom crust in pie pan.
Combine first 3 ingredients and fill pie crust.
Top with remaining crust; make slits in top. Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Mix all together and cook 20 minutes after it boils.
If it's not red enough, add red food coloring.
If you want more cinnamon taste use a few drops of oil of cinnamon.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a baking dish, except crackers and margarine.
Crumble crackers and mix with margarine.
Spread on top of all.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and taco seasoning, prepare according to package directions, using only 1/2 amount of water called for.

title: beef roll
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 days.
Each day take out and mix.
Fourth day divide into 5 long rolls.
Lay on broiler pan.
Bake 5 hours at 175°.
Keeps well in freezer.

title: herman hot rolls
directions: Mix together.
Knead on a floured board until smooth.
Allow to rise 1 hour.
Punch down and make into rolls.
Allow to rise until double.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add to sauce, water and spices.
Mix in macaroni and put 1/2 mixture in long, shallow baking dish.
Add a layer of cheese and the rest of macaroni mixture.
Put pepperoni on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef and biscuit casserole
directions: Saute beef.
If
using	yellow	onion, saute with beef. Drain. Stir
in
remaining
ingredients,	except biscuits and cheese. Heat until bubbly.	Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Cut biscuits in half to form 20 half circles.
Place cut side down around edge of casserole.	Sprinkle
with cheese.	Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.	Serves 4 to 6.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook on medium heat; stir constantly until it starts boiling.
Cook until it forms a ball when dropped in cold water.
Add butter and popcorn.

title: blueberry jam
directions: Wash berries and drain. Mash berries to a pulp. Add apples and mash in with berries. Add sugar and mix together. Add water and stir. Cook on low heat until sugar melts. Then turn on medium heat and cook slowly, stirring occasionally as jam thickens. When thick enough, pour into containers and seal.

title: no-sugar frosting
directions: Whip cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Sweeten with honey or fructose, continuing to whip.
Don't let cream cheese get runny.
Cakes must be completely cooled before frosting.
Frosting may be tinted pink with a small amount of beet juice.

title: beef casserole
directions: In a large soup kettle, saute onion in butter until soft, but not browned.
Add meat and garlic and cook until meat is brown. Drain off fat.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Bring soup to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 1 hour.

title: szechwan noodles
directions: Boil noodles; coat with oils and refrigerate.
Mix sesame seed paste (peanut butter) with 1 tablespoon soy sauce.
Continue adding soy sauce, mixing until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour sauce over noodles immediately before serving.

title: spicy tomatoes
directions: Put tomatoes and all the rest in bowl, any size that will fit your quantity.
Mix lightly; refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Place on bed of lettuce or drain and add to your sandwich.

title: potato puff casserole
directions: In a small bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Prepare mashed potatoes as directed on package.
Turn into large bowl.
Whip potatoes with other ingredients.
Fold in egg whites.
Spoon into buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Drizzle melted butter over top; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Prepare rice.
Beat eggs with salt in bowl.
Set aside.
In 12-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat in 2 tablespoons of hot oil, gently stir rice until rice is well coated with oil.
Push rice to one side of skillet.

title: california blend
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower until tender.
Blend with each soup.
Melt cheese spread; pour on top.
Sprinkle with onions. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chewy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl cream together margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla, beat well. Add flour mixture and beat until well blended.
Stir in coconut, chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.
Remove cookies to rack to cool.
Store in tightly covered container. Yields 5 dozen.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, stirring with a wire whisk to remove large lumps.
Add oil eggs, water and sour cream.
Stirring until smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour batter into greased and floured bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes on wire rack.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic over medium heat until beef is completely done and onion is tender; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, plus 1 cup water.
Stir well.
Simmer over low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.
Leftover sauce freezes well.

title: christmas punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed in two 8-inch round cake pans. Place one round cake layer (cooled) in bottom of a large glass punch bowl.
Cover with half the pudding prepared as directed, half the cherry pie filling, half the fruit cocktail, half the pineapple, half the coconut and half the whipped topping. Sprinkle with nuts.
Place remaining cake layer on top and repeat remaining layers.
Decorate with cherries and pineapple, as desired.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Serves 25.

title: sausage and cheese puffs
directions: Grate cheese finely.
Cook sausage until fully cooked.
Mix Bisquick with water and cheese; add sausage.
Form into balls and bake at 400° for exactly 10 minutes on lightly greased cookie tins.
To freeze, don't get too brown.
Freeze and reheat.

title: oil cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix liquids and dry ingredients, then add flour to mixture. Let set and raise.

title: super sandwiches
directions: Slice bread almost to bottom in 15 places.
Spread every other slice hole with Italian dressing.
Place 1 slice of turkey or corned beef with cheese and tomato into prepared section.
Wrap in foil.
Chill.
Later bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into blank section and serve.

title: autumn vegetable minestrone
directions: Mix all ingredients except rice in a 3 1/2 to 6-quart slow cooker. Cover and cook on low heat for 6 to 8 hours or until vegetables are tender. Stir in rice. Cover and cook on low heat setting for about 15 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into crust.
Refrigerate several hours or until firm.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Grease round pizza pan.
Pat cookie dough to edges of pan (use little flour so dough won't stick to hands).
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until brown.
Allow to cool.

title: homemade potato soup
directions: Pare and dice potatoes and put in large saucepan.
Add celery. Cut bacon into small pieces and add to potatoes.
Cover with cold water and boil until potatoes are tender.
Turn heat to medium-low and stir in butter.
Add salt and pepper.
Simmer until soup thickens slightly.
For a richer soup, 1 cup of cream may be added, if desired.
Stir cream during the last 15 to 20 minutes of simmering.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Add onion and garlic; cook until onion begins to turn golden.
Add tomatoes, salt, oregano and pepper. Simmer 40 to 50 minutes.
Add a little water if it gets dry. Serve over rice or spaghetti.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix all with a blender or food processor.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Blend corn meal, flour, sugar and nuts.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add mashed bananas to egg, then add to the dry ingredients.
Stir in melted shortening.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: baklava
directions: In 12 x 18-inch pan place 1 sheet of pastry.
Brush with melted butter.
Do this with 5 more sheets of pastry.
Starting with the 6th sheet, brush with butter, then sprinkle with nuts and sugar/cinnamon mixture. Do this with each sheet until 6 sheets are left.
Continue to layer remaining sheets, brushing with butter. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Pour hot syrup over baklava and let stand for 3 hours.

title: aline's party chicken with rice
directions: Place each 1/2 bacon strip on 1/2 of boned chicken breast in a greased casserole (9 x 12-inches). Combine next 6 ingredients into a sauce and pour over chicken. Bake for 2 hours, covered, at 300°. Uncover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes more.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix milk and soda and set aside.
Cream sugar and oil together.
Add the beaten eggs to sugar and oil.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Stir everything together, then fold in prunes and pecans.	Bake in layer pans at 350° for 1 hour.	Ice with your favorite white icing.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add eggs, milk and butter.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla.
Cool.
Alternate wafers, bananas and pudding in a bowl.

title: camper's cobbler
directions: This simple cobbler requires no mixing of ingredients at all. Simply pour the peaches in a cast-iron pot.
Next, sprinkle the cake mix evenly over the peaches.
Last, slice the margarine and place it in thin slivers all over the mix.
Put lid on pot and place in coals for approximately 25 to 35 minutes.
The juice from the peaches will mix with the cake mix to form a nice, brown crust.
Serve hot or cold.

title: original "snappy turtle cookie"
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter.
Add brown sugar and sugar and cream well.
Add egg and egg yolk; beat well. Blend in vanilla and maple flavoring.
Add dry ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Arrange pecan halves, rounded side up, in groups of three on greased baking sheets to resemble head and hind legs of turtle.
Mold dough into balls, using rounded teaspoonfuls of dough; press onto nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool and frost.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bake 9-inch pie shell.
Mix water, sugar and cornstarch. Cook until mixture comes to a boil.
Cook 2 minutes longer; add strawberry jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Put fresh strawberries in baked pie shell.
Pour glaze over strawberries.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: heaven salad
directions: Cut all of the ingredients above and mix together.

title: boiled cake
directions: Boil all ingredients except last 3 for 5 minutes; let cool completely.
Add the flour, baking soda and salt.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in loaf pans.
Can be frozen.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Place pork chops
in
x 13-inch pan.
On top of each put 1 tablespoon	brown sugar, 1 lemon slice or a few drops of ReaLemon, 1
slice onion and 2 tablespoons catsup.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 325° for 1 3/4 hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well and pour into 2 large or 3 small greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 1/2 hour before removing from pans.

title: cream puffs
directions: Add butter to water and heat until butter melts.
Add flour all at once and stir vigorously until ball forms in center of pan. Cool slightly.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each egg. Mixture should be very stiff.
Shape on buttered cookie sheet by dropping from spoon or using pastry bag and tube.
Bake until free from beads of moisture for 40 to 45 minutes in 375° oven.
Fill with cream filling, whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in the skins; drain, let cool, peel and dice. Add butter to hot potatoes.
Mix together onion, peppers, pickles, celery, cucumbers, eggs and carrot.
Add to diced potatoes along with vinegar.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Toss all together with mayonnaise.
(You can adjust mayonnaise more or less, as needed.)

title: pear salad
directions: Heat the pear juice to boiling and pour over jello.
Stir until jello is dissolved. Add cream cheese.
Mix with electric mixer until cream cheese is dissolved. Cut up the pears and add. Cool. When mixture starts to thicken, whip the cream and add. Refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.

title: knephla soup
directions: 1. Bring the water, onion, bouillon cubes, salt, and pepper to a boil.
2. Make dough by mixing flour, eggs, salt, baking powder,
and 1 c. water.
3. Cut dough in small strips and place into the boiling
pot. Let boil for 15 minutes then add the half and half
and bring to a light boil.

title: bore hole biscuit delite
directions: Hold one biscuit edgewise in left hand; use first 2 fingers of right hand to bore good size hole in biscuit.
Pour hole full of Baldree syrup and squeeze lightly, working syrup into biscuit, then dig in. "Betcha can't eat just one."

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all together; mix until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown in 9 x 13 pan.
Can be eaten like this, but I always use confectioners icing on mine.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening at medium speed with electric mixer about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed, 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla.

title: fruit punch
directions: In a gallon container, combine Kool-Aid, sugar and pineapple juice.
Mix well until sugar dissolves.
Fill the balance of the gallon with water.
Chill before serving.
Punch can be partially frozen to create slush.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream butter, eggs and sugar.
Pour hot water in cocoa, then add to mixture.
Add buttermilk.
Sift dry ingredients (soda, baking powder and flour).
Add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake about 30 to 40 minutes in layer pans at 350°.

title: raisin muffins
directions: Mix and bake in greased muffin pan at 350° until done.

title: yum yum cake(an old family treasure)
directions: Sift together and add to cooled mixture.
Bake in a slow 275° to 300° oven for 1 hour in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix flour and salt in a bowl.
Cut in oil and shortening until small particles appear.
I prefer to use two butter knives for the job.
Sprinkle with half of water and mix with fork.
Add rest of water and mix.
Press into two balls and roll on floured surface to make top and bottom crusts for 9-inch pie.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large bowl. Make a well in center of mixture. Combine egg, milk and butter.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Yields 12 muffins.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Place potato chips over top.

title: squash stew
directions: Pull skin from sausage and fry.
Add celery and fry an additional 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except peppers and cook 30 minutes.
Then add peppers and cook an additional 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Serve hot with Parmesan cheese.

title: no peek skillet chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil and drain.
Stir in tomatoes, mushrooms and garlic combined with onion soup mix.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, 45 minutes or until chicken is tender and no longer pink.
Serve over hot noodles and sprinkle, if desired, with chopped parsley.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in lightly salted water until done and debone. Place chicken pieces in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix soups and sour cream together.
Spread mixture over chicken.
Top with dry dressing mix.
Combine butter or margarine with broth; pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until soup mixture bubbles over casserole topping.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: marinated pretzels
directions: Mix and pour over 24 oz. bag of pretzels.
Stir occasionally, until oil absorbs, within 1/2 hour.
Great snack!!

title: french fried potato puffs
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonful in hot oil. Cook until golden brown.

title: nacho cheese chowder
directions: In a 2-quart microwave-safe casserole, crumble the beef.
Add the green pepper.
Microcook, covered, on 100% power (High) for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes or until no pink remains in the beef, stirring once.
Drain off the fat.
Stir in nacho soup dip, milk, corn, onion and tomato.
Cook, covered, on High for 7 to 10 minutes or until chowder is heated through, stirring once.
Makes 3 main dish servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions. In casserole dish, combine rice, corn, soup and cheese.
Bake at 350° approximately 20 minutes.

title: wiener appetizers
directions: Combine gravy mix and water in saucepan; mix thoroughly.
Add other ingredients and heat, stirring until sauce thickens and wieners are hot.
Serve with toothpicks from chafing dish.

title: cheesy artichoke squares(servings:  4)
directions: Combine eggs with crumbs, salt, pepper, oregano and hot pepper sauce.
Set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and artichokes.
Combine with egg and crumb mixture.
Spread in greased 11 x 7 1/2 x 1/2-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
May be served hot or cold.

title: orange beets
directions: Mix all together and boil until cornstarch is clear.
(A good way to coax your family to eat beets.)

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Put strawberries in bowl and let thaw.
Add pineapple and juice, apricots with juice and sliced bananas.
Add lemon juice. Put foil baking cups in cupcake pan.
Fill about 3/4 full.
Set baking pans in freezer.
When frozen, they may be put in freezer bags, ready to use.

title: hot tamales
directions: Cook beef in pot of water until tender.
Take meat out of liquid.
Grind meat with onions while meat is hot.
Use about half as many onions as meat.
Salt meat to taste.

title: shish kabob
directions: Alternate pieces of vegetables with meat and broil until well browned.
Serve immediately.
Yields 1 serving.
One serving contains approximately (Exchanges):
3 meat and 1 vegetable.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt chips with milk.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Chill for about 2 hours.
Cut in squares.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake mix, mandarin oranges, eggs and oil well.
Pour into 3 (8-inch) round greased and floured cake pans.

Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. While the cake is baking, mix the pudding and pineapple together. Add the Cool Whip. Set this in refrigerator to chill until the cake is cool. Frost between and sides of the layers.
Store in refrigerator.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions but leave out salt.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine with cheese and stir over broccoli.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and add Ritz crackers.
Pour on top.
Cook until bubbles.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla extract until creamy. Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in oats and butterscotch chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes for chewier cookies and 9 to 10 minutes for crispier cookies.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: creamy carrot soup
directions: Chop onion; in a soup pot, heat oil over medium low heat.
Add onion and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cover and cook until tender, 5 minutes.
Stir in cumin; add the carrots, stock and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Bring to a simmer; cook until carrots are heated through, about 2 minutes.
In a blender or food processor, puree the carrot mixture, in batches if necessary, until smooth.
Return to pot; stir in the cream and warm over low heat until soup is heated through.
Taste for seasoning and add salt and pepper, if needed. Sprinkle with parsley before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add to cooked squash with eggs, milk, cheese, sugar, crackers and season with pepper and salt if needed.
Spoon into greased casserole and top with additional cracker crumbs, if desired.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.

title: my mother's chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk and bring to a boil.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add flour and soda, alternately with milk. Combine egg and vanilla; stir well.
Combine the two mixtures and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch or 10 x 15-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Watch closely as it bakes quickly.

title: apple pudding
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg.
Add flour sifted with baking soda.
Cut apples and nuts thin.
Dough seems to thicken, but apples make moisture.
Use small square pan or double for 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: w. va. creamed tomatoes
directions: Pour tomato juice
in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Mix water and flour
together until smooth.
Add milk to water and flour and mix
well.
Add
this
mixture to boiling juice. Bring to boil until thick.
Add butter salt and pepper.
Serve over hot, split buttered biscuits.

title: snicker bar
directions: Soften ice cream.
Mix all ingredients into ice cream.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch cake pan and freeze.

title: peach brandy fruit dressing
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, milk and beaten egg yolks.
Cook until thickened over low heat.
Remove from heat; add brandy and cool. Add whipped cream and stir well with small wooden spoon.
Serve over fresh melons and assorted fruits.

title: my favorite peanut brittle
directions: Measure the sugar, corn syrup and water into a 3-quart saucepan; stir until the sugar dissolves. Stir until the syrup comes to a boil, then put in a candy thermometer and boil mixture over high heat until the thermometer registers 280°. Reduce heat to low and add butter, then the salted peanuts, stirring rapidly all the while. (If peanuts are not salted, add 1/2 teaspoon salt.) Cook and stir for 2 to 3 minutes, then stir occasionally until thermometer reaches 300°. Remove pan from heat. Add soda. Stir until mixture bubbles. Add the vanilla. Stir again and pour onto a large cookie sheet. Spread out thinly with a wooden spoon. When cool enough to handle, stretch and pull to thin the brittle. You can pick it up and turn it over, stretching all the while. When cool, break into pieces and store in tight container.

title: pizza dough (1)
directions: Spread dough on greased pan.
Bake at 450° for about 15 minutes (until light brown).

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar by hand until smooth and doughy.
Divide in half.
Add a few drops of flavoring; add to taste.
Add food coloring.
Pinch off small pieces of dough.
Roll into balls and dip into sugar; press into molds.
Refrigerate, covered.

title: great mashed potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add cream cheese and butter.
Beat well and mix in French onion dip and milk with salt and pepper.
Place in greased 9-inch casserole dish and refrigerate.
If using immediately, bake at 350° for 45 minutes until light brown. Serves 8 to 12.

title: apple pineapple coleslaw
directions: Combine first five ingredients, then combine mayonnaise, sugar and salt, tossing all together until well mixed.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix soup, milk and butter.
Use a greased casserole.
Layer potatoes and soup mixture (end up with soup mixture on top).
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, uncovered, or 1 hour at 450°, covered.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Beat together until smooth, 2 cups sugar and oil.
Add eggs, orange juice and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder and add to mix.
Beat for 5 minutes.

title: garlic fried chicken
directions: Cut each chicken breast in 3 or 4 strips.
Salt each piece with garlic salt and pepper.
Place in bowl and drench with buttermilk so each piece is covered.
In separate bowl mix flour, garlic salt and chili powder thoroughly.
Dredge each piece thoroughly in flour mixture and drop in hot oil to fry until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Blend ingredients and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake until done.
Sprinkle top with sugar when removed from oven.

title: mints
directions: Work with hands.
Add coloring of choice.
Make a long roll the size of a dime and cut with a buttered knife or use molds.
Let set for 2 hours before serving.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs (well beaten) and apples.
Sift and add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan 1 hour at 350°.
(Very thick.)

title: marinated cabbage slaw
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Heat vinegar with remaining ingredients in saucepan until sugar dissolves, stirring frequently.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Chill for 24 hours to 1 week.
Yield:
12 to 14 servings.

title: tofu oatmeal
directions: In a bowl, mash the tofu with a potato masher.
Add skim milk and oatmeal.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Add raisins and cut up apple.
Serve Brazil nuts on the side.
The Brazil nuts complement the protein of the tofu which is low in sulfur containing amino acids.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook meats together until tender.
Cut up fine.
Add other ingredients.
Cook slowly for 2 hours.

title: spicy dip for vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients, blending well.
Chill.
Serve with carrot sticks, celery sticks, green pepper strips, cauliflower, cucumber or squash strips.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Put flour, sugar and salt in a large bowl.
Beat egg and add to water and vinegar.
Mix into flour.
Mix well and roll out. Makes 4 single pie crusts.

title: tomato soup (canned)
directions: Wash and cut up tomatoes. Chop onions, celery, parsley and bay leaves. Add to tomatoes; cook until celery is tender. Put through sieve. Rub flour and butter into a smooth paste, thinned with tomato juice. Add to boiling soup. Stir to prevent scorching. Add salt, sugar and pepper. For smooth consistency, put through sieve again. Fill jars to within 1-inch of top of jar. Put on cap and screw band firmly. Process in water bath 15 minutes.

title: green chili chicken
directions: Boil chicken with celery, onion, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Cool and pull off of bones.
Line a large casserole dish with corn tortillas.
Make a broth by combining the three soups with some of the chicken broth.
Top the tortillas with shredded chicken, green chiles, grated cheese and broth.
Layer until full, ending with broth mixture and grated cheese.
Bake at 325° to 350° until bubbly.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Sprinkle on top and press into cream cheese mixture.
Freezes well.

title: heavenly bits
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Cream or beat well.
Add flour, salt and vanilla, working all in with hands.
Form in 1-inch balls. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
While hot, may be rolled in powdered sugar.

title: cinnamon and sugar pecans
directions: Beat egg white until frothy and stir in 1 pound of pecans adding tablespoon of water. Mix together sugar, salt and cinnamon. Pour sugar mixture into coated pecans and stir.
Pour into greased shallow pan and bake in 300° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes. Spread on wax paper and cool.

title: mary's best cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and milk.
Mix well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Grease and flour 10 inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for about 2 hours.
You may add 4 Tbsp. cocoa to flour for chocolate pound cake.

title: chocolate chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer, adding chocolate chips after mixture is smooth.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This cake is delicious, needs no frosting, keeps and serves well!!
First used this recipe on a Girl Scout outing; it is a must when Potluck spends a weekend in the Palm Desert/Desert Hot Springs area.
And we always need two cakes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring 1/2 cup water to boil, then add sugar and syrup. Stir until dissolved and boil until a thread spins. Add peanuts and cook slowly over low fire until it turns golden brown. Take from flame and add remaining ingredients. Stir quickly. Spread on 2 large cookie sheets, well buttered. Place in cold spot to harden, then break into small pieces.

title: pretty posies
directions: Spread thin layer of softened cream cheese over slice of ham. Lay on pickled okra across and roll up into a tube.
Continue until enough is made.
Place ham rolls in container and freeze. When frozen use sharp knife to cut from end to end making little circles.
Place on tray and serve.
Can be frozen in advance for later use.

title: heavenly cloud bread pudding
directions: Heat milk and margarine until margarine melts.
Set aside to cool slightly.
Break bread into small pieces; place in ungreased casserole or souffle dish.
Separate eggs.
Beat yolks until lemon colored.
Slowly add yolks to milk; add vanilla.
Pour over bread. Bake in pan half filled with water 55 to 60 minutes at 325°. While pudding is baking, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time and beat until stiff.
Remove pudding from oven.
Spread choice of fruit pie filling on top. Cover completely with meringue.
Return to oven until meringue is lightly brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: egg salad filling
directions: Stir together all ingredients until well mixed.
Makes 2 cups.

title: breakfast eggs
directions: You will need a muffin tin.

title: cabbage and white beans
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in skillet.
Add cabbage and onions. Stir-fry for 1 minute and add to skillet remaining ingredients. Heat until cabbage is crisp-tender and serve immediately.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding mix together.
Add pecans, pineapple and marshmallows.
Mix thoroughly and serve.

title: rose's zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl, mix together the flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking powder, baking soda, zucchini, raisins, and nuts. In another bowl, beat together the eggs, vanilla, and oil. Pour over flour mixture and stir until thoroughly mixed. Turn into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 1 and 1/2 hours.

title: old south biscuits
directions: Combine flour and margarine until crumbly.
Add buttermilk. Stir until mixture leaves sides of bowl.
Turn onto floured surface and knead until smooth.
Roll out thick and cut with round cutter. Place on baking sheet (may be brushed with melted margarine before baking).
Bake at 450° for about 20 minutes.

title: sand pail mud(kids love it)
directions: Crush all of the Oreos as finely as possible.
Save out approximately 1 cup.
Combine the rest of the crumbs with enough pudding to fill pail.
Mix in worms.
Spoon into sand pail; sprinkle rest of crumbs on top to look like black dirt.
Serve with shovel at a picnic.
A flower pot with plastic flowers works well too!

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Drain. Stir in pizza sauce, oregano and mushrooms. Refrigerate for 2 or more hours. Stir in Mozzarella cheese. Put mixture on buns and bake open-faced in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt 1/4 stick of butter in 9 x 5 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix all ingredients except fruit.
Pour into baking dish; add fruit. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until batter is completely done. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: mazurki(polish strawberry cookies)
directions: Combine margarine with flour.
Mix 3 ounces of sugar with 2 eggs.
Beat into margarine-flour combination.
Spread on ungreased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan.
Spread preserves on dough.
Combine 1/2 pound of sugar with 4 eggs and vanilla.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour over top of preserves and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour longer.
When cool, dust with confectioners sugar.
Cut into diamond shapes.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: very special chili
directions: In large saucepan, brown beef in oil.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until meat is tender.
Garnish with chopped onion.
If desired, serve with additional hot pepper sauce.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: oatmeal cookies(these are nutty delicious!)
directions: Cream together butter and brown and white sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, soda and baking powder.
Add flour to butter mixture.
Mix well.
Add cups of oatmeal and pecans or walnuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Drop by tablespoon for larger cookie.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Pour cake mix into bowl.
Take 1 cup dry cake mix and set aside.
Take remaining cake mix and add 1 egg and 1/2 cup butter. Pour mixture into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Take pumpkin.
Add 2 eggs, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg and milk.
Pour mixture over bottom layer.
Take remaining cake mix and add 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup butter.
Mix until crumbly. Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate glaze
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler. Blend in butter and milk.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, vanilla and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Thin with cream if necessary.

title: tapioca
directions: Add the tapioca to the boiling water; boil for 15 minutes. Cover; let stand 15 minutes.
Add the jello and sugar.
Add the fruit, juice and all.

title: egg white cookies
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Add sugar slowly to egg whites, beating after each addition.
Fold in coconut, dates and nuts. Put small spoonfuls on foil paper on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° about 10-12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: blueberry cheese dessert
directions: Mix well.
Spread evenly in an 11 x 7-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake 25 minutes in a 375° oven.
Cool!

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish (or use non-stick spray).
Put all ingredients in dish and stir.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken n' peaches
directions: Place cut up chicken in a 9 x 13 baking dish.
Combine peach syrup, lemon juice, soy sauce and peach halves.
Pour over chicken.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours. Baste often.

title: veal with rice and sour cream
directions: Brown veal in oil.
Add onion, garlic and green pepper; cook a few minutes.
Add parsley and broth; simmer, covered, 15 minutes. Add rice and stir.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Slowly stir in sour cream.
Season to taste and cover.
Cook 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: quick salad
directions: Mix jello and cottage cheese well.
Stir in crushed pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Mix and chill.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add vanilla and Milnot.
Add pineapple or strawberries.
Pour into ice cream freezer and fill with milk to fill line, then freeze.

title: hamantaschen
directions: Cream sugar, oil and shortening, then add eggs and juice.
Mix well.
Blend in dry ingredients.

title: flying saucers
directions: Cream first four ingredients together and add Karo. Mix rest of ingredients together in separate bowl and then add to creamed mixture.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet by tablespoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Break cake into pieces and place in oblong dish.
Cover cake with crushed pineapple, juice included.
In a separate bowl, mix pudding according to directions on box and pour over cake and pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: russian salad
directions: Melt jello, water and marshmallows over low heat until dissolved, then cool.
Add and mix the other ingredients and chill until set.
Keep refrigerated.

title: 10 cup cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder together.
Add to other mixture.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet for 10 to 13 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add egg, milk and shortening.
Stir just to moisten dry ingredients.
Put in greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: taco bake
directions: Brown ground chuck in skillet along with the onion.
Drain. Add the water, taco seasoning and tomato sauce; mix.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in macaroni, chilies and 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 6 servings.
Budget stretcher.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Wash and pierce squash with a fork.
Place on paper towel in microwave. Cook 8 minutes on High power. Turn halfway through cooking time. Cut in half.
Remove seeds.
Mix the brown sugar, butter, applesauce, pecans and cinnamon all together.
Fill cavity with the ingredients.
Return to cook for 4 minutes on High. Yields 4 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples, 1 cup sugar, brown sugar, lemon juice and cinnamon in long baking pan.
Mix flour, sugar, oats and grated cheese with margarine until it looks like coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: pink lady punch
directions: Slowly add cranberry juice to sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add chilled pineapple juice.
Slowly add ginger ale just before serving.
Makes 32 servings.

title: barbecued baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Saute onion and green pepper in bacon fat. Do not brown.
Combine all ingredients except uncooked bacon in baking dish.
Top with the uncooked bacon.
Bake 1 hour.
Set under broiler to crisp bacon.

title: agnes' hungarian goulash
directions: Boil water to cover meat and boil 5 minutes.
Lower heat to simmer and cook 1 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes, salt, pepper and carrots.
Save juice for thickening.
Cook noodles; drain and add to large pan of mixture.
Mix 1/2 stick margarine with flour like for white sauce and add to juices, then add to meat mixture.

title: christmas slaw
directions: Chop first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil vinegar, sugar, mustard, salt, turmeric and celery seed.
Cool and pour over chopped ingredients.
Mix and store in covered container.
Will keep up to 2 weeks.

title: hand dipped chocolates
directions: Mix and roll into balls.
Let dry for 1/2 hour.
Dip in white or	dark coating bark.
(Hershey candy bars can be used for coating.)
Add
1 tablespoon paraffin to the dip if it is real stiff.
Refrigerate between heatings, or hide.
Use a low heat for melting coating.

title: mayonnaise muffins
directions: Mix well and place in 12 greased muffin tins.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Should be golden brown.

title: barbecue frankfurters
directions: Mix all ingredients, except frankfurters, and simmer for 20 minutes. Cut franks into bite-size pieces and add to the sauce. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: grape pickles
directions: Use
half
gallon
jar.
Use 3-inch cucumbers or cut up larger ones.
Put cucumbers in jars, leaving about an inch at the
top of	the
jar.
Add 2 tablespoons salt (not piled), 1 bunch	green grapes
(small)
and 1 cup hot vinegar.
Fill to about
1-inch from
the top.
Put in 6-inches of the end of a grapevine (tender end).
Fill with boiling water.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice dough into 1/8-inch slices and place on 12-inch pizza pan, overlapping edges. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool.

title: crock-pot - quick beef stroganoff
directions: Place beef, soups, and water in crock-pot; cook on low 8 hours.
Serve over noodles.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and margarine; pour into greased oblong pan.
Mix sugar, 2 eggs, cream cheese and pecans.
Pour on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, milk and lemon juice.
Pour into large graham cracker crust.
Top with the pie filling.
Add a little sugar to the pie filling (if desired). Change flavors of pies by changing pie filling.

title: chicken supremes in vermouth
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken.
Mix the 5 seasonings in a dish. Heat butter and oil in a skillet.
Dip each breast into seasonings (both sides) and saute just until opaque.
Place in shallow baking dish and bake, uncovered, in 300° oven about 20 minutes.
Using same skillet, add cream and vermouth.
Stir and simmer until sauce has thickened.
Pour sauce over chicken and serve.

title: cebiche
directions: Combine all ingredients, except corn and sweet potatoes and refrigerate two hours.
To serve place in a large dish.
Garnish with the corn and sweet potatoes.
Serving size:

title: fish baked with summer squash
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Coat a 9 x 12-inch pan with oil. Spread half vegetables.
Lay fish on top.
Cover fish with remaining vegetables.
Sprinkle lemon juice, salt and pepper. Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 45 minutes.
Just before serving, sprinkle with herbs.
Serves 4.

title: grandma's  rhubarb  crisp
directions: Layer
a
10 x 15 in. pan with rhubarb. Sprinkle with white sugar. Cover with the mixture of flour, sugar, and butter. Bake at 400°F for 20 minutes.

title: no bake coconut cookies
directions: In bowl, combine oats, nuts and coconut.
In saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Bring to boil for 1 minute. Add vanilla.
Remove from heat and pour over ingredients in bowl; mix.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Let stand until firm, about 10 minutes.

title: venison stew
directions: Cut deer meat in small cubes,
peel potatoes and cut into bite-sizes.
Peel and slice carrots.
Cut green pepper in strips. Dredge meat in flour and place in heavy kettle.
Add seasonings, onion and garlic.
Brown.
Add potatoes and carrot.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat to simmer until vegetables are done.
Stir.
Before serving, add peas and green pepper.
Cook until peas are tender.

title: low calorie dressing mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl and blend well.
Put mixture in a foil packet or a 1 pint glass jar and label as Low Calorie Dressing Mix. Store in a cool, dry place and use within 6 months.
Makes enough mix for 3/4 cup of dressing.

title: jalapeno cheese dip
directions: In the top of a double boiler set over simmering water, combine the bread crumbs, the milk and the cheeses and cook the mixture, stirring, until the cheeses are melted.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli according to package directions.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Mix all ingredients together; place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: poor man's gingerbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together with exception of sugar. Lightly flour raisins.
Cream margarine and sugar; add egg and blend.
Stir in molasses.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Add orange rind.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.
Delicious with chips or raw vegetables.

title: pearl's butterscotch pie
directions: Mix all together and cook over double boiler until thick and creamy, stirring constantly.

title: orange jello mold
directions: In bowl, mix Jell-O with 2 cups hot water.
Stir well until dissolved, then add 1 cup cold water.
Stir well.
Add sour cream and beat with mixer just until blended (takes just a few seconds).
Add mandarin oranges with juice and almonds.
Stir and pour into Jell-O mold.
Chill until firm.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Pour a little butter in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix juice of 1 can of asparagus with mushroom soup.
Layer:
crackers, cheese, asparagus, 1 1/2 eggs, asparagus and mushroom mixture.
Pour butter over top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: "b.l.t.  salad"
directions: In large bowl, mix mayonnaise, chili sauce, lemon juice and sugar.
Mix elbows, onions and tomatoes into dressing.
Before serving, add bacon and lettuce.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: ice pick cake
directions: Combine cake mix with olive oil, apricot nectar and the 4 egg yolks; beat well for 4 minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into cake batter.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Combine cocoa and butter; melt over low heat.
Remove from heat; mix in sugar and eggs.
Add flour, salt and vanilla.
Mix well; add nuts.
Bake at 350° in 13 x 9-inch pan for 35 minutes. Sprinkle marshmallows on hot cake.

title: hot milk cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs at high speed until thick, about 5 minutes.
Gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to batter with vanilla and beat at low speed until smooth.
In a saucepan, heat milk and butter just until the butter melts, stirring occasionally.
Add to batter, beating until combined.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool on wire rack.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.
This cake is wonderful with fresh strawberries or peaches and whipped cream or broiled frosting or 7 Minute Icing (recipe follows).

title: jim gilliam's julio sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients in food processor until desired consistency.

title: dirt cups
directions: Mix all ingredients together; it should look like dark brown dirt.
Put in eight to ten 7-ounce paper or plastic cups.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle the rice in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange the fryer on top of the rice. Dilute the chicken soup with the water.
Pour over the chicken. Sprinkle the onion soup mix over all. Bake, covered, for 2 hours at 350°.

title: old-fashioned cookies
directions: Put sifted dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Make a well and add buttermilk, eggs, lard and vanilla; mix well.
Place a small amount on a lightly floured board.
Roll 1/8 inch thick and cut into cookies.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: egg a la king
directions: In a frying pan, cook mushrooms in butter until lightly browned.
Blend in soup.
Slice eggs lengthwise into quarters. Add eggs, pimiento and parsley to mixture, stirring gently.
Cook until heated.
Serves 6.

title: cherry squares
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray an 8-inch square baking pan with a nonstick coating.
Combine sugar, oats, nuts, oleo and flour. Mix until crumbly with fork.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of crumbly mixture.
Spread the remainder in the bottom of the pan.
Spread pie filling evenly over crumb crust.
Sprinkle reserved crumb mixture over top.
Press gently into filling.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until browned.
Good served warm with whipped topping.

title: tempting cheese crepes
directions: Combine the flour, salt and eggs; beat until smooth. Gradually add milk, mixing until well blended.
For each crepe, pour 1/4 cup batter into hot, lightly greased 8-inch skillet or crepe pan, tilting skillet to cover bottom.
Cook over medium-high heat until lightly browned on both sides, turning once.

title: pumpkin loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well 2 (9 x 5-inch) pans.
In large bowl with fork, mix flour and next 7 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until just blended.
Turn batter into pans.
Bake 1 hour or until toothpick comes out dry.

title: quick and easy strawberry dessert
directions: Place vanilla wafers in bottom of a glass or Tupperware dish. Then slice strawberries over wafers.
Mix very good Eagle Brand milk and 1 1/2 cups water.
Mix pudding and Cool Whip.
Then mix all together and pour over strawberries and vanilla wafers.

title: beef stroganoff supreme
directions: Cut beef into small bite size strips. Brown in skillet with cooking oil, onion and mushrooms until tender. Cook egg noodles. Put noodles in lightly greased Pyrex dish or pan. Spread meat mixture over noodles. Add 1/2 soup can of milk to mushroom soup and pour over casserole. Salt and pepper to taste. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
(This is a good way to use leftover roast.)

title: maurine's bread rolls(very good)
directions: Trim crust off bread. Beat the cream cheese, egg and sugar together well. Spread on bread. Fold over into a roll. Roll in melted oleo. Roll again in a mixture of cinnamon and sugar. Put on a cookie sheet. Freeze before baking. Cook any time later. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown and drain chuck and sausage.
Add oregano, garlic, Worcestershire and cheese to hot, drained meat.
Heat on low until cheese melts, stirring several times.
Spoon onto rye bread; place onto cookie sheets.
(Can be made ahead to this point.
Freeze for about 1 hour and put into freezer bags for storage.
Partly thaw before baking.)
Heat for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot. They disappear like diamonds or liquid gold.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into small balls and then in confectioners sugar.
Bake at 350° on a greased cookie sheet.

title: salsa cheese dip
directions: Melt Velveeta and butter together. Brown meat and onion.
Mix all ingredients together. Serve warm with Tostito chips.

title: fudge royale ice cream cake
directions: Crush cookies and reserve 1 cup for topping.
Press the remainder in a 9 x 13-inch glass or plastic container.
Melt ice cream and pour over cookie layer.
Freeze.
Soften hot fudge topping and spread over ice cream.
Freeze.
Spread on whipped topping and sprinkle with reserved crumbs and nuts.
Freeze.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip, blending well.
Stir in mini chips.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook milk and sugar until forms soft ball.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow.
Beat until thick.
Pour in greased pan and cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Slice strawberries and place in baked pie shell. Mix sugar, flour, jello and water in a boiler and stir over low heat until thickened.
Pour over strawberries. Top with Cool Whip if desired.

title: microwave cheese sauce
directions: Microwave ingredients in 1 1/2-quart bowl on High 2 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes or until cheese is melted, stirring every minute. Serve on hot cooked pasta, vegetables or fish.
Makes 1 cup.

title: banana pickles
directions: Boil the vinegar, sugar, turmeric, water, salt and mustard together.
Pour into jars over pickles.
Process 10 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Combine ingredients in order.
Spread in a shallow greased pan. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Combine the first five ingredients.
Pour into 13-inch greased pan.
Slice bread 1/2-inch thick.
Put bread on top of casserole. Beat the rest of ingredients together and pour on top. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: layered banana pineapple dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press to form a crust.
Arrange banana slices on top of crust.

title: al's potato salad
directions: Mash potatoes and add ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: butter pecan pound cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, vanilla pudding and oil together. Then add hot water and nuts. Grease tube pan, pour batter into pan. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until the middle is done. Check with a tooth pick.

title: seasoned crackers
directions: Sprinkle seasonings over crackers and pour 1 cup Wesson oil over all and mix well.
Bake in shallow pan 25 minutes at 250°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add to hamburger taco mix and water. Refrigerate to cool.
After hamburger mixture has cooled, mix together lettuce, onion, celery, tomatoes, scallions and black olives.
Just before serving, add Doritos.
Use Caesar salad dressing (not creamy) at end or put on individual salads.

title: pancakes and waffles
directions: Combine eggs, milk and melted shortening.
Add dry ingredients and beat until free from lumps.

title: caramel dreams
directions: Mix the ingredients and let them cook on a moderate fire an hour.
Stir at intervals, with your big spoon.
Then pour on a greased dish.
Pull off caramel size squares and wrap each separately in waxed paper.

title: bananas
directions: Just put it in the oven.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in oil and remove from pan.
Add onion and brown.
Add other ingredients.
Cook, covered, approximately 15 minutes.
Return chops and cook, covered, for about 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: french fries
directions: Slice potatoes as you would for French fries.
Drop in boiling water and boil for 4 minutes.
Drain and pat dry.
Spread on cookie sheet and spray lightly with Pam.
Sprinkle with salt and paprika.
Broil 4 minutes.
Turn over and broil 4 minutes more.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Toss potatoes with cheese, mayonnaise, onion and seasonings. Turn into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Combine bacon bits, olives and relish. Spread over salad mixture. Bake at 325° until thoroughly heated, about 45 minutes. Can be prepared ahead and refrigerated. If cold, heat an hour. Leftovers are good warmed over. Serves 10.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend together shortening, sugars and eggs until fluffy.
Add flour, baking powder and soda.
Add oats and chocolate chips.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cook less for soft chewier cookies.
Cool some before removing from cookie sheet.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions and bell pepper.
Mix soup, mushrooms and tomatoes.
Add meat and cooked noodles. Put into large casserole dish.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes until bubbly. Remove from oven and cover with grated cheese.
Return to oven just until cheese melts.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Line muffin tin with foil liners.
Place one vanilla wafer in each liner.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar on medium speed until well-blended.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Pour over wafers, filling 3/4 full.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Remove from pan when cool.
Chill.
Top with cherries.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate, butter and salt together in double boiler. Add the sugar, 1/2 cup at a time, stirring after each addition. Add the evaporated milk, a little at a time, and continue stirring until well mixed.
Serve over ice cream while hot and sprinkle with Spanish peanuts, if desired.
Makes 3 cups sauce.
Store extra sauce in refrigerator.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until done and drain.
Mix together soup, cheese, egg, mayonnaise and onion.
Then add broccoli and mix well.
Pour into greased casserole.
Mix crushed Ritz crackers and butter; put over top of broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tessie's pound cake
directions: Blend margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and then flour.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: taco dip i
directions: In a 9 x 13 glass pan, spread cream cheese on bottom of pan. Pour chili beans over cream cheese. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top. Bake in 375° oven until cheese is melted. Serve with nacho chips.

title: great punch
directions: Mix lemonade and pineapple juice; add ice cream.
Pour in ginger ale.
To stretch, add more ginger ale.

title: new orleans rice
directions: Saute chestnuts and mushrooms in oleo.
Add water to liquid to equal 1 cup.
Ad rice, onion soup and liquid in baking dish.
Then add sauteed chestnuts and mushrooms.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato donuts
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Then mix with other liquids.
Add dry ingredients that have been sifted.
Mix well.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness on floured board.
Cut and deep fry in oil or lard at 365° to 375°.

title: 60-minute raised rolls
directions: Crumble yeast into lukewarm water.
Set aside until it pops to top of water.
