title: party pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and dressing mix.
Add ham, cheese and onions.
Put 2 to 3 tablespoons of mixture on tortilla shells; roll tight.
(You'll be able to judge how much mixture to put on a tortilla shell.)
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.
Cut into 1 inch pieces.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend together cheese soup, milk, pepper, sliced potatoes and onion.
In buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, put alternate layers of potatoes, onion and sauce.
Dot with butter.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover.
Bake 15 minutes more or until potatoes are done.

title: carol's potatoes
directions: Put potatoes in 11 x 17-inch casserole.
Saute onions in butter and pour over potatoes.
Mix Cheez Whiz, soup, milk and sour cream; pour over potatoes.
Top with corn chips.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spice raisin crisps
directions: Place racks in upper third of the oven and preheat to 350°. In a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat butter, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy, about 1 minute. Add eggs and mix until thoroughly incorporated. Add oats, flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Mix on low speed until blended. Add nuts and raisins; mix on medium speed. Drop batter by heaping tablespoon 1 1/2-inches apart onto a greased baking sheet. Bake for 10 to 13 minutes or until golden brown. Cookies will feel soft, but will firm up as they cool. Let stand on baking sheet 2 minutes before transferring to racks to cool. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: lillie's ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until lemon colored.
Add rest of ingredients and stir to incorporate.
Finish by adding enough whole milk to fill ice cream container.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Soften Butter; add Sugar, Flour, Lemon Juice, Salt, Egg Yolks and Lemon Rind.
Beat together until well blended.
Stir in milk and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into pie shell and bake in moderate oven 375 degrees for 15 minutes.
Then 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; cut into small pieces.
Cook spaghetti.
Saute onion.
Mix all together.
Add soups and Velveeta cheese.
Add enough milk to moisten.

title: chili
directions: Let cook for 3 hours or more.

title: 1817 plantation eggs
directions: Mix eggs, parsley, pepper and salt together well.
Add cubes of cheese.
Brown sausage, breaking into small pieces.
Drain well.
Cover bottom of casserole dish with sausage.
Pour egg mixture on top.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: stir-fry cabbage
directions: Oil pan; heat and add onion.
Cook until clear.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until crisp, about 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: honey wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Heat milk and 2 cups of water to lukewarm.
Add salt, oil and honey.
Mix flours together in a very large bowl.
Stir in water and milk mixture, then add yeast liquid.
Finish kneading by hand.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Heat milk to boiling point and stir into sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir until slightly thickened.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Thaw lemonade concentrate and whipped topping.
Combine lemonade, condensed milk and food coloring; mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Put in graham cracker crust and freeze until firm (4 hours or overnight).
Garnish with lemon slices or whipped topping, if desired.

title: mom's rolled oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, sift together sugar, salt and soda. Add brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Add oats.
Work with fingers until dough just holds together. Sprinkle board lightly with confectioners sugar.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut with cookie cutters which have been dipped in confectioners sugar. Bake on greased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool and decorate.
Recipe from Mary Kobinski.

title: scalloped pineapples
directions: Mix flour, sugar, juice and margarine. Put pineapple and cheese in a greased casserole dish. Pour liquid mixture over pineapple and cheese and stir. Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot milk coconut cake
directions: Add melted butter to milk while hot. Beat eggs and sugar and cream well. Add sifted flour and milk mixture alternately while warm. Bake in layers as any other butter cake. Use the filling. Makes 3 layers.

title: beverly slimm's now you see it now you don't
directions: Fold vanilla pudding into pineapple.
Add rest of ingredients. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Mix together.
Put into uncovered dish.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Coat tomatoes in flour/cornmeal mixture; salt and pepper.
Place in heavy skillet containing bacon drippings.
Fry slowly until very brown, turning once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Put mixture into lightly greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix and boil for 3 minutes.
Then beat with mixer until creamy. Great with yellow sheet cake.

title: stuffed clams
directions: Mix well.
Spoon into greased clam shells.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs on sheet at 375° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: dream corn
directions: Place corn in skillet; put in butter.
Stir until brown and add lemon pepper and sugar.
Cook for 2 minutes; let simmer for 5 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: hasty cake
directions: Combine butter and egg white; beat well.
Gradually add powdered sugar, beating well.
Gently stir in vanilla.
Spread on cake.

title: shrimp parmesan
directions: Shell and devein shrimp.
Arrange in a shallow baking dish. Pour melted butter and lemon juice over shrimp.
Combine last 4 ingredients and sprinkle over shrimp.
Microwave at High 6 to 8 minutes, uncovered.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain well.
Add soups, seasonings and green chilies.
Layer into a greased 2-quart casserole dish. Start bottom layer with tortillas, layer of hamburger mixture and continue to layer with tortillas, ending with tortillas as last layer.
Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.
For extra zip, add some picante sauce.

title: sweet-sour cabbage
directions: Put first 6 ingredients all together in a very large kettle and boil about 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients (can use more or less to taste).
Cook another 15 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Melt margarine for 30 seconds.
Add cocoa; stir.
Put back in microwave and cover with wax paper.
Put on High for 2 minutes, then take out and stir.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour in pan to harden.
Makes good cake or brownie topping.

title: sweet potatoes with marshmallows
directions: Cover sweet potatoes or yams with water and boil until tender (test with fork).
Remove skins and mash sweet potatoes until smooth.
Add canned cream or milk to the consistency you like. Add 2 or 3 tablespoons butter.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: You will need one 9 x 13-inch pan and wax paper.

title: tuna souffle
directions: In a small bowl, beat the eggs.
Soak the bread with the milk. In a pan, saute the onion and tomatoes in butter.
Mix all these ingredients with the tuna fish.
Bring to oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet roll dough
directions: Stir yeast into warm water to dissolve. Stir in milk, sugar, salt, eggs, shortening and half of the flour.
Stir until smooth. Add remaining flour.
Knead for 5 minutes.
Let rise until double. Punch down until double again.
Shape into cloverleaf rolls, sandwich buns, cinnamon rolls, etc.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cherokee bean bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a large bowl. Add milk, water and egg. Beat until mixed well. Add beans and ham just until mixed. Pour into well-greased heavy skillet or pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes. Top should be slightly browned.

title: surprise chicken
directions: Soak chicken in Italian dressing overnight. Pat it dry a little; roll in Ritz cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili egg puff
directions: In a bowl, beat the eggs until light and lemon colored. Add flour, baking powder, salt, cottage cheese, Jack cheese (grated) and melted butter. Mix, then stir in chilies. Pour into a buttered 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Combine the dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar.
Mix together the dry and creamed ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time. Stir in peppermint, orange peel and zucchini.
Put into well-greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp in cream cheese sauce
directions: Thaw, clean and drain shrimp on paper towels.
Press to remove all excess moisture.

title: crock-pot apple butter(serves 60)
directions: Cook apples and apple cider 10 to 14 hours. Cub through colander (optional). Then add sugar, cinnamon and cloves. Cook an additional 2 to 3 hours. Cook: 17:00.

title: banana cake
directions: Sift together flour and soda.
Set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk alternately to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Then add vanilla, bananas and nuts, mixing thoroughly.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until a soft dough forms.
Beat for 30 seconds.
Drop the dough by spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet (approximately 1-inch in diameter).
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix margarine and garlic powder and brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Serve warm.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Cream the sugar, cream cheese and oleo together well.
Line a 9 x 13-inch dish with graham crackers and spread creamed mixture over the crackers.
Drain crushed pineapple and spread over the creamed mixture. Spread drained apples and sliced bananas over the pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with chopped pecans. Chill.

title: james fried chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in buttermilk with Dales and tabasco overnight.

title: overnight vegetable salad
directions: Drain vegetables.
Heat onion, sugar, wine vinegar and salt and pepper.
Heat until dissolved and pour over vegetables. Refrigerate over night.
Will keep a few days in refrigerator.

title: sweet potato pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and butter; add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine next 4 ingredients, stirring well.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in sweet potatoes and flavorings.
Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan; sprinkle almonds and coconut over bottom.
Pour batter into pan; bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan.
Yields one 10-inch (delicious) cake.

title: purple poke cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes. Then poke cake with a fork every 1/2 inch.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add cold water.
Pour over cake in pan.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cake frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thickened.
Let cool.
Cream the shortening, butter and sugar.
Add cooled flour and milk mixture, tablespoon by tablespoon, beating all the time with mixer.
When finished, it will be like whipped cream.

title: carrot salad
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in 1 1/2 cups water.
Add pineapple and lemon juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: quicky salads(fast, cheap, easy)
directions: Mix together and keep in refrigerator.

title: gingersnap pot roast
directions: In 1 large pot with lid, brown meat on all sides in 1 tablespoon of oil; after this is done, cut onion and brown in with meat and oil.
When finished, add water to halfway up meat.
Add 4 gingersnaps, broken up.
Cover and simmer three to four hours. About 1 hour before done, peel and cut carrots and break 6 more cookies and place in pot.
Gingersnaps make your gravy; check to make sure water is not down too low.
When carrots are done, enjoy. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and let stand 1 hour; drain.

title: outdoor pot roast
directions: Place roast on lowest level of grill.
(Coals should be ash gray in appearance.)
Sear 10 minutes on first side; turn and sear 5 minutes.
Transfer to a large sheet of heavy aluminum foil; shape sides to form pan.
Combine remaining ingredients except potatoes together in bowl.
Pour over roast.
Close foil.
Adjust grill temperature.
Cook 1 hour; turn roast in sauce.
Add potatoes; close foil and continue cooking 1 hour more or until meat and potatoes are tender.
Serves 8 to 10.
Very delicious. This recipe is from the Cross Lutheran Church Cookbook, Burlington, Wisconsin.
I have used it many times and was enjoyed by all.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, drain and mash and mix with other ingredients. Put in greased casserole.
Cover with more cracker crumbs. Drizzle oleo over the top of crumbs.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned and bubbly.
Very good!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: noodle pudding
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and lemon juice.
Beat in cottage cheese and sour cream.
Fold in the cooked, drained noodles.
Place in ungreased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: i can't believe it's so easy hot bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well in a casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips or Fritos.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Combine flour, meal, salt, sugar and baking powder and mix well.
Add beaten eggs and milk together and pour slowly into dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Add melted margarine.
Pour into an 8-inch square baking pan that has been greased and bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 16 servings.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, ginger and cinnamon.
Add molasses, butter and soda.
Dough will be stiff.
Chill overnight.
Take out of refrigerator and let it get to room temperature.
Work small pieces, about large biscuit size, in hands until soft.
Roll out thin and cut cookies.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 12 minutes, depending on thickness.

title: freezer rhubarb jam
directions: Combine rhubarb, pie filling and sugar.
Boil slowly 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in Jell-O.
Cool.
Spoon into jars.
Put into freezer.
Makes 9 pints.

title: pumpkin apple streusel muffins
directions: In large bowl combine first 5 ingredients.
In medium bowl, mix eggs, pumpkin and oil.
Add the two bowls together.
Add apples and mix.
Spoon into greased or papered muffin tins.
Fill 3/4 full.

title: cold mexico dish
directions: Use large platter and spread beans from can.
Spread dip over bean layer.
Top with sour cream.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients over top of sour cream in order listed.
Arrange chips around border of tray at edge of beans.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini lightly and drain.
Mix stuffing with butter. Mix all ingredients with 1/2 the stuffing.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and top with the other half of the stuffing.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: papa bear's super-duper juice
directions: Mix fruit juices.
Place ice cream in punch bowl.
Add juices. Pour ginger ale into bowl just before serving.
Makes 20 small servings.

title: favorite "taters"
directions: Bake in oven for 35 to 60 minutes until bubbly hot.
Serve.

title: lemon coconut squares
directions: Mix the flour, 1/2 cup brown sugar and butter together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 275° for 10 minutes. Combine eggs, 1 cup brown sugar, coconut, nuts, flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla and spread on crust.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Frost while warm with:

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Boil raisins and water for 5 minutes and let cool.
Cream the margarine and sugar together; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, ginger and cloves.
Add to creamed mixture, blending well.
Stir in raisins and 1 cup chopped nuts may be added, if desired.
Drop by tablespoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, oleo and brown sugar.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzel crust. Dissolve jello with boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Let thicken and then put on top of cream cheese mixture.

title: magic meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Press firmly into ungreased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about an hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: bean spread
directions: Combine.
Makes a delicious sandwich spread.
May also add fresh, chopped onions.

title: inside out ravioli
directions: Cook hamburg, onions and garlic.
When brown, add juice from spinach and all tomato sauces.
Let simmer 10 minutes.
Cook spinach as instructed on package.
Drain and reserve juice, add water to make 1 cup to add to meat mixture.
Mix eggs, bread crumbs, spinach and cheese.
Then mix with macaroni and spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread meat mixture over macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand before serving.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick stuck in the center comes out clean.

title: family's favorite potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in skins and allow to cool.
Peel potatoes and cut into small cubes, placing them in large bowl.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Stir gently to mix.
Peel eggs and place in small mixing bowl.
Chop eggs fine with fork or pastry cutter.
Add remaining ingredients to eggs and stir until well mixed and creamy.
Pour egg mixture over salad and stir until mixed thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate until time to serve.

title: angel biscuits(an easy yeast bread and most delicious)
directions: Mix together yeast, sugar and lukewarm water.
Sift together flour, soda, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening using pastry blender.
Add buttermilk and the yeast mixture.
Mix well into dough.
If additional flour is needed, sift amount required.
Keep in refrigerator and roll out as needed.

title: carrot cake with chocolate cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until mixture is light.
Add the eggs, one at a time, and beat.
Add the flour, salt, cinnamon and soda; beat for 1 minute, until blended.
Add rest of ingredients; beat until blended.
Put into 2 buttered layer pans (with removable bottoms).
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove rings; let cool.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix in a large bowl the oleo, flour and sugar. Mix well. Shape in small balls or half moon shapes. Bake for 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: asparagus with lemon sauce
directions: Combine egg, butter, sugar and cornstarch in top of a double boiler.
Cook for 3 minutes, until mixture begins to thicken.
Add lemon juice.
Stir constantly an additional 2 to 3 minutes, or until slightly thickened.
Pour over asparagus.
Sprinkle with lemon rind.

title: hamburger and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Brown ground beef, pepper and onion.
Drain. Combine with cooked rice, cheese (melted), soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes covered with foil.
Bake 15 minutes longer, uncovered.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix oil, white vinegar and sugar.
Pour over cabbage, sweet peppers, onions and carrots.
Let stand overnight.

title: choco peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all together; pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: quick english toffee(tastes like heath bar)
directions: In a buttered 9-inch pie plate, sprinkle pecans.
Melt butter in a small, heavy saucepan.
Add sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until it reaches 290° on a candy thermometer. Pour over nuts.

title: holiday bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water plus sugar for 5 minutes.
Scald milk.
Add oleo.
Mix eggs, salt and remaining sugar together. When just warm, combine the 2 mixtures.
Add about 4 cups flour; mix well.
Beat for a few minutes.
Add enough flour to make dough handle nicely.
Set to rise for about 1 hour.
Divide dough in 6 parts.
Make 2 braided loaves.
Place loaves in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Gets better with age.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Add all ingredients into cooked macaroni except crackers and butter.
Pour into greased casserole dish and top with Ritz crackers.
Dot with pats of butter or margarine and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Tent with foil if topping browns too quickly.

title: frozen pineapple pie
directions: Stir together the condensed milk and Cool Whip until well blended.
Fold in the pineapple.
Pour into pie crust and freeze about 4 hours.
Serve.

title: jambalaya
directions: In large skillet, cook first 5 ingredients in Wesson oil until onion is soft.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 40 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Great way to use leftover meats.
I usually serve mine over rice, also!

title: blueberry pinwheel cobbler
directions: Combine sugar
and
water
in
saucepan; then stir well until sugar
dissolves.
Stir
in vanilla and lemon juice. Set aside. Cut
Crisco
into
flour until mixture resembles meal. Add milk and stir until dry ingredients are moist.
Turn dough onto floured surface and knead lightly 4 to 5 times.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs. Mix dry ingredients; add alternately with bananas to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts. Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until done.
(Insert toothpick into center; if it comes out clean, bread is done.)
When thoroughly cool, wrap in foil and store in refrigerator or freeze.
Flavor improves after refrigeration.

title: baked onions
directions: Layer thinly sliced onions in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 bag of crushed potato chips over onions.
Sprinkle cheese over chips.
Start again with onions and repeat layers.
Mix soup and milk together, pour over casserole.
Salt and pepper lightly to taste.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: angel pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in top of double boiler.
Add boiling water and mix well.
Cook in double boiler until thick. Remove from fire and cool.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg and vanilla.
Put in pie shell which has been baked and cooled.
Chill at least 2 hours or overnight.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip when ready to serve.

title: diced potatoes
directions: Mix soup and potatoes and stir in a 14-inch Dutch oven. Salt and
pepper
to
taste.
Cook 1 hour with 14 coals on top and 12 coals on the bottom.
Add cheese with 10 minutes to go.

title: glazed cornish hens
directions: Sprinkle hens inside and out with salt and rosemary.
Roast in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
While hens are roasting, chop apricots; add to applesauce and wine in medium saucepan.
Stir in orange rind, brown sugar and ground cloves.
Simmer for about 30 minutes, until apricots are tender.
Spoon glaze over hens; roast 30 minutes longer.

title: chicken divan
directions: Sprinkle breasts with seasonings.
Bake, covered, 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Chill and bone.
Cook broccoli until tender.
Place spears across greased 2-quart dish.
Add breasts.
Combine soup, dressing, lemon juice and curry.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. This may be prepared a day ahead and refrigerated.

title: glazed apple loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pans (one 9 x 5-inches, two 8 x 4-inches or six 5 x 3-inches).
Sift flour, salt and soda; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl beat oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg until well blended.
Add dry ingredients and mix until smooth.
Fold in apples and pecans. Divide batter evenly among desired pans.
Bake in the center of 350° oven for one hour or until tested done.
Decorate with glaze.

title: baked creamed spinach
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbly and lightly brown.

title: mom's potato wedges
directions: Scrub unpeeled potatoes well.
Cut each in half lengthwise. Then cut into even wedges.
Boil wedges for 5 minutes in salted water.
Drain and pat dry.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning mix and sour cream together.
Let stand. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread bean dip on bottom of pan.
Next layer is taco seasoning mix.
Third layer is green chilies. Fourth layer is diced tomatoes.
Fifth layer is green onions. Sixth layer is Cheddar cheese and seventh layer is black olives. Use your favorite Tostitos chips.

title: mexican candy
directions: Start 2 cups sugar and 1 cup water cooking in a deep saucepan. Separately, melt 1 cup sugar; add 1 cup water and cook until thin syrup is formed.
Pour this into first mixture and cook to soft (234°) boil.
When thermometer reaches 230°, add pecans.
Remove from fire and cool undisturbed until pan can be held on hand with comfort.
Stir until creamy and drop by spoon quickly onto wax paper.
Makes 1 3/4 pounds.

title: prune cake with buttermilk icing
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with buttermilk.
Add nuts and prunes.
Pour into a buttered pan and bake at 325° about 45 minutes or possibly a little longer (when toothpick comes out clean).
Remove from oven and while still hot, cover with icing.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream the butter and blend in the molasses.
Sift the baking powder, flour and salt.
Beat the eggs and add the sour milk and honey.
Stir.
Add milk and flour alternately to the creamed butter and molasses.
Mix well.
Stir in the spices, raisins, figs and almonds.

title: donna's cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except one package of chopped beef.
Shape mixture into a ball and cover with remaining beef.
When refrigerating, leave lid off until ready to serve.

title: boiled shrimp
directions: Bring water and vinegar and seasonings to a boil. Rinse shrimp before adding to boiling water.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes after water comes to boil. Place in colander to drain-quickly refrigerate.
Serves 2.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and zucchini.
Sift flour, cinnamon, baking powder, soda, and salt.
Add to above mixture. Add vanilla and nuts.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5 inch pans.
Pour 1/2 of batter in each pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.
(Or 3 - 3 x 7 inch pans for 50 minutes.)

title: vegetable soup
directions: Place all the ingredients in a large pot. Bring to a boil, then turn heat to medium and cook for 30 minutes.

title: black bean soup
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight in water in the refrigerator. Next day, boil beans and other ingredients.
When it boils, turn to simmer until beans are tender.
Serve over rice.
Great main dish.

title: pepperoni and cheese crescent
directions: Separate dough into triangles.
Pat out each triangle.
Place 3 pepperoni slices slightly overlapping on the center of triangle. Top with cheese.
Roll starting with short side of triangle. Place point side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.

title: beets in orange sauce
directions: In a saucepan, stir together brown sugar, cornstarch, orange peel, salt and pepper.
Stir in orange juice and vinegar.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and gets bubbly.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in beets and cook until beets are hot. Serves 12.

title: tomato catsup
directions: Put the spices and garlic into a cloth bag to prevent the catsup from being dark.
Boil until the desired thickness.
Stir frequently to prevent sticking.

title: fish and fries
directions: Grease	the
bottom
and sides of a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish with cooking oil.
Arrange thawed fish fillets in a
single layer
on
the
bottom
of the dish.
(Use any fish fillets.)

title: german spatzel
directions: Mix together flour, eggs and salt.
Add water and mix.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Fill noodle press 2/3 full and squeeze into salted boiling water and cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Drain. Meanwhile, fry 12 ounces of bacon (cut into small pieces) and 1/2 onion.
Drain fat; set aside.
Add 4 ounces Gouda cheese to noodles, then bacon, stirring until melted.
Serve immediately.

title: do-dad snack mix
directions: Combine Do-Dads, pretzels, raisins, candies, nuts, crackers and sunflower seeds in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Store in airtight container.

title: boiled spice cake
directions: Place sugar, water, raisins, butter, cloves, cinnamon and salt in a stew pan and let boil.
Cool and then add baking soda and flour.
Bake in a slow oven.

title: pumpkin nut roll
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in sugar and add pumpkin and lemon juice and mix well.
Sift flour, spices, salt and baking powder and add to mixture.
Use large oblong cookie sheet with sides.
Grease and spread with wax paper and grease again.
Pour mixture onto paper. Sprinkle with 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. When done, remove from oven.
Pick up wax paper and cake and place on clean dish towel.
Roll cake and paper in towel.
Set 1 1/2 hours.
Unroll (ends may curl) and spread with filling.

title: rebecca's favorite sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a casserole dish. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: picnic beans
directions: Put the first 7 ingredients in a baking dish.
Combine the brown sugar, catsup, Worcestershire and Karo syrup.
Add mixture to beans.
Stir together.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Add water if too dry.
Do not cover.
Serves 12.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend in shortening, cheese and pimento.
Add milk to make a soft dough.
Roll out on floured board to 1/2-inch thickened.
Fold over and roll again.
Cut with biscuit cutter and place on greased cookie sheet, leaving space between so all sides can brown.
Bake at 450° for approximately 15 minutes.
Makes 36 tiny biscuits.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar together, then add liquid in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat until sugar is dissolved, then turn to medium heat for about 20 minutes.
Mix and sift the flour, baking powder and salt, then cut in the shortening.
Add milk to make a soft dough.
Roll out thin.
Add a layer of butter; sprinkle cinnamon and sugar over top of butter.
Roll like jelly roll; cut into 1 1/4-inch pieces.
Place in baking dish.
Dot with butter and sugar.
Cover with hot vinegar mixture and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes, or until done.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add gradually sugar, mixed with baking powder, vanilla and salt.
Fold in cracker crumbs and walnuts.
Put in well-greased pie pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
When cold, spread with heavy cream, whipped with vanilla and sugar to taste.
Grate chocolate on top.

title: chewy squares
directions: Melt butter in a double boiler, then add sugar; stir until dissolved. Remove from heat and add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. (Do not use an electric mixer.) Add flour, vanilla and nuts; mix well. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: rose's green beans
directions: Prepare green beans (snip and wash).
Parboil green beans (until fork goes into bean easily), not too long.
Drain beans. Place in low casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, Romano and Parmesan cheeses, oregano, salt, pepper, garlic powder and tomato sauce (don't saturate).
Cover or use aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 50 minutes, depending on size of casserole.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt the butter and chocolate or cocoa.
Mix together the sugar and salt.
Add to butter-chocolate mixture.
Add the eggs and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; bake for 45 minutes at 300°.
You may add chopped nuts to ingredients.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, two at a time, beating well after each addition.
Then add flour, one cup at a time, alternately with whipping cream and flavoring.
Pour into tube pan. Place in a cold oven.
Turn oven to 325° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Put in baking pan. Sprinkle top of casserole with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beer and onion pot roast
directions: Place pot roast in baking dish; place vegetables around meat. Sprinkle dry soup over all.
Pour beer over all.
Cover and place in 300° oven for about 3 hours.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Cream margarine and cheese together.
Add other ingredients. Form into small balls and flatten with fork on top.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: In a blender process all ingredients until creamy.
Chill.

title: molasses drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening, adding sugar.
Add molasses.
Beat egg and add.
Dissolve soda in milk.
Mix and sift flour, spices and salt. Add alternately with milk to first mix.
Add raisins.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray oblong dish with Pam or grease.
Mix nuts and coconut together and put in bottom of dish.

title: crunchy frozen punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 9 cups of boiling water.
Combine sugar with 4 cups water and bring to a boil.
Add to the Jell-O mixture and set aside to cool.
When cool, add lemon juice and pineapple juice. Mix well and freeze in plastic containers.
When ready to serve, place in hot water to loosen.
Place in large punch bowl.
Add ginger ale or 7-Up.
Makes 50 cups.
Color is determined by Jell-O used.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together and pour into two well-greased and floured bread pans.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chocolate goodies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until crumbly; spread in loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese with powdered sugar until creamy.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread in pan. Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Pour the pudding on top of the cream cheese.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Beat cream until stiff.
Fold in other ingredients. Delicious served with beef brisket and corned beef.

title: santa snacks
directions: Mix melted margarine and graham cracker crumbs.
Add coconut in baking pan; press lightly.
Sprinkle layer of chocolate chips, then chopped nuts.
Drizzle condensed milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares like brownies.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Melt margarine with Cheez Whiz.
Mix with Veg-All and put in a baking dish.
Top with an additional 1/2 stick of melted margarine and 1 roll of crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 325° until bubbly.

title: jello slush punch
directions: Mix jello and add sugar, juice and pineapple juice.
Freeze in ice cube trays.
When ready, add frozen cubes and "cold" ginger ale in punch bowl.
Mix or stir to slush.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: In a large bowl, mix Ricotta cheese, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, egg, spinach, salt, oregano and pepper.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with 8 slices bread.
Layer cheese on bread, then place ham on cheese.
Place remaining slices of bread over ham.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg, sugar and salt; add milk.
Beat in flour and baking powder.
Add melted shortening and blueberries.
Mix lightly and fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 350° until brown.

title: art's sausage muffins
directions: Simmer raisins in water 5 minutes.
Drain.
Saute sausage until almost cooked and drain off fat.
Mix sausage, brown and white sugars and eggs.
Add nuts and raisins.
Mix flour, spices and baking powder.
Stir baking soda into coffee and add flour mixture and coffee to sausage mixture.
Spoon into muffin tins; bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Mixture also can be baked in a 9-inch tube pan and baked for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend oil and sugar well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to oil and sugar.
Beat eggs slightly and add to batter.
Add vanilla. Fold in apples and nuts. Grease and flour large tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool and invert.
Add topping.

title: quick chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until tender, remove bones.
Add cream of chicken soup to broth and bouillon.
Add black pepper to taste.
Bring liquid to a boil and drop in floured dumplings a small amount at a time.
Cook until all are done then add chicken pieces back in. You can also use egg noodles.

title: hearty ham and bean soup
directions: Combine ham, water, beans, onion, Worcestershire and bay leaf in large stockpot.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until beans are almost tender, about 2 hours.
Stir in carrots.
Cover and simmer until beans are tender, about 1 hour longer.
Remove ham shank; cut off skin from bone and discard. Cut meat into chunks and return to stockpot.
Heat until hot.

title: scott's quick one dish meal chicken salad
directions: Cube chicken and drop into hot wok with oil; add liberal amounts of both Worcestershire sauces.
Brown chicken cubes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Prepare lettuce bed on a large meat platter; add all other salad ingredients to edges of platter.
Place chicken chunks on center of lettuce bed.
Serve with your favorite salad dressing and baked potatoes.

title: potato bread
directions: Warm liquid to 110°.
Add honey and yeast; whisk until yeast is dissolved.
Blend dry ingredients.
Add liquid to dry mix. Knead thoroughly.
Let rise to double.
Punch down.
Knead again. Form loaves.
Rise to double.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: chocolate peanut buddy bars
directions: In bowl, mix peanut butter and butter until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup morsels.
Spread mixture into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Immediately sprinkle remaining morsels over cookie layer.
Let stand 5 minutes or until morsels are spreadable.
Spread over cookie dough.

title: strawberry dream cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl and beat for 2 minutes.
Add 1/2 of a 10 ounce package of frozen strawberries (save the other half for icing) and beat for 1 minute.
Add oil and beat 1 minute.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 3 (8-inch) layers or 1 sheet cake and a dozen cupcakes.

title: mother's peanut butter cups
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and peanut butter for filling.
Melt chocolate, put small amount in bottom of paper candy cup.
Add small patty of peanut butter mixture, finish filling up with melted chocolate.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk in a double boiler.
Add chopped nuts and chopped cherries; mix with dry ingredients.
Add marshmallow mixture to chopped nuts mixture and mix well.
Pack in waxed paper-lined loaf pan.
Cover with foil and refrigerate for 2 to 3 days.
Slice thin to serve.

title: fried deer steak
directions: Tenderize steak by pounding with a meat tenderizer (mallet) until thin enough to fry. Place meat in a plastic bag and pour the dressing over it. Add more dressing if needed. Place in refrigerator for 3-4 hours, turning bag often to make sure meat is well coated. Remove from bag, drain well. Beat egg and milk together. Season flour. Dip in egg mixture and coat with flour. Pan fry until tender and golden brown.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add pineapple with juice and vanilla.
Mix well. Add flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Beat well.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Chill overnight.
Save a few orange slices for garnish.
Keeps several days in refrigerator.

title: minestrone
directions: Cover beans with water and refrigerate overnight.
Drain. Heat oil, add onion and celery.
Saute 8 to 10 minutes.
Add garlic and saute 2 minutes.
Add chicken broth, beans and basil. Bring to boil, lower heat and simmer one hour.
Add tomatoes, carrots, orzo and zucchini.
Return to boiling.
Lower heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: candy apples
directions: In a heavy deep 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat sugar, corn syrup, candies, 1 cup water and 1/4 teaspoon red food coloring to boil.
Cook without stirring to 290° about 20 minutes.

title: lobster dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serve with variety of crackers.

title: hawaitt fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: chocolate pumpkin brownies
directions: Add dry ingredients and beat on low until smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Use 11 x 7-inch pan. Makes 15 squares. One square = 82 cal. One square = 3 gr. fat.
Low-fat recipe.
Very moist.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Blend all ingredients until creamy.
If too thick, add reserved cucumber juice until right consistency for dip.

title: banana loaf
directions: Beat bananas until liquified; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar together; add eggs and mix well.
Then add bananas, mixing well.
Combine all dry ingredients together and add into rest of mixture.
Beat well.
Pour into large loaf pan or 2 small pans. Bake at 350° for 50 to 70 minutes (until center is done).

title: blue cheese burgers
directions: In mixing bowl, mix all ingredients together. Roll and pat out burgers to desired size. Spray broiler pan or grill rack with cooking oil spray. Cook to desired doneness.

title: scandinavian salmon loaf
directions: Mix
egg,
lemon
juice,
tablespoon
melted butter, mayonnaise and
seasonings using only 1 teaspoon of dill weed. Mix with
salmon
and add the milk.
Add crushed potato chips. Mold mixture
into
loaf.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Add 1/4 inch of water and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Roll biscuit pieces in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Arrange in greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Melt butter and stir in brown sugar.
Pour over biscuits and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nana's best steamed rice pudding
directions: Steam in double boiler for 1 hour the milk, rice and salt. Then beat eggs and sugar.
Mix in slowly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: salsa - harper
directions: Salt and pepper to taste.
In blender or food processor, combine tomatoes, spices and chilies.
Blend until smooth and chunky.
Place in large non-metallic bowl.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Let chill for 1 hour, then serve with tortilla chips.

title: raspberry bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and creamy.
Add oil, sugar, raspberries and vanilla.
Mix lightly but well.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Pour into two greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: aunt nancy's cheese pudding
directions: Cut crusts off bread.
Butter both sides and cut in fourths. Alternate layers of cheese and bread in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, ending with cheese on top layer.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add the other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie(early settler's version)
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients together.
Add scalded milk and beaten egg whites.
Filling will seem quite thin.
Pour into 10-inch crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake another 45 minutes.

title: orange birthday cake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly grease a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with butter. Sift the flour, baking soda and salt together. Set aside. Cream the butter, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and orange zest together in a medium-size mixing bowl until light and fluffy, about 2 minutes. Add eggs 1 at a time until each yolk is partially blended, 10 seconds. Scrape bowl after each addition. Fold in half the dry ingredients with the rubber spatula until partially incorporated, then turn the mixer to low and blend for several seconds. Repeat with the remaining dry ingredients. Finish by hand with a few broad strokes of the spatula. Spread evenly in the pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Allow to cool completely on a rack while preparing the glaze.

title: cream cheese delights
directions: With a wet knife, cut block of cream cheese longways into 4 or 5 bars.
Roll each bar of cream cheese in 1 or 2 slices of meat. Place a toothpick about every inch or so on each roll and push an olive on each one.
Then slice apart and place on your favorite plate or tray.

title: fruit dressing
directions: Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth. Stir in preserves, lemon juice and curry. Chill 1 hour. Stir in whipped cream and serve with assorted fruit.

title: balloons
directions: Take refrigerator biscuits and roll each biscuit flat.
Place large marshmallow in center of each.
Fold around marshmallows and roll in melted butter and cinnamon sugar.
Place in greased muffin pan and put in a 350° oven until biscuits have expanded.

title: yakitori(microwave)
directions: Cut boned chicken into 1-inch lengths.
Slice green onions into 1-inch lengths.
Alternate chicken and green onions onto bamboo skewers.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken/onion skewers.
Marinate for 30 to 45 minutes.
Arrange 8 to 10 skewers on round glass plate or shallow baking dish for 3 to 4 minutes on High.
Microwave remaining skewers as needed.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make graham cracker crust to cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Open can of pineapple and save juice to soak bananas in. Slice bananas in juice.
Make filling by combining butter, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Whip until fluffy and spread over crust. Place sliced bananas over filling, making only 1 layer.
Slice pineapple over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Garnish with cherries.
Sprinkle with nuts. Chill 12 to 24 hours.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream
together
the oleo, sugar and vanilla.
Continue to cream
as
you add flour and nuts; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes in 2 (9-inch) pie plates.
Cool, then add the
mixed cream cheese and Cool Whip; spread over crust.
Top with fruit. Cover this with glaze.

title: calico bean bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for the beans.
Then add the beans and mix well and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
A slow cooker works very well.
Cook several hours (4 hours).

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix everything together, except Cheddar cheese.
Put into 2 quart casserole dish.
Spread cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes. Serve over rice (optional).

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter together until smooth (don't boil).
Add vanilla; remove from heat.
Add confectioners sugar. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.

title: stuffed green bell peppers
directions: Cut off tops of peppers; remove seeds.
Combine ground beef, egg, onion, oats, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon into peppers, pressing gently. Arrange in a 3-quart microwave-safe baking dish.
Spoon remaining spaghetti sauce over peppers.
Microwave covered on High for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes before serving.

title: vera's dip
directions: Beat all ingredients with electric mixer until well blended. Chill.
Serve with chips and/or vegetables.

title: caramel filled chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup, level off. In small bowl, combine flour, cocoa and baking soda, blend well. In a large bowl, beat 1 c. sugar, brown sugar and margarine until light and fluffy. Add vanilla and eggs, beat well. Add flour mixture, beat well, stir in 1/2 c. of the pecans. For each cookie, with floured hands, shape about 1 Tbsp. dough around each caramel candy, covering completely. In small bowl, combine remaining 1/2 c. pecans and 1 Tbsp. sugar. Press one side of each ball into pecan mixture. Place, nut side up, 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes or until set and slightly cracked. Cool 2 minutes. Remove from cookie sheets, cool completely on wire rack.

title: peanut butter and jelly cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and brown sugar.
Beat egg until fluffy.
Add to butter mix.
Sift dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Roll into 1 inch balls.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Indent centers of balls with thumbs.
Fill with jelly.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.

title: crazy or wacky cake
directions: Mix everything together, then add cooking oil.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: butter cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until smooth and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour a little at a time (fold in). Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Cut tomatoes, onions and peppers into large pieces.
Mix all ingredients and simmer 2 hours. (Cook down thick).
Put in jars and seal.
Delicious with pintos or any dried beans.

title: broccoli chicken hot dish
directions: Grease pan and place ingredients in pan in the above order. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Add 1 can onion rings and bake another 10 minutes.

title: chocolate haystacks
directions: In saucepan, bring first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop quickly from teaspoon on wax paper; cool.
Makes 48.

title: tina's applesauce cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift all dry ingredients into another bowl.
Add 1/2 of applesauce to creamy mixture and stir.
Add 1/2 dry ingredients until all mixed together.
Add raisins.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Wrap each apple piece with a piece of crescent roll.
Place in baking dish.
Bring orange juice, sugar, margarine and cinnamon to a boil; pour over the apples.
Bake at 325° until brown, approximately 35 minutes.
Spoon juice over apples occasionally while baking.

title: hot pickles
directions: Drain pickles and rinse thoroughly.
Layer pickles, sugar and Tabasco in gallon jar.
Keep turning jar every few hours until sugar is dissolved and thoroughly mixed.
Should be put in smaller containers.
Makes a different and delicious gift.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook on electric at medium-high (gas at high), until popping, stirring constantly.
Cook until starts smoking and turning a dark amber color around edge of skillet.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Before beginning, lay newspapers out with foil on top, butter foil.
Pour peanut brittle on foil to cool.
Use a fairly deep iron skillet to make candy.
Also, cut recipe in half until you learn to make the candy.
Cook about 25 minutes.

title: cranberry apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, spices, lemon rind, and cornstarch. Add cranberries, apples and lemon juice; toss until well coated. Crumble cookies in bottom of pie shell. Add cranberry mixture. Sprinkle with topping.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: In large skillet, saute onion, green onions, garlic and celery in butter until tender.
Add flour, cook and stir until lightly browned.
Add water, tomato puree, bay leaves, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally for 25 minutes or until sauce is almost of desired consistency.
Add shrimps and continue cooking 15 minutes.
Serve with parsleyed rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: low-fat corn pudding
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in bowl first, then add egg substitute, the corn and milk.
Bake in a 350° oven approximately 1 hour.

title: tomato soup(for canning)
directions: Cook tomatoes, celery,	cloves, onions, salt and pepper until vegetables are tender.
Run
through
sieve and let cool completely.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir together margarine, sugar and milk in a heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat or until it reaches 234°, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cut shrimp in small pieces. Combine all ingredients. Chill and serve with crackers or chips.

title: wedding fruit dip
directions: Mix together. Refrigerate before serving.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix ingredients; stir well.
Bake in a 275° oven for 2 hours or until done.

title: pick me up peach
directions: Blend all in blender on high, until ice is reduced to small pieces.
Serve immediately in chilled glasses.

title: muriel's texas hash
directions: Saute onion and green pepper slowly in oil. Add ground beef and cook until mixture is crumbly.
Pour off drippings.
Add tomatoes, rice and seasonings.
Mix thoroughly.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover and continue cooking in a 350° oven about 45 minutes or until done. Serves 4 to 6.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Cook beef until crumbly in butter.
Add garlic, salt, sugar, pepper and tomato sauce.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes. Cook noodles according to directions; drain.
Chop onion; mix with cream cheese and sour cream after meat sauce and noodles have cooled.

title: chocolate supreme dessert
directions: Mix together.
Pack crust into a 9 x 13-inch dish or a 2-quart casserole.
Bake for 20 minutes at 300°.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Combine in saucepan, sugar, syrup and water.
Start cooking slow and increase heat as mixture starts to cook.
Cook until hard boil on candy thermometer.
When temperature gets almost to hard boil, beat in large mixing bowl the egg whites until stiff.
Slowly drizzle the candy mixture into the egg whites with the mixer beating and the bowl rotating.
As you beat, you can pour a little heavier stream, but be careful not to cook the egg whites.
The mixture will get real smooth and shiny.
Beat until it gets a slightly cloudy look and then either beat slowly with mixer or by hand until you get a dough-like texture on a large spoon.
Spoon out dough into 4 to 5 rolls.
Then with flour on your hands, pat down and knead like dough if necessary.
Roll with well floured rolling pin and spread softened peanut butter on dough.
Roll like jelly roll and set aside to get a little firmer before cutting on an angle.

title: taco pie
directions: Combine, mix ingredients together.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: dog biscuits for your pet
directions: Add a little water if needed while mixing.
Batter will be firm.
Roll out on pastry board approximately 1/2 inch thick and cut as desired.
I cut like bars.
Our dogs are crazy about them.

title: divinity
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook to a hard crack.
Spread on wax paper and cut into pieces.

title: maurine way's brisket deluxe
directions: Put brisket in slow cooker or heavy dutch oven to cook over night. Sprinkle with onion salt, celery salt, garlic salt and worcestershire sauce to taste. Pour liquid smoke over top of meat.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: In microwave, in covered casserole dish, melt cheese and margarine.
Add powdered sugar, cocoa and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Spread in a large pan or Pyrex dish that has been greased with margarine.
Chill.

title: michelle's chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with crushed potato chips.
Slip back in oven for 10 or 15 minutes.
Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Cut one bread loaf into approximately 15 slices and put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sides of loaf must be touching, but not touching sides of pan.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; do not drain grease off. Add the cream of mushroom soup and mix well. Put in an ungreased 9 x 13, top with cheese and Tater Tots. Bake until heated through and Tater Tots are done.

title: too easy peach cobbler
directions: Place fruit in buttered 8 x 8 inch dish.
Cut crust from bread and cut each piece into 5 slices.
Place evenly over the fruit.
In a bowl mix sugar, flour, egg and melted butter.
Pour over fruit and bread slices.
Bake 350° for 35 minutes.

title: russian salad
directions: Mix 1 cup hot water with gelatin and pineapple and let cool. Add whipping cream, cream cheese and mayonnaise to gelatin.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for about 30 minutes until it begins to gel.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli and place all ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese, into large Teflon cake pan or Pyrex (13 x 9 x 2-inch) greased casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: coffee punch
directions: Mix coffee and water together, add sugar, ice cream mix together.
Add 2 tsp. sherry to 1 qt. coffee.
Add 4 dashes nutmeg. 1 qt. will serve 10 cups. 4 qt. will serve 32 cups.

title: peppermint crunch
directions: Stir together.
Spread thinly onto wax papered cookie sheet. Put in freezer for 5 minutes.
Hand break into pieces.
Store in covered container.

title: marshmallow torte
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk over slow fire.
Cool.
Drain juice of pineapple and combine with marshmallow mixture.
Whip the cream and add to the rest.
Put half of graham crackers in pan; sprinkle remainder on top.
Put in refrigerator to set.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix ground meat, rice, 1/2 cup water, onion, salt, celery salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Shape mixture by rounded tablespoonfuls into 12 balls.
Cook meatballs in a 10-inch skillet until brown on all sides; drain.
Then mix the remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat balls.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Melt oleo.
Combine oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and bananas.
Sift flour and add with dry ingredients.
Add nutmeats. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: white chile
directions: Combine beans, broth, garlic and half the onions in a large pot, bring to boil.
Reduce heat to simmer until beans are soft (2 hours), adding more broth or water as needed.
In a skillet, saute remaining onions in oil until tender.
Add chilies and seasonings, mix thoroughly, add to bean mixture; simmer one hour.
Serve topped with grated Monterey Jack cheese, salsa and sour cream.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sycamore hills chicken and rice
directions: Combine everything but bacon.
Spoon in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay bacon on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Triple recipe for 12 people.
You can make ahead of time.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook in iron skillet.
Stir until all water has boiled out. Put can of tomato soup in hamburger (dash of tomato catsup is good).
Cook a few minutes.
Put mixture into unbaked pie shell. Place other pie shell on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: jail house rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Mix remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well and put in a greased bowl in refrigerator.
Cover with a damp cloth.
Take out what is needed. Let rise and bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remainder of dough will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: french toast strata
directions: Cut bread into cubes (about 12 cups).
Grease a 3-quart rectangular baking dish.
Place half of bread cubes in dish.
Top with cream cheese cubes and remaining bread cubes.
Combine eggs, milk, melted butter and syrup in a mixing bowl or blender.
Beat or process until well combined.
Pour egg mixture over bread and cheese cubes.
Slightly press down to moisten.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 24 hours.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until center appears set and edges are golden.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serve with syrup. Serves 6 to 8.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Fry ground beef and chopped onions until done.
Drain.
Add black olives.
Warm flour tortillas and dip in enchilada sauce. Fill with meat and cheese.
Roll and place in pan.
Line bottom of pan with enchilada sauce.
When all are rolled up, top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: goop
directions: Add food coloring to water and combine with cornstarch in a bowl, then have fun by squeezing, pulling and letting the Goop drip through your fingers.
Store in a covered container.
If it dries out over time, a little water will revive it.

title: foil catfish
directions: Place each fillet on a piece of aluminum foil.
Put two pats of butter on each fillet, then slice garlic over it to taste. Wrap the foil and place on coals for 5 to 10 minutes.
For easier cleanup, prepare vegetables and potatoes in separate foil packs. (Works with almost any fish.
Spaghetti sauce may be substituted for butter and garlic.
For milder flavor, substitute onion for the garlic.)

title: easy raisin-nut cake
directions: Add raisins to cold water.
Boil and cook until soft.
Add baking soda and set aside to cool.
Mix remaining ingredients together; add raisins and water.
Grease and flour pan (angel food pan or Bundt pan).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Leave plain or top with confectioners sugar.

title: barbara's broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli in salt water 8 minutes until tender.
Drain. Blend soup and flour.
Add sour cream, onion, salt and pepper. Top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° uncovered 30 to 35 minutes.

title: john's peanut balls
directions: Mix and roll the peanut butter, vanilla, margarine and powdered sugar into balls.
Then melt the paraffin and chocolate chips.
Dip balls in hot chocolate mixture.
Let cool on wax paper.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiff; fold in last.
Put in unbaked pie crusts.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: molly richter's puppy chow
directions: Melt together oleo, chips and peanut butter.
Pour over entire 12 ounces cereal.
Stir to coat cereal.
Place powdered sugar in paper sack.
Pour coated cereal into sack.
Close and shake until coated.

title: shake-n-bake mix
directions: Mix thoroughly. Place in plastic bag. Use with chicken or pork.

title: *salad dressing for fruit
directions: Beat eggs.
Cook everything together, except the butter and cream, over medium heat until it thickens.
Remove from heat; add butter and cream.
After it cools, mix over a bowl of fresh fruit or canned fruit.

title: chipped beef on toast
directions: One pound hamburger, crumbled, browned and drained can be used.
Soak chipped beef (broken) in hot water while making gravy.

title: tomato quiche
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs.
Spray pie plate with Pam.
Slice and place tomatoes in pie plate.
Layer separated onion slices over tomatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle grated cheese over vegetables.
Pour batter over layered ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes in preheated 375° oven.
Serve warm.

title: pumpkin spice cake
directions: Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350°. When cool, cover with Cool Whip.

title: creamy vegetables in pastry shells
directions: Prepare pastry shells according to package directions.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done; save broth.
Debone chicken; cover long baking dish with chicken.
Heat soup and milk together. Pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing with chicken broth and 1 tablespoon of butter until moist; spread over mixture.
Bake at 350° until stuffing is done.

title: pull apart cheese bread
directions: Cut bread into crisscross pattern almost through to bottom. Stuff strips of cheese into each slit.
Mix onion, mustard, Lawry's, lemon juice and poppy seed into melted butter. Drizzle butter over bread. Wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until cheese melts.
To serve, allow guests to pull apart pieces.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into a jar and shake well.
A blender also works great.
Refrigerate.

title: crispy nests
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and butter; mix until well blended.
Add noodles and 1 cup holidays plain M&M's; mix well.
Drop by 1/3 cupfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Shape with greased fingers to form nests.
Let stand until firm.
Dust bottom of nests lightly with confectioners sugar, if desired.
Fill with holidays peanut M&M's before serving.
Makes 10 to 12 nests.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: larry's finger licking chicken wings
directions: Rinse wings and place in 1 or 2 large Ziploc bags.
Pour red hot sauce evenly into bags.
Shake to coat.

title: salmon noodle ring
directions: Combine butter, flour and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
Add salmon.
Season to taste.
Fill well-oiled ring mold with alternate layers of creamed salmon and noodles.
Sprinkle each layer with crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Unmold.
Fill center with buttered canned peas and carrots.
Garnish with slices of hard-cooked eggs.
Yields 8 servings.

title: sausage and garlic mashed potatoes
directions: In a small saucepan simmer garlic in oil until golden.
Stir in sage and remove pan from heat.
Let stand 15 minutes and strain out solids.
Fry sage leaves in 1/8 cup olive oil for 3 seconds. Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Peel potatoes and quarter.
Cover with 1 inch cold salted water.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: pasta and salmon casserole
directions: Cook pasta per directions; combine with fish, mayonnaise, vegetables and salt.
Blend milk and soup; heat.
Add cheese to soup and milk mixture; stir until cheese melts.
Combine pasta and cheese/soup mixtures.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.

title: zucchini and cheddar bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease and flour round pan, 9 x 11 x 2-inch.
Cook and stir onion in margarine until tender; cool slightly.
Mix onion mixture, Bisquick, parsley, basil, thyme, milk and eggs.
Beat vigorously one minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: tourtiere(pork or beef pie)
directions: In saucepan combine all ingredients (except pastry).
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes.
Uncover and cook 10 minutes more. Preheat oven to 425°.
Line pie pan with pastry.
Pour in mixture and cover with remaining pastry.
Press edges together.
Prick top; bake pie 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: soft 100% whole wheat bread
directions: Combine yeast and 1/2 cup warm water and let stand for 10 minutes.
Combine and mix all ingredients except flour.
Add flour, one cup at a time and mix well with mixer until stiff.
Add rest of flour, 1 cup at a time and knead until it does not stick to hands. Let rise and work down every 20 minutes for 3 hours.
Put in greased bread pans and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: no peek casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and place in baking dish.
Top with corn flakes and melted butter.
Bake 50 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into baking dish; top with topping.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine and cream cheese.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, mixing well after each ingredient is added.
Add flour gradually, mixing after each addition.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube or large Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: mostaccioli and meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil, mostaccioli and sauce. Shape meat balls.
Heat oil and brown meat balls.
Add sauce and simmer until done.
Cook mostaccioli to package directions and drain.
Serve spaghetti sauce and meat balls over mostaccioli. Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar, vanilla and salt. Add nuts; stir in.
Put on greased foil.
Bake at 300° until golden brown.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package.
Drain well.
Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs in a 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fake sausages
directions: Note:
Ocara can be gotten free at tofu factories.
Check your yellow pages for locations.

title: butter pecan torte
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour equal amounts of batter into three 8-inch cake pans which have been lined with 2 layers of waxed paper.
Bake in a moderate 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: ranch chicken
directions: Mix chicken with onions, soups, tomatoes and seasonings.
In a baking dish, layer tortillas with chicken mixture.
Top with lots of grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes until cheese is melted and brown.

title: peas and asparagus casserole
directions: Mix the above ingredients and bake at 300° for approximately 20 minutes, then top with about 1/2 cup grated cheese and Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake about 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Serves 8 or more.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; save broth.
Put cut up chicken into a casserole dish.
Mix in sour cream and soup.
Mix saved chicken broth in dressing mix to moisten.
Put dressing mix on top of chicken mixture.
Bake in a 375° oven until brown and bubbly.

title: granny zander's walnut kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in sugar very slowly.
Fold in black walnuts with a spoon.
Put on slightly greased sheets and bake at 250° for 40 minutes.

title: chili sauce
directions: Mix in order given. Boil 2 hours.
Bottle while hot.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar.
Beat eggs; add oil and pumpkin.
Mix altogether and add walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.
Grease and flour 11 x 17-inch pan with sides.

title: hot and handy spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving-size portions.
Put in a shallow baking pan in single layer.
Bake in a very hot oven (450°) for 30 minutes, turning once.
Drain off fat.
Saute onion and garlic in butter in a saucepan until tender, 3 minutes.
Add chili sauce, lemon juice, sugar, horseradish and salt.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 15 minutes on low heat.
Brush ribs with sauce.
Grill over grayed coals or broil 6 to 7 inches from heat for 20 minutes.
Brush with sauce until ribs are nicely glazed.

title: pumpkin cheese dip
directions: Cut off pumpkin top; reserve top.
Scoop out innards and discard.
Layer cheese, croutons, cheese and croutons until pumpkin is full.
Pack down.
Pour margarine or butter over this.
Replace pumpkin top.
Bake at 250° on a cookie sheet for 2 hours or until mixture melts.
Serve in pumpkin with raw vegetables and crackers.

title: charlie's chops
directions: Sprinkle salt, pepper and garlic powder on chops and dredge in flour.
Brown in oil.
Add tomatoes (use juice of tomatoes and water to equal 1 cup of liquid), onion, and rice.
Simmer 1 hour, covered.
Serves 4.

title: green chili corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly oil 9-inch square baking pan. Using electric mixer, beat butter, cornmeal and sugar in bowl until blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: saucy dogs
directions: Slice hot dogs and Smokies crosswise to make 5 pieces from each (or use cocktail wieners).
Melt mustard and jelly together in saucepan.
Add meat and heat until hot.
Do not cover or sauce will be watery.

title: sausage-apple balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: orange carrots
directions: Slice carrots into rounds and cook until tender; drain.
Mix sugar and flour.
Add orange juice; cook until thickened.
Pour over carrot slices; add oleo.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: egg nog
directions: Mix all ingredients with a mixer for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and nutmeg to taste.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk until it thickens a little.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Mix well until it thickens.
Starting with crackers, make a layer in a 13 x 9-inch pan, then spread frosting on top.
Refrigerate.
Then cut into squares.

title: debbie's tacos
directions: Prepare Taco Shells.
Cook and stir hamburger in skillet until done.
Drain.
Stir in water, 1/2 cup onion, chili powder, salt, cumin and garlic.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, until thickened, about 10 minutes.
Spoon 1/4 cup mixture into each shell.
Top with lettuce, onion, cheese, tomato and sour cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Lay chicken in bottom of large casserole dish.
Stir condensed soup and sour cream together; cover chicken.
Spread crushed Ritz crackers on top.
Pour melted margarine over all.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: round steak hot dish
directions: Brown steak, onion and celery in small amount of fat.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Add rice, soups, mushrooms and water. Blend ingredients; bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mexican tossed salad
directions: Toss lettuce, tomatoes, onion, cheese and kidney beans together.
Crush corn chips before opening bag.
About 30 minutes before serving, pour chips over the other ingredients and add dressing over top.
Toss again.
Use very large bowl.
Best when eaten first day.

title: mexican stuffed shells
directions: Cook pasta shells according to package instructions.
Drain and set aside.
Combine picante sauce, tomato sauce and water.
Set aside.
Cook meat over medium heat until brown, stirring to crumble.
Drain.
Add 1/2 cup picante mixture, chiles, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onion.

title: no calorie salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pint jar; shake.
Cover tightly. Store in refrigerator.
Shake before using.

title: pork chops en casserole
directions: Place a layer of sweet potatoes, sliced crosswise, in a greased casserole.
Dust
with salt, pepper and a little brown sugar; continue
the
layers until the dish is about 2/3 full. Heat the
milk
and
pour
over potatoes, it should just cover them.
Place pork chops on top of potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for an
hour,
then remove cover and season with salt and pepper.
Leave the cover off and cook until the pork chops are tender and nicely browned on top.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Prepare the lime, orange and cherry jello in separate 8 x 8-inch pans,
using
cup
boiling
water and 1/2 cup cold water each.
Place
in refrigerator.

title: copper pennies
directions: Peel and slice carrots. Boil in saltwater until tender. When cool, alternate layers of carrots, green peppers and onion rings.

title: appetizer roll-ups
directions: In a bowl, combine the cream cheese, carrots, zucchini and dill. Spread about 2 tablespoons on each slice of ham and turkey. Roll up tightly. Wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate overnight. Slice into 1 1/2-inch pieces. Yield: 6 to 7 dozen.

title: beacon hill cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips over hot water.
Set aside.
Add a dash of salt to egg whites and beat.
Gradually add sugar beating until well blended.
Then beat until mixture will form stiff peaks. Beat in vinegar and vanilla.
Fold in Baker's cocoa, chopped nuts and melted chocolate.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream
shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg, molasses; then dry
ingredients,
which have been sifted together.
Add hot water last and beat until smooth.
Bake in greased shallow pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in flour mix and thoroughly coat.
Heat oil and butter in frypan.
When hot, add chicken and saute until brown on each side.
Remove chicken and place on heated plates.
Pour most of fat from pan, leaving brown bits.
Add wine and lemon juice and stir to incorporate drippings. Pour over chicken and serve immediately.
Serves 2.

title: easy chocolate bars
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together by hand; pat into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cheese and eggs.
Add sugar; blend until smooth.
Add pecans.
Pour over first layer.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: mocha fireside coffee
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well. Store in an airtight container. To serve, add 1 tablespoon mix to 3/4 cup boiling water. Yield: 6 cups mix.

title: broiled cheese appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on party rye bread.
Broil 4-inches from heat until hot and bubbly.
Serve hot! Yield:

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir eggs, corn syrup, sugar, chocolate chips, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans. Pour into pie shell. Bake in a 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies per package instructions.
Cool. Punch holes in brownies with a fork.
Pour coffee over brownies.
Set aside. Whip up Jell-O chocolate mousse per package directions.
Break up candy bars (in wrappers).
Break up half the brownies, place in bottom of glass trifle dish.
Cover with half the mousse.
Layer half candy (or brickles) then add half whipped topping.
Repeat layers.
Chill and enjoy.

title: exquisite pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in milk, eggs and vanilla.
Add raisins, coconut and nuts.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer until set.

title: ambrosia
directions: Peel oranges and divide into sections.
Place in a bowl and slice bananas into it.
Add sugar and mix lightly; chill.
When ready to serve, top with coconut.

title: grandma's noodles
directions: For each egg, beaten, add 1 tablespoon of water, a little salt and enough flour to roll the dough as thin as possible.
Let dry on the breadboard until the small noodles can be cut without sticking or cracking.
If wish to keep for a while, let noodles dry after cutting and put in freezer.
Otherwise, cook noodles in one or more pints of chicken or any other broth, or water, for 15 to 20 minutes.
