title: chicken breasts with artichoke cheese stuffing
directions: Pound chicken into 1/4-inch thickness.
Set aside.
Mix cheese, 1/4 cup mayo, onions, parsley flakes and mustard in a small bowl.
Cut artichoke hearts into bite-size pieces.
Stir into cheese mixture.
Spread about 1/4 cup cheese mixture down center of each piece of chicken.
Roll up and secure ends with wooden picks.
Mix flour, salt and pepper in shallow dish.
Set aside.
Mix egg and water in shallow dish.
Dip rolled chicken in egg mixture, then in bread crumbs, pressing to coat thoroughly. Cover and refrigerate about 1 hour.

title: glazed carrots
directions: In a saucepan, cook carrots with water. Add salt and pepper. Cook until barely tender; drain.
Melt butter, marmalade and jelly. Cook with carrots for a few minutes.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Beat the cheese into mayonnaise, then beat in the cream. Season to taste with salt, pepper and serve over your favorite salad.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Boil noodles until tender, but still firm.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients into 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with slices of American cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, until casserole is heated through.
Serve hot.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Bring beans and water to boil; soak overnight.
To cook, add cooked bacon (diced) to which the onion was cooked in grease before drained and cubed raw potatoes and carrots along with tomatoes. Add ham and honey.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until done. Mash with potato masher and stir in 2 cups milk.
Simmer for an additional 10 minutes.

title: mock swiss steak
directions: Mix together and pour over top of meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 15.

title: scallops with fresh tomato
directions: Cut scallops crosswise in half; set aside.
In frying pan, simmer margarine or butter, lemon juice, salt and pepper approximately 5 minutes.
Add scallops and green onion.
Cook until scallops are done.
Stir in tomato.
Cook until tomato is warm.
Sprinkle with dill.
Serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: french-canadian meatball ragout
directions: Thoroughly mix spices with meat. Form meat into balls 1 1/2 to 2-inches.
Roll each ball in flour, packing firmly.
Brown balls on all sides in Dutch oven. Cover with water.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Thicken gravy with flour, diluted with 1/2 cup water.
Serve over potatoes or egg noodles. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: crunch top potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Put butter in a jelly roll pan and put in oven to melt.
Add a single layer of potatoes, turning to coat with butter.
Mix remaining and sprinkle over the potatoes.
Bake 1/2 hour or until done.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water; set in pan of warm water until soft.
Mix into cranberry sauce.
Add other ingredients, except cream cheese.
Soften cream cheese.
Serve over salad as a dressing.
Serves 6.

title: mexican chicken and rice(25 minutes)
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add chicken, onion and green pepper.
Cook and stir until chicken is cooked through.
Add corn, broth and salsa (hot or medium).
Bring to a boil.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add all other ingredients except cabbage.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add cabbage; simmer until flavor is blended and cabbage is cooked.
The longer it simmers the better it tastes.
Can be frozen and then reheated (flavor improves).

title: low calorie dressing
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes.
Dissolve this mixture in hot water.
Add the sugar and salt.
Mix until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
When cool add the lemon juice, mustard and paprika.
Shake the mixture well and chill.
If it becomes solid in refrigerator, warm a little.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Melt and bring to a boil the water, cocoa and margarine.
Pour over the flour, sugar, soda and salt that have been mixed together. Beat well. Add the eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Mix and pour into a 13 x 15-inch jelly roll pan and bake for 20 to 22 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese and meatball soup
directions: Place vegetables, water, bouillon cubes and Tabasco sauce in crock-pot.
Mix meat, egg, salt and pepper, dash of Tabasco sauce and bread crumbs in bowl.
Form into small meatballs and drop into soup mixture.
Cook 4 to 6 hours on low.
(If cooked on range top, cook until all ingredients are done.)
Add Velveeta cheese and mix until it melts.
Serve immediately.
Freezes well.

title: radio cookies
directions: Bake for 10 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: thumbprints
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add flavoring, flour and nuts. Chill in freezer for 30 minutes.
Roll into small balls and put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Put thumbprint into ball.
Cook at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool.
Put icing in middle. Use any flavor icing.

title: diet punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.

title: pepper sirloin steak
directions: Lightly score edge of steak at 1 inch intervals.
Preheat grill or broiler.
Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until butter melts.
Reserve 1/4 of mixture.
Place steak on grill or broiler.
Brush mixture on steak.
Cook about 6 minutes on each side for a medium broil.
Place on platter, drizzling remaining mixture on steak.

title: favorite pumpkin pie(no bake)
directions: Combine pie filling mix, sugar, spice, milk and egg, adding the pumpkin last. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full bubbling boil.
Remove from heat. Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into shell and chill 4 hours. Garnish with whipped topping.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar. Add oil.
Mix dry ingredients together. Add to the mixture.
Add apples and nuts last.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 to 30 minutes.
Check with toothpick for doneness. May cook in Bundt pan, well-greased and floured.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into three 8-inch well-greased pans.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar
until light and fluffy.
Add salt, vanilla, flour and nuts.
Preheat oven to 325°.
With teaspoon remove small amount of dough.
With hands form a ball. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Remove and roll immediately in powdered sugar.
Makes 30 to 36 cookies.

title: susie's chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Cut up into chunks.
Cook broccoli according to directions on box.
In a 9 x 13 pan, spread stuffing on bottom.
Add broccoli.
Put chicken on top of that.
Mix soup and mayonnaise together.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ultimate roast beef sandwich
directions: Combine mayonnaise and horseradish.
Fill rolls with roast beef, lettuce, tomato, onion and mayonnaise mixture.
Serves 4.

title: pickled okra
directions: In pot, mix together and boil as brine:vinegar, water, dill seed, salt, and hot peppers.
Wash and prepare okra.
Pack okra and garlic tightly into hot, sterilized jars.
Pour brine over okra in jars.
Seal and process in boiling bath for 10 minutes.
Ripen several weeks before opening.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all together and top with paprika.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain. Add onion; saute. Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, cream of chicken soup, green onion dip and picante sauce.
Heat together.
Break tortillas in small pieces into microwave casserole dish.

Layer in dish half the tortillas, 1/2 of the mixture, 1/2 of the tortillas and balance of the mixture. Cook on High for 6 minutes. Top with Velveeta cheese slices. Cook on low 3 or 4 minutes until cheese melts. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: daffodil salad
directions: Combine jello, hot water, cold water, sugar and salt.
Let cool.
Add apples, bananas and pineapple to jello.
Let set.

title: eggless chocolate cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients in a large bowl, then add all wet ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Combine with all other ingredients and chill for 4 to 6 hours.

title: broccoli stuffed onions
directions: Peel and halve onions.
Parboil in water 10 to 12 minutes, drain.
Remove centers, leaving 3/4-inch edges.
Chop center portion to equal 1 cup.
Cook broccoli as to package directions, drain.
Combine chopped onions, broccoli, Parmesan cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Spoon into center of onion halves. Melt butter.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add milk and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and blend in cream cheese.
Spoon sauce over onion halves and bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: rum walnut cake
directions: Mix all cake ingredients (except walnuts).
Sprinkle walnuts in a 10-inch greased and floured tube cake pan.
Pour cake ingredients over walnuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Cool cake, then invert on serving platter.

title: banana crunch cake
directions: Mix bananas, eggs and sour cream until well blended.
Add cake mix; beat on high for 2 minutes.
Put half of batter in tube pan, add half of crunch mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with crunch mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: always ready fruit pie
directions: Peel and cut peaches into 1-inch cubes.
Combine peaches with blueberries, sugar, cornstarch, lemon juice and spices.
Stir to mix thoroughly.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with plastic wrap with 5-inches overhanging the edges.
Spoon fruit mixture into pie plate.
Freeze until firm.
Unmold filling and fold plastic over frozen filling; put in one-gallon freezer bag.
Freeze until ready to use.
To bake, prepare pastry crust, line pan.
Place frozen fruit filling in unbaked crust.
Cover with top crust, crimp and seal edges.
Cut steam slits in top.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes, then 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix well and form patties.
Dip in cornmeal or flour; fry until brown.

title: fabulous ham and cheese souffle
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Spread half of the bread cubes evenly in dish.
Add the ham and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and mustard and pour over all, then cover with remaining bread crumbs and refrigerate overnight.
Combine corn flakes and butter for a topping.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender.
In skillet, melt butter and add bell pepper and onion.
Drain squash.
Mix with skillet mixture.
Add eggs, soup and 1/2 crackers.
Put into ungreased casserole dish. Put remaining crackers on top.
Can add cheese before cooking. Cook at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: banana oatmeal breadel paso, texas
directions: Cream egg and butter, add bananas, dry ingredients and nuts. Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend eggs and sugar well.
Add pumpkin, oil and water; mix well. In a separate bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
Slowly blend in dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
A 1-pound coffee can may be used.
Fill it half full and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: bacon potato soup
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Add diced potatoes and onions to 2 tablespoons fat.
Cover with water and cook until done.
Add crumbled bacon, cubed eggs, milk and seasoning.

title: ugly salad
directions: Cook 1 box rotini noodles.
Add to mixture of ingredients. Slice 2 big cucumbers and 2 onions.
Stir well.
This is better if left set overnight.

title: cheese grits
directions: Combine grits, water and salt.
Cook until thick.
Add oleo, onion, cheese, Cheez Whiz, eggs, garlic powder and red pepper. Stir until well mixed.
Put in oiled casserole and bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.
This serves about 20 people and it freezes well.

title: orange chicken burgundy
directions: In a large frying pan or electric skillet, brown chicken in butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients, except Burgundy and orange slices.
Reduce heat, cover (can also be put in 375° oven) and simmer, stirring and basting occasionally until tender.
Add Burgundy and orange slices.
Continue simmering another 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: sweet biscuit crust
directions: Mix
flour,
baking powder, sugar and salt together in a mixing
bowl.
Cut	in
butter
or margarine to resemble coarse crumbs.
Combine milk and egg, add to dry ingredients, stirring with
a fork until it forms a soft dough.
Roll out to 1/4 inch thickness,	cut
out
biscuits
with
2-inch
cutter.
Good for cobblers, chicken pie, etc.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well; roll into small walnut size balls.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: easy donuts
directions: Melt Crisco for deep frying.
Cut biscuit centers out with a small medicine bottle.
Drop biscuits in hot Crisco.
Brown on one side, then the other.
Take out of Crisco.
Put in glaze.
Then take out of glaze and put on plate to cool.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kibbles and bits(for people)
directions: Melt together.
Add 1 large box Crispix cereal.
Stir to coat. Place in a large grocery bag.
Add 1 pound powdered sugar and shake well.

title: s'mores
directions: For each serving, you need 1 square graham cracker, 1 square of a chocolate bar and 1 marshmallow. Place on a grill or in electric skillet. Cover and heat until the chocolate has melted. This can be done in a microwave.

title: grape leaf pickles
directions: Put cucumbers in a jar in layers with grape leaves and green grapes.
For a half-gallon jar, use 3 tablespoons of salt.
Fill jar with cold water and let stand 3 days.
Pour off liquid and discard.
Add 2 tablespoons of salt to each jar and fill again with cold water.

title: avanti's bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water (115°).
Mix in remaining ingredients. Knead.
Place in greased bowl.
Turn over.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Punch down.
Let rise again.
Grease 5 bread pans. Divide dough into 5 equal parts.
Place in bread pans and cover. Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pork sausage ring
directions: Beat eggs slightly and add milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well as a meat loaf. Pat firmly into a greased 6-cup ring mold and chill overnight.

title: spaghetti sauce for 12
directions: Brown garlic and onion in 1 cup olive oil; add tomatoes, water and paste.
Stir; add seasonings and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Stir often; add mushrooms and raw ground beef.
Simmer 1/2 hour; taste for seasonings.
Simmer for 3 hours or more.

title: naomi's pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Set aside.
Cream butter; gradually add sugars.
Beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Alternate flour mixture with pumpkin, mixing well.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients; put in refrigerator for at least 15 minutes. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to this.
Add nuts.
Pour into two greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, or until done.

title: apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a rectangular pan, 13 x 9-inches. Mix sugar, oil and eggs until blended. Beat 1 minute. Stir in remaining ingredients except apples; beat 1 minute. Stir in apples. Pour into pan. Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean or 35 to 45 minutes.

title: bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar and oil.
Add salt.
Beat flour into liquid mixture real well; dump on floured surface. Knead in 1/2 to 3/4 cup flour.
Knead almost 10 minutes.
Grease bowl that dough was in; return dough to bowl.
Let rise until double, approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down; shape into balls and place into greased loaf pan.
Let rise again approximately 1 1/2 hours or until double.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until very brown on top.
Remove from oven and rub butter on top.
Will make approximately 2 dozen rolls or 1 loaf of bread.

title: roasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Mix and bake on cookie sheet at 250° until dry and crisp. Stir often (1 1/2 to 2 hours).

title: crunch romaine toss
directions: Brown walnuts and noodles in 325 degrees for 10 minutes for crunchy.
Cool on paper towels.
Combine noodles and walnuts with broccoli, romaine and onions.
Pour Sweet & Sour Dressing over and toss to coat well.
Serves 10-12.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine until tender.
Add rest of ingredients.
Heat until thoroughly mixed.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: meat loaf
directions: Put foil in bottom of pan, leaving enough on edges to "tent" over top.
Mix all ingredients together and shape into loaf in center of pan.
Tent the pan and bake for 45 minutes at 350° (or until done through and brown).

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Combine dry ingredients in separate bowl.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Combine cream, margarine and sugar.
Add egg and beat well. Add dry ingredients and almond flavor.
Fill cookie press with dough and drop onto cookie sheet.
Brush with beaten egg white and sprinkle on pecans.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine shortening, cocoa and salt. Add milk and vanilla. Stir sugar in 3 parts, mixing until smooth and creamy. Add more sugar to thicken or milk to thin.

title: old-fashioned doughnuts(club member: lee higginbotham)
directions: Mix all ingredients together well until batter is thick and ready to roll on floured board. Cut in shapes and sizes you desire. Cook in a pot on top of stove in hot cooking oil. May be rolled in powdered sugar after you have cooked them or you can also dip in chocolate syrup.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix eggs, corn syrup, sugar, peanut butter, vanilla and butter.
Mix together and put in unbaked pie shell and cook at 300° until done.

title: barbecued pork
directions: Remove fat, combine all ingredients . Put pork in and soak 1 hour at room temperature or overnight.
Drain pork.
Keep liquid. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Baste with liquid marinade.

title: easter or santa claus cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients. Roll out. Cut with cookie cutter which has been dipped into flour.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake cookies on ungreased cookie sheet on top rack of oven for 6 to 7 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: round steak delight
directions: Brown cubed steak in a deep pan.
Season and add some Worcestershire sauce while browning.
Do not drain.
Add soup to meat and meat juices.
Add more Worcestershire to your own liking. Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk; boil for 1 minute at rolling boil.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter.
When thoroughly blended, stir in oats.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Cool and store.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Cut pocket in each chop and set aside.
In a saucepan, mix undrained pineapple, water, celery, margarine, sugar, soy sauce, vinegar and garlic powder.
Heat to boiling.
Add stuffing and mix lightly.
Spoon stuffing mixture into pork chop pockets.
Place chops, stuffing-side up, in baking dish and cover.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 25 minutes more or until done.

title: russian tea
directions: Shake ingredients in a large jar.

title: best caramel cake
directions: Bake as directed on the box in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool slightly and poke holes in the top of the cake with a pencil or wooden spoon.
Mix caramel sauce and condensed milk
and dribble over cake.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed candy bars.
Refrigerate.

title: small christmas fruitcake cupcakes
directions: Mix together and place in small muffin tins that have been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: spinach dip
directions: Dip out insides of bread. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Put spinach mixture inside bread.
Use bread for dipping.

title: brendan's fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 9-inch square pan with foil, grease foil.
Melt chocolate and butter in double boiler.
Cool 15 minutes.
Stir eggs, sugar, vanilla and flour into chocolate mix; pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: oven barbecued ribs
directions: Arrange ribs with meaty side up, in large pan.
Place in oven at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix juice from beets, vinegar and water, then mix sugar and flour together.
Add to juice mixture.
Cook until thick.
Add butter, salt and beets.
Cook 5 minutes.

title: egg casserole
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients in order given. Beat or mix the next 3 ingredients and pour over layered mixture. Add sausage to top and bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: crawfish etoufe
directions: Before going to work, combine all ingredients in crock-pot. Serve over rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Stir in cheese to melt.

title: bacon dip n' dunk
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain well.
Reserve 1 tablespoon of drippings.
Crumble bacon.
Combine sour cream and mayo. Gradually stir in drippings. Add onion, parsley, salt and bacon. Mix well. Cover and chill a couple of hours before serving.

title: broccoli and chicken soup
directions: Cook broccoli until tender
in 3/4 cup water about 5 or 8 minutes.
Stir in
soup
and
milk.
Cook
over medium heat, stirring constantly until
thoroughly
heated.
Stir in pepper and salt and serve.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Stir in Bisquick and potatoes.
Cover and chill one hour.
Shape into balls and put 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Makes a large batch.

title: apple taffy cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add yolks and flour.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
While warm, insert round toothpicks and cool.
Melt caramels with milk.
Dip cookie into caramel mix and roll very carefully into finely chopped nuts just around sides so it looks like a taffy apple.
Keep caramel mix warm or it will harden.

title: apple cream coffee cake
directions: In a bowl, mix walnuts, cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar.
Set aside. In a large bowl with mixer at high speed, beat margarine until creamy, gradually adding 1 cup sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla until blended.
Sift flour.
Add baking powder, baking soda and salt alternately with sour cream.
Spread 1/2 of the batter in Bundt pan.
Top with thin apple slices and half cinnamon mixture.
Top with remaining batter and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: marissa's "tater tot" casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onions.
Drain fat.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Place meat in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Layer vegetables, cream of mushroom soup and cheese.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until Tater Tots are crispy golden brown. Can be made ahead and frozen before or after baking.

title: blueberry snack cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar. Cut in butter until crumbly. Set aside 3/4 cup for topping. Add baking powder, milk and egg yolks to remaining mixture; mix well. Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; fold into batter. Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with blueberries and reserved crumb mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: *For thicker sauce, add additional teaspoon of cornstarch.

title: baked redfish with oysters
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a baking dish.
Place fillets in dish so they don't touch.
Spread onion, tomatoes, garlic and herbs over fillets. Add vermouth.
Add oysters and liquor.
Put dish in oven 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove fish and place on platter; cover.
Reduce sauce over high heat for 2 minutes. Pour sauce over fish. Garnish with fresh parsley and serve.

title: sweet and sour cabbage soup(vegetarian recipe; serves 6 to 8)
directions: Place barley, carrot, celery, onion, margarine and bay leaves in a large soup pot and cover with the vegetable stock or water. Bring to a boil, then add all the remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer over very low heat for 30 to 35 minutes, or until the vegetables and barley are tender, but not overcooked.
Allow the soup to stand for an hour before serving, then heat through.
This is also a good soup to make a day ahead.

title: lazy day peach pie
directions: Melt the stick of butter in a deep pie pan.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together and pour into butter. Add the peaches in center of mixture. Bake slowly at 350° until brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix gelatin with 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add 3/4 cup cold water.
Chill until thick.
Add fruit.
Chill until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients.
Add next 2 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in greased muffin tins.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes or until tested done when inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: blueberry bundt cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a Bundt cake pan.
Drain and rinse blueberries; set aside.
Mix brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
In a large bowl, blend eggs, sour cream and water.
Blend in muffin mix with a fork.
Spread 1/3 of batter in pan; top with half the sugar mixture and half the blueberries.
Repeat, ending with muffin batter.
Bake for 50 minutes.
Mix confectioners sugar and milk until smooth.
Drizzle on warm cake.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Put marshmallows on bottom of lightly greased pan (do not overlap).
Mix cake according to box directions; pour over marshmallows.
Mix strawberries and Jell-O together.
Spoon mixture over the cake
batter and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Marshmallows will come to the top and strawberries will go to the bottom.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: eclair cake
directions: Layer a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with whole graham crackers.
Mix the pudding with the milk; fold in the Cool Whip.
Spread half of mixture on top of graham crackers.
Make another layer of graham crackers.
Spread on remaining pudding mixture.
Top with another layer of whole graham crackers.
Frost with 1 can of chocolate frosting.
Chill overnight.

title: sugar cookies(a favorite home economics foods demonstration)
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
In another bowl, beat shortening, sugar and egg yolk until fluffy.
Alternately add flour and then buttermilk to shortening mixture.
Then stir in vanilla.
In another bowl, beat egg white until stiff.
Fold egg white into creamed mixture.
To make cookies, drop by tablespoons onto a greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: syrup cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and syrup; stir in flour.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Use any kind of spices you like.
Cook 45 minutes or until done.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Blend peppers and mix in sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a brisk boil for 3 minutes.
Add pectin and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and set aside for 5 minutes.
Pour into hot sterile jars.

title: family favorite cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream margarine and sweetener.
Sift baking powder, salt and flour, then add alternately with skim milk to creamed mixture.
Add almond extract and beat stiff and fold in whites.
Pour into two well-greased 9-inch layer pans.
Bake about 30 minutes.
Cool a few minutes, then remove cake from pans and cool further on wire rack.

title: mexican wedding balls
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar together.
Stir in flour, salt and nuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: punch recipe
directions: Add water to the lemonade as directed on the cans.
Mix with the other juices and add ice.

title: stuffed flank steak
directions: Split a flank steak like a pita pocket. Make stuffing with dried bread, onions, sage, celery, chicken broth. Stuff into pocket. Roll steak up and tie or skewer to keep stuffing in. Roast in oven or 350° like a pot roast until done.

title: sailboat
directions: Fill the peach half with cranberry sauce or cottage cheese. poke a toothpick through the carrot curl or cheese to make a sail and then stick it in the peach.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except topping, and place in a 2-quart uncovered casserole dish.

title: spring tonic salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Cool.
When slightly set; add other ingredients.
Add radishes for color (optional).
Serve 10 to 12.

title: carrots casserole
directions: Place cooked carrots in casserole.
Melt 1/2 stick butter, cheese and 1 tablespoon water; pour over cooked carrots.
Crumble 15 crackers and melt other 1/2 stick butter; mix together.
Put cracker mixture on top of carrot mixture and bake at 350°
until it bubbles, about 25 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix with spoon.
Use two mini muffin pans.
Spray with Pam. Put a small pat of butter into each cup, then put 1/2 teaspoon batter over butter.
Cook at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: waffle syrup pecan pie
directions: Pour into pastry lined pan.
Bake at 375° until set and pastry is nicely browned or about 40 to 50 minutes.

title: slow cooker stew
directions: Brown beef in skillet on top of stove.
Transfer to slow cooker.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring to blend.
Cover and slow cook.
Set temperature depending on how long you wish the stew to cook.
If you want stew ready in 9 to 10 hours, set on low temperature; 8 hours, set on medium; 5 hours, set on high.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Work in fat with tips of fingers; then add milk.
Roll very thin.
Prick well and bake for 15 minutes in moderately hot oven.
When cold, break into pieces. May be served in place of crackers; also good when hot served with butter.

title: stir-fry veggies
directions: Place veggies in Ziploc bag with dressing.
Marinate 24 hours, shaking occasionally.
Drain liquid.
Add mushrooms. Stir-fry until veggies are tender-crisp.

title: fettuccine alfredo with soy milk
directions: Saute peppers in oil; add garlic when peppers are almost done. Do not burn.
Melt butter, medium-low.
Add flour to form paste. Add broth and combine thoroughly.
Add soy milk, cheese and pepper. Cook until thickened; stir constantly.

title: cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugars and eggs until smooth.
Add all other ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1/2 cup butter.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch dish.
Add 1/2 package of hash browns.
In a separate bowl, mix soup, sour cream, milk and green onions.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over hash browns.
Pour remainder of mixture on top.
Add remainder of hash browns.
Pour remainder of mixture on top. Sprinkle remainder of cheese on top.
Cover with crushed corn flakes.
Pour 2 tablespoons of melted margarine over mixture.; Bake for 45 minutes or until done.

title: turtle cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients, except pecan halves; blend thoroughly by hand to form firm dough.
Place cluster of 3 pecan halves on greased cookie sheet.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place in center of pecans.
Flatten ball slightly to press into pecans.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 4 to 4 1/2 dozen.

title: party apple creme
directions: Heat apple juice to boiling.
Combine with gelatin in a 1 1/2-quart bowl and stir to dissolve gelatin.
Blend in ice cream. Fold in 1 1/2 cups applesauce.
Chill until mixture is thickened. Spoon into bowl and garnish with remaining applesauce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: deviled crab
directions: Saute onions and peppers in butter until soft. Add milk and flour gradually and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add to crab meat with grated eggs, salt, pepper, mustard, lemon juice and Worcestershire. Put in crab shells. Top with bread crumbs. Dot with butter. Sprinkle paprika on top. Brown under broiler. Can be frozen.

title: baked cubed steak
directions: Roll steak in flour and brown in oil; place steak in casserole dish.
(Salt and pepper both sides of steak during browning.)
Cut up 1 large onion all over steak.
Put water with oil from frying pan and completely cover steak.
Cover dish and bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed, mustard and onion with mixer. Add oil until mixture is thick.
Refrigerate.
Makes 1 quart.

title: noodles siciliano
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
In a medium skillet, heat oil and cook mushrooms until tender.
Stir in anchovies, olives and parsley.
Toss mixture with hot noodles. Makes about 2 main dish or 4 side dish servings.

title: jello-fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and cherries; save juices.
Replace juices to cold water of jello; add water if necessary.
Refrigerate.
When jello is half hardened, whip the whipping cream until stiff peaks. Add sour cream and softened cream cheese.
Mix completely; refrigerate.
Halve cherries.
When jello is 2/3 hardened, add all ingredients.
Mix and chill.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Mix ingredients and let set overnight.
Strain.
Heat and serve piping hot.

title: uitsmijter(for one person)
directions: Butter the bread and cover with ham or roast beef, a matter of taste.
Fry eggs and put them on top of the meat.
Add the dill pickle.

title: marinated spam vegetable salad
directions: In a skillet, saute Spam until brown over medium heat. Combine other ingredients in bowl.
Add the Spam and set aside.

title: egg noodles
directions: Beat eggs and milk.
Add salt and pepper.
Add flour, 1/2 cup at a time, until dough pulls away from sides of bowl and forms a ball.
Knead.
Sprinkle surface with flour and roll dough to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into thin strips.
Boil in meat broth about 10 minutes or until done.
May dry and freeze for later use.

title: creamy chicken casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, prepare sauce.
In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook mushrooms and onion until tender in butter.
Do not brown. Stir in remaining ingredients except macaroni and bread crumbs. Heat through.

title: barbecue style potatoes
directions: Cut the potatoes into 4 wedges. Cut crosswise at 1/4-inch intervals to within 1/4-inch from bottom of potatoes. Place in ice water 1 hour. Dry potatoes. Mix the margarine, catsup, mustard, paprika and salt. Place potatoes on jelly roll pan. Brush with 1/2 of the catsup mixture. Bake in 425° oven, brushing occasionally with remaining mixture, 35 minutes or until tender. Serves 6.

title: nut cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Shape or roll into finger-size pieces and flatten with fork lengthwise.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and bell pepper.
Pour in beans, barbecue sauce and sugar.
Add salt and pepper
to taste.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts and shape into ball. Press nuts on the outside. Serve with crackers.

title: pork picante
directions: Coat pork with hot sauce.
Heat oil in nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add pork and brown.
Add salsa and preserves to pan; lower heat, cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Mix and bake in small muffin tins at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over bran and let cool.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add buttermilk.
Add flour and baking soda.
Fold in water and bran.
Fold in Kellogg's All-Bran.
Makes 1 gallon.
Keeps 6 weeks in the refrigerator. Fill muffin tins 1/2 full and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter and jam bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugars, shortening, peanut butter and egg.
Stir in flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Reserve 1 cup dough.
Press remaining dough into ungreased rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Spread with jam.
Crumble reserved dough and sprinkle over jam.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes. Cool and drizzle with Glaze.
Cut into bars, about 2 x 1 1/2-inches.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pudding poke cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix as directed on package for 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Remove from oven.
Immediately poke holes down through cake to pan with round handle of wooden spoon.
Holes should be at 1-inch intervals.

title: lemon charlotte russe
directions: Soften gelatin in lemon juice; set aside.
Beat egg yolks with 1 cup sugar and the salt until thick (beat in sugar gradually). In top of double boiler, combine egg yolk mixture, softened gelatin and butter.
Cook over hot, not boiling, water until thickened, stirring constantly, about 10 minutes.
Stir in lemon peel and vanilla.
Cool until mixture begins to thicken.

title: fruit slush punch
directions: Heat sugar and water until sugar is dissolved; cool.
Blend bananas in blender.
Add a little of the pineapple juice.
Combine banana mixture, remaining pineapple juice, orange juice and lemonade; freeze in 1/2-gallon containers.
(I use Ziploc Baggies.)

title: biscuit pizzas
directions: Biscuit pizzas are great for every occasion.
They are good for party hors d'oeuvres, cookouts, quick snacks or supper, lunch and even breakfast.
It's really very simple, just spread pizza sauce on the biscuits, put cheese on them and pop them in the oven at 350°.
Cook from 7 to 10 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Add all ingredients at once in bowl and mix together.
Grease tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Top when cool with powdered sugar. Cake can be frozen.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Sprinkle flour over meat.
Slowly add water; blend.
Simmer, stirring, until thickened.
Mix sour cream and soup; blend with meat.
Return to heat; simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve on toasted bun or wide noodles.

title: shrimp and crab salad
directions: Cook macaroni, drain well.
Finely chop celery, green pepper and onion.
Add all ingredients and mix well.

title: mexican rice
directions: In large skillet, heat oil and add the rice and saute to a light brown color.
Stir continuously.
Add onion, garlic and green pepper.
Add salt, pepper and cumin.
Add tomato sauce and stir well.
Add tomatoes and water.
Cover and cook over medium heat for about 20 minutes or until water is absorbed.
Do not stir while cooking.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: jew bread
directions: Cook sugar and eggs at low heat until creamy.
Then mix flour and pecans together.
Add sugar, egg mixture and vanilla.
Put in greased pan.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cut in squares while hot and remove from pan.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown chicken in butter in large skillet.
Add sausage, green pepper, onion and celery; cook until vegetables are just tender, about 5 minutes.
Mix in tomatoes and water; bring to a full boil. Stir in rice, salt and hot pepper sauce.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: angel cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add dates and beat about 3 minutes.
Stir in nuts, cereal and vanilla.
Cool. Drop into small balls and roll each in coconut.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen balls.

title: rice salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large container.
Chill and serve.

title: homemade mints
directions: Add coloring to water.
Mix all the ingredients together with your hands.
Roll out with rolling pin and cut into desired shapes.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
With mixer, add salt, baking soda and baking powder.
With mixer add 1/2 flour and oatmeal.
(Put small amount of oatmeal in blender at a time and blend until it turns to a powder.)
By hand mix in balance of flour and oatmeal, chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and nuts.
Bake on ungreased sheet.
Make golf ball size cookies. Bake at 375° for 6 to 10 minutes.
Makes just over 100 cookies.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients.
Pour small amount of batter into a greased tube pan.
Add a layer of apples and sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on the apples, then add another layer of batter.
Cover with another layer of apples, sprinkled with cinnamon and sugar.
Continue layering until ingredients are used. Apples to be last layer; top with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: baked custard
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt oleo in baking dish.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour over oleo.
Cover and bake one hour.

title: sweet and sour stir-fry chicken
directions: Toss chicken with cornstarch.
Heat oil in large nonstick frying pan. Add chicken stir-fry 2 or 3 minutes until vegetables are crisp and tender.
Pour in sauce and return chicken to skillet.
Then stir for a few minutes.

title: tuna chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat, but do not boil.
Serve and enjoy!

title: potato and egg scramble
directions: Saute onion and potatoes in butter or margarine until potatoes are golden brown.
Mix eggs with milk, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Cook gently, stirring lightly, until eggs are cooked.
Serve with ham, bacon or fried bologna, toast and jelly.

title: tortilla chip dip
directions: Brown and drain beef. In a crock-pot, heat the beef, cheese and salsa until the cheese melts. (This will take about an hour.) Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: low-fat quick muffins
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients. Add milk and mix. Blend in fruit and nuts. Spoon into muffin cups and bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato bourbon pie
directions: Cook (boil or bake) potatoes; then use a potato masher strainer to get 2 cups of mashed sweet potatoes.
Cream sugar and butter; add potatoes, eggs, nutmeg, vanilla, lemon juice and bourbon.
Bake in unbaked pie shell (9-inch pan) at 325° for 45 minutes.
If you don't use the pie fairly soon, you can freeze it (wrap in individual slices in plastic wrap before freezing).

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in small amount of fat.
Remove and drain. Saute onion, celery and bell pepper.
Arrange pork chops in bottom of casserole.
Add onion, celery and bell pepper, soup using can full of water.
Add raw rice and mix with soup.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove cover and brown slightly if desired.

title: cheese broccoli casserole
directions: Grease a
2-quart
casserole dish and lay broccoli flat along the bottom.
Sprinkle
half
of the shredded cheese over the broccoli.
Pour
the
cream
of
mushroom
soup
over
the cheese. Sprinkle with half of the can of onion rings and then the rest of the cheese.
Drip the French dressing all over the top of the casserole.	Top
with
the	remaining onion rings. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.	Serves 4 to 6.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Put a layer of each of first 4 items in a baking dish.
Place crackers on top.
Bake approximately 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: oriental fish rice
directions: Saute
onion
in
margarine. Add curry powder, soup and milk. Mix and heat.
Cook rice as directed on package. Fry or broil fish
fillets.
Place
rice
on
serving platter.
Pour sauce over
rice. Arrange fish on top of sauce.
Garnish with lemon slices or sprigs of parsley.
Serve immediately. Serves 4.

title: holiday punch
directions: Put in large punch bowl.
Blend Hawaiian punch, dry lemonade, pineapple juice and 7-Up.
Spoon in sherbet just before serving.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: You will also need six 8-ounce hot sterilized jars.

title: easy punch(serves 60)
directions: Mix and freeze in Tupperware container for 2 days.
When ready to serve, add 4 quarts ginger ale.
The punch mix will keep for weeks.

title: maple fudge frosting
directions: Mix together. Cook (about 13 minutes) to soft-ball stage (234°). Cool. Beat until thick enough to spread.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon.
Chop bacon fine and sprinkle (uncooked) on top.
Bake at 300°, uncovered, in a 9 x 13-inch pan, for 2 hours.

title: french crepes
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, milk, eggs, oil and salt.
Beat until blended.
Heat a lightly greased skillet.
Remove from heat; spoon in 2 tbsp. or 1/4 c. butter.
Lift and tilt skillet to spread batter evenly.
It should be very thin.
Return to heat.
Brown then flip.
(This makes a lot of crepes, usually half the recipe for the chicken.)

title: michelle's fudge
directions: Mix cocoa in sugar; add milk and Karo.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally to soft ball stage.
Take off heat; add margarine and cool until pan can be held.
Add vanilla; beat the fudge until it starts to hold shape in pan for 15 seconds and fudge loses glossiness.
Pour in buttered plate; score and cut in small squares.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt oleo and mix with crumbs.
Pat down in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

Sprinkle ingredients on in this order: 1 cup chocolate chips, 1 cup butterscotch chips, 1/2 cup walnuts, 1/2 cup coconut, 1 cup chocolate chips, 1 cup butterscotch chips, 1/2 cup walnuts, 1/2 cup coconut and then Eagle Brand milk.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: venison stew
directions: Roll the meat in flour, salt and pepper, then brown in shortening.
Add seasonings or seasoning mix, 1 teaspoon salt and water.
Cover and simmer for about 45 minutes.
Add vegetables and cook another half hour.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add beef and brown.
Drain off grease.
Add spaghetti sauce, soup and sugar.
Mix well.
Stir in spaghetti (use your own judgment about how much spaghetti to add, mixture should not be too dry).
Pour into baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In saucepan over low heat, melt morsels with milk.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread evenly into wax paper-lined, 8-inch square pan.
Chill 2 to 3 hours or until firm.

title: jigsaw casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and minced onion in a 10-inch frypan on automatic top burner set at 400°.
Add tomato and chili beef soup. Lower temperature to 325° and bring mixture to a simmer, stirring well.
Blend in salt and chili powder.
Line casserole dish with half the corn chips.
Spoon in meat mixture.
Top with remaining corn chips.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted or about 25 minutes.
Serve hot!

title: chicken and broccoli with mushroom sauce
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Mix margarine and flour together in saucepan.
Cook briefly over medium heat. Blend in chicken broth, stirring constantly until thickened and smooth.
Stir in mushrooms.
Place broccoli pieces in shallow baking pan.
Cover with chicken and pour mushroom mixture on top of chicken.
Top with parsley and bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 15 to 25 minutes or until bubbly and brown on top. Yields 4 servings.

title: creamy fettucini alfredo
directions: Combine cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, margarine and milk. Cook over low heat until smooth.
Then add 8 ounces of fettucini, cooked and drained.
Toss lightly.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Melt chocolate chips.
Add milk and sugar until you have desired consistency.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Put chopped lettuce (and green onions and/or radishes) in large metal or glass bowl.
Add bacon and toss.
Mix vinegar, sugar and water together until dissolved.
Then pour vinegar and sugar mixture over lettuce; toss some more, cover with a lid or plate to keep warm.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini to package directions.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
Combine pasta and remaining ingredients.
Toss well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
This makes a large batch, but will keep for several days.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix ground beef, rice, salt and pepper.
Break cabbage head into pieces and lay in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer ground beef mixture, then sauerkraut and cover with sauce.
Add 1/4 cup of water; cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain off grease.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes, garlic, onion, basil, salt and pepper.
Cook about 30 minutes. Cook noodles as directed.
Mix in large bowl, Ricotta or cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, eggs and parsley and set aside.
In a 9 x 13 baking pan arrange 1 layer of noodles, then Ricotta mixture, Mozzarella cheese and meat sauce mixture.
Repeat layers until you use all of mixtures.
Bake at 425° for about 25 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes before cutting.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix together and cook over medium heat until thickened into a sauce the flour, sugar and juice.
In a baking dish, alternate layers of pineapple, cheese and sauce.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Good with ham or chicken.

title: chicken picatta
directions: Lightly coat chicken in flour, salt and pepper mixture.
Heat oil in skillet to medium.
Brown both sides of chicken breasts (until done).
Remove chicken from skillet.
Add margarine, lemon juice and wine to pan drippings.
Heat to boil.
Pour over chicken on serving platter or return chicken to pan until ready to serve (warms over nicely).

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into bite size balls.
Bake in shallow pan at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
If frozen, add 15 minutes to baking time.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix juice from oranges and enough water to make one cup.
Heat and stir in Jell-O until dissolved.
Let cool, mix together and let set.

title: kria's tomato soup
directions: Use a small pan and pour both juices in pan.
Simmer slowly until heated thoroughly.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water in saucepan until tender. Cool.
Peel potatoes.
Combine with melted margarine, sugar, 1/2 cup brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and evaporated milk in mixer bowl. Beat until smooth or process in blender for creamy mixture.
Spoon into lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Cut 1/3 cup margarine into flour and 1/2 cup brown sugar in small bowl until crumbly. Add pecans; mix well.
Sprinkle over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Make a roux of 1 stick of butter and the flour, cooking over low heat until flour is brown, stirring constantly, about 20 minutes.
Add the chopped vegetables and seasonings; cook until vegetables are softened, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in stock and let simmer 15 minutes or until thickened.
Add shrimp, green onions, remaining butter, and sherry; bring to a simmer. Simmer for about 5 minutes, cover, remove from heat and let sit for 15 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: raspberry rectangles
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix, then add all dry ingredients.
Add coconut and nuts.
Pat 2/3 of mix into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then spread jam over this.
Add remaining mix on top and pat down.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: macaroni and chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 10.

title: raisin pie
directions: Boil all until it is thick.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake until done.
Can cover or strip the top.

title: pea salad
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl, season to taste and mix gently. Chill.

title: bacon and water chestnuts
directions: Roll 1/2 strip of raw bacon around 2 chestnuts.
Broil until bacon is done.
Pour off grease.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Mix together sugar and ketchup; pour over bacon and serve.

title: holiday crab dip
directions: Blend together first 5 ingredients.
Fold in chopped parsley, garlic powder and crab meat.
Serve with crackers.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Melt butter in larger saucepan over medium heat.
Add potatoes, green onions and dill seed.
Saute for 3 minutes.
Add milk and simmer over low heat for 20 minutes.
Add fresh salmon and simmer for 10 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Garnish with dill sprigs.
Serves 8.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix until thick.
Add Cool Whip. Eat and enjoy!

title: mints
directions: Add water to ingredients to make a thick mixture.
Shape into design and let sit for 4 or 5 days.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch or one 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients; beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and buttermilk.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° in 9-inch pans for 35 minutes or oblong pan for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: lazy man cabbage rolls
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add remaining ingredients, except cabbage.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Spray casserole dish with nonstick spray.
Place 1 small head of cabbage, shredded, in dish. Top with meat mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Enjoy!

title: noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add tomato puree, tomato soup, olives, mushrooms and spaghetti sauce.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix with cooked noodles.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts. This freezes well.

title: meatball vegetable soup
directions: Season meat with garlic powder and pepper.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls and brown on all sides.
Drain and put in soup pot with water.
Put on high heat.
Add onions and celery.
Bring to a boil.
Then add carrots and potatoes.
Cook until carrots are almost done.
Then add frozen vegetables, bay leaves and tomatoes. Cook 20 minutes longer. Tastes even better the next day.
Serves 10.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in margarine.
Pour in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with mixed vegetables.
Next, mix soups and pour over top of vegetables.
Arrange Tater Tots over soup, vegetables and meat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti
directions: Cook items together for 1 hour.
Add cooked spaghetti, then cook together 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: parmesan baked vidalias
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8-inch casserole dish.
Peel and slice onions into 1/2-inch strips.

title: lemon fruit creme(fruit dip)
directions: Beat in a bowl the eggs, 1/2 cup sugar and lemon juice.
Cook 1/2 cup sugar mixed in 1/2 cup water and cornstarch and stir until thickened in bowl.
Remove from the heat.
Gradually beat the egg mixture into the hot mixture.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened over low heat.
Add vanilla and cool.
Fold in whipping cream.
Chill.
Serve with cut apples, grapes, kiwi, strawberries, peaches, etc.

title: babe's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
My favorite use is baking pork chops with this sauce over them.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix together.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, beat 1 1/4 cups sugar, shortening and vanilla until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and bananas. Combine flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Beat into sugar mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Chill 30 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheets.

title: spiced zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts; set aside.
Beat eggs lightly in a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients, stirring only until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: beet soup
directions: Put pork in pot; cover with water.
Add bay leaves, salt and pepper.
Cover; simmer for 1 hour.
Fry bacon and onion until golden.
Add flour until brown.
Add vinegar and beets to meat, along with bacon mixture.
Mix sour cream and 2 tablespoons water; dump in the pot.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Combine soup, mayonnaise, milk and cheese.
Blend well.
Stir in salmon, peas, noodles and onion.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Something smells fishy!)

title: no weep meringue
directions: Beat egg whites with cornstarch until fairly stiff, then add sugar.
Bake as usual.
Makes enough for one pie.

title: crock-pot scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and chop potatoes.
Cook in water to cover in saucepan for 3 minutes; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Spoon into crock-pot.
Cook on high for 3 hours.
Yields 10 servings.

title: opal's chocolate fudge
directions: Mix chocolate chips and marshmallow cream in a bowl.
Mix butter, sugar and milk in boiler.
Boil 8 to 10 minutes.
Pour over chips and marshmallow mixture.
Beat until glossy.
Pour on baking dish.
Cut in squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: grandpa bradshaw's fudge
directions: In large saucepan, bring first 4 ingredients to boil; cook for 5 minutes at low boil.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and chocolate.
Stir until stiff.
Pour into greased pan.
When set, cut in squares.

title: potato chowder
directions: Combine half the potatoes with broth in saucepan with tight fitting lid.
Bring to boil; simmer until potatoes are tender when pierced with a fork, about 10 minutes.
Mash potatoes with a fork.
Stir in remaining
potatoes, carrots, corn, celery, onion and seasonings.
Cover; simmer until vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes.
Dissolve flour in a little of the cream and parsley. Cook stirring over medium heat to thicken slightly.
Serve topped with grated cheese.
Makes about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: old fashioned chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut chicken into pieces.
Combine chicken, celery, carrot, onion, salt and pepper in a large pan; cover with water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for about 1 1/2 hours. Remove chicken from broth; set aside until it cools.
Debone chicken; place pieces back into pan.
Add the potatoes and corn to mixture; simmer.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine the butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla, bananas, pecans, sour cream, flour, baking soda and salt in the order listed in a mixer bowl, mixing well after each addition.
Beat for 1 minute.
Spoon into a greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Invert onto a wire rack to cool.
Slice and spread with Orange Cream Cheese Filling.
Yield:
1 medium loaf.

title: apple bread
directions: Beat by hand the oil, nuts, eggs and sugar.
Add flour, soda, salt, vanilla and apples.
Pour in ungreased angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Leave in pan until cool.

title: short'nen bread
directions: Cream eggs and butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour a 9-inch loaf pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt in heavy saucepan.
Cook until it reaches a hard ball stage on candy thermometer (very important).
Remove from heat.
Pour syrup over stiffly beaten egg whites very slowly, beating constantly.
Add vanilla and nuts and continue beating until it loses its glossy look and holds its shape.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: easy oven barbecue brisket
directions: Mix together salt, pepper, mustard, Lea & Perrins, brown sugar, Tabasco, garlic powder, liquid smoke, catsup and red pepper.
Pour mixture over brisket.
Wrap in heavy foil and fasten loosely.
Bake at 250° to 300° for 4 1/2 to 5 hours.
After brisket cooks, slice thinly and spread sauce from brisket over each slice.
Delicious.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots; drain.
Saute onion in 3 tablespoons butter. Stir in soup, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup cheese.
Mix with carrots in casserole.
Toss bread croutons in 1/2 cup butter (melted). Arrange on carrots; top with 1 cup of remaining cheese.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of mushroom

title: scalloppine di vitello con carciofi(escalopes of veal with artichokes)
directions: Heat oil and butter in a large skillet.
Add veal and brown gently over moderate heat for 10 minutes.
Add thawed artichokes. Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle wine over all.
As soon as the wine has evaporated, stir in the parsley and cream.
Cover and reduce heat to low.
Continue cooking for 15 minutes.
Transfer escalopes to a serving dish.
Arrange artichokes on the dish and coat with sauce.
Serve immediately.

title: mexican chicken somis
directions: Pound chicken breasts thin.
Put in microwave dish; cover and cook at half power 3 1/2 minutes, turning several times.
(Chicken will not be cooked.)
In large pan on stove, saute onions in 2 tablespoons oil (add margarine if needed).
Add oregano, cumin, paprika, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Stir well.
Add enchilada sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Add salt to taste and peanut butter. Cook on low heat 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Place chicken in large baking dish.
Salt and pepper.
Place a slice of cheese and whole green chilies over that.
Spread sauce over breasts. Bake 25 minutes at 400°, basting halfway through.
Serve extra sauce on the side.

title: peanut soup
directions: Melt butter in cooking vessel.
Add onion and celery; saute for 5 minutes (not brown).
Add flour; mix well.
Add hot chicken broth; cook for 1 half hour.
Remove from stove, strain and add peanut butter, celery salt, salt and lemon juice.
Sprinkle ground peanuts on soup just before serving.
Serves 20 (1/2-cups).

title: stuffed steak and parsley potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In roasting pan, place sliced potatoes in single layer.
Add 3/4 cup water.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: snow biscuits
directions: Mix yeast in warm water first.
Put into dry ingredients.
Mix gently.
Turn onto floured board and shape into rolls.
Let rise about 45 minutes if possible.
(It doesn't take long for these to rise, just depends on the temperature.) Bake for about 12 minutes at 425°.
Makes about a dozen.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix macaroni, hamburger and onions together.
To this, add rest of ingredients.
Add several dashes of garlic salt, onion salt and oregano.
Mix well.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: creamy shrimp dip
directions: Put cheese and soup in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Microwave on Medium (50%) for 4 to 6 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Stir halfway through cooking.
Stir in shrimp, juice, and chives until smooth.
Serve with crackers or vegetable.
Yield: about 2 cups.

title: seafood nachos
directions: Place chips on baking sheet.
Place crab meat on top of chips. Put cheese on top of crab meat. Sprinkle with paprika.
Place in hot oven until cheese melts or in microwave in glass dish until cheese melts.
Serve with cocktail sauce.

title: russian meat pockets(pirozhki)
directions: Soften yeast in milk.
Add 1 cup of flour.
Let rise in warm place for 1 hour.
Add remaining flour and 1/2 tsp. of salt, sugar, eggs and melted butter.
Mix well.
Let rise until doubled in size. Divide into egg sized pieces.
Roll each piece flat.
Brown onion and meat in remaining 1/2 cup of butter.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add eggs, mix well.
Place 1/2 Tbsp. of meat mixture on each piece of dough and fold over.
Seal edges and let rise a few minutes.
Fry in oil heated to 375 F until brown.
You can also brush with a beaten egg and bake at 400 F for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: squash parmesan
directions: Dice onion and saute in butter until transparent.
Add sliced squash and continue to saute.
When squash is slightly brown and limp, remove from heat.
Serve with generous amounts of Parmesan cheese on top.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, and vanilla.
Beat until thick and foamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Combine flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, baking powder, nutmeg, nuts, and raisins.
Gently stir in zucchini mixture.
Stir with spoon until blended.
Pour into two 5 x 9 greased and flour pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes before dumping out.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Allow several hours to blend in refrigerator.
Finished results:
congealed.

title: ham casserole
directions: Combine bread cubes, parsley, onion, salt, poultry seasoning and 1/2 cup milk.
Toss gently until combined.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Drain peas; reserve liquid.
Put peas over dressing.
Add ham.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Blend in flour and mustard.
Measure liquid from peas and add milk to make 2 cups.
Blend into flour mixture.
Over medium heat, cook stirring until sauce thickens and boils.
Pour over ham.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: fruit-filled coffee cake
directions: Put half of mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Spread 1 can pie mix over this, then add rest of mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake 50 minutes at 325°.

title: kathy's chicken pot pie
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Add flour and stir until blended.
Add milk or chicken stock.
Stir with wire whisk and cook until thickened.
Add chicken and vegetables, salt, pepper and celery salt to taste.
Put into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover with pie pastry, bake at 400° about 20 minutes, or until pastry is lightly browned.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Add to 8 oz. cool-whip. Turn into a graham cracker or cookie crumb pie shell. Freeze. Take out of freezer 15 to 30 minutes before serving. The Keebler Cookie Crumb Crust is especially good!

title: egg custard
directions: Break eggs in mixing bowl; mix them thoroughly.
Stir in sugar until blended in good.
Stir in milk.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 375° until firm, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: vegetarian stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops off peppers; remove seed.
Place peppers in a 12 x 8-inch microwave-safe baking dish.
Cover with waxed paper. Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Mix 6 ounces Velveeta cheese spread and remaining ingredients; fill peppers.
Cover with wax paper. Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes or until thoroughly heated, turning dish after 5 minutes.
Top with remaining Velveeta cheese spread.
Microwave on High 2 minutes or until cheese spread begins to melt.
Makes 6 servings.
Preparation time:
20 minutes. Microwave cooking time:
16 minutes.

title: streusel coffee cake
directions: Measure cake mix into small bowl.
Cut in oleo.
Mix in brown sugar and chopped nuts.
Set mixture aside.

title: jewish bagels
directions: Scald milk.
Add butter and sugar.
Cool to lukewarm.
Mix in yeast.
Beat in egg white and salt.
Work in flour and knead until no longer sticky, about 7 to 9 minutes.
Let rise until double. Punch down.
Shape into 12 to 15 doughnutlike pieces.
Let rise for 10 minutes (maybe a little longer).
Drop into boiling water for about 15 to 20 seconds until dough puffs.
Put on greased baking sheets.

Brush with egg yolk, diluted with 1 tablespoon water. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown on top. Spread with cream cheese mixed with imitation crabmeat or shrimp, celery and onions.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend first four ingredients well.
Add Cool Whip, pour in 1 large or 2 small graham cracker pie crusts.
Refrigerate or freeze, covered.
If frozen, allow to thaw in the refrigerator.

title: fireweed-clover honey
directions: Wash blossoms in colander to remove dust and bugs.
Put blossoms in large pan with water and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let steep for 10 minutes (like tea).
Strain. Bring to a boil again, adding sugar and alum.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Pour into small, sterilized jars and seal.
Yields 1/2 gallon honey.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese or vanilla frosting.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts on top.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix soup and water, pour over chicken pieces in baking pan (9 x 12-inch).
Slice boiled eggs on top (can substitute a can of Veg-All, drained).
Mix flour and buttermilk together and pour over chicken.
Over this, pour 2 cups chicken broth.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Feeds 8.

title: "lite" creamed potatoes
directions: Steam (covered) boil potatoes in small amount of salted water. (A chicken bouillon cube can be substituted for salt.)
When tender, drain, retaining liquid.
Add Ranch dressing (more or less as needed) and beat potatoes with electric mixer.
If needed, add small amounts of retained liquid (or skim milk if desired) until of desired consistency.
Add butter sprinkles to taste.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Mix.
Cover bowl, let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: gingerbread with vanilla sauce
directions: Cut flour, oleo and sugar together.
Set aside 1 cup of mix. In remainder, sprinkle soda and spices.
Then add eggs and mix well.
Lightly stir in buttermilk.
Pour in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle rest of mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
When ready to serve, top with Vanilla or Rum Sauce, if desired.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and margarine.
Spread 1/2 this mixture in an 8 x 10-inch pan.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Prepare both packages of whipped topping mix according to package directions.
Add cream cheese mixture to whipped topping; mix thoroughly.
Put 1/2 of this mixture over the first layer of crumbs.
Spread pie filling over that, then remainder of whipped topping over pie filling, then remainder of crumbs.

title: ground meat and pasta pie
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions and drain.
In a large bowl, toss with 2 tablespoons butter and set aside.

title: old-fashioned apple-raisin cake
directions: *Two cups of chopped apples may be substituted for applesauce. Increase water to 3/4 cup.
Add apples with raisins.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in 2-quart saucepan. Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Remove from heat. Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, until bubbly, 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.
Fat: None.
Oil:
Per serving - 2 1/3 teaspoons.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and flour alternately. Mix in other ingredients.
Bake in tube pan, greased and floured, at 325° on bottom rack for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: kentucky mile-high biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add egg and milk all at once; mix until dough forms a ball.
Turn dough out on a lightly floured surface and knead 10 to 12 times.
Roll out to 3/4-inch thickness; cut with floured 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and freeze.
When biscuits have frozen, they may be stored in a plastic bag in the freezer until needed.

title: potluck rice
directions: Brown sausage and onion together.
Drain off excess fat.
Add bouillon, salt and tomatoes; heat to boiling.
Stir in rice. Cover and cook over very low heat for approximately 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Add olives and pimento.
Mix lightly with a fork.

title: christmas cupcakes
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add sour cream.
Stir in dried ingredients and then fruit and nuts.
Mix well.
Fill greased and floured muffin tins 3/4 full, placing half cherry on top of each one.
Bake in 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes.

title: frozen lemon pie from the red barnwestport, connecticut
directions: Beat the yolks, salt and sugar in the top of a double boiler. Stir in the lemon juice and rind.
Cook over hot, not boiling, water until the mixture thickens and coats the spoon.
Remove from the heat and chill.
Beat the egg whites until stiff, and fold in the whipping cream and cooked mixture.
Sprinkle half of the wafer crumbs into a freezing tray, then pour in mixture.
Top with the remaining crumbs and freeze until firm.
Serve in finger length slices.
This may be made a day or two before serving.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in a little oil.
Thaw broccoli and drain.
Cut up into pieces.
Mix all ingredients and pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until bubbly in oven at 375°.

title: cheese crescents
directions: Just before baking rolls, brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with cheese.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together oleo, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Pour over cereal.
Stir until coated.
Empty powdered sugar in brown paper bag.
Dump cereal mixture in bag and shake until coated. Great snack.

title: mozzarella cheese puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream butter; add cheese and blend.
Add dry ingredients; mix well and shape into small balls.
Place balls on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until puffed and golden brown. Makes 24 puffs.

title: potato cakes
directions: Prepare potato mix as directed on package.
Cool.
Mix potatoes, cheese, crumbs, egg, parsley, onion, herbs and salt. Heat oil in a 10-inch skillet.
Drop potato mixture by rounded tablespoonfuls into skillet.
Flatten with spatula.
Cook over medium heat until light brown, about 3 minutes on each side. Drain.

title: chicken milano
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot margarine, cook onion and garlic until tender. Stir in chicken and cook until lightly browned, stirring frequently.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot rice.

title: sticky buns
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

In 9 x 11 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pan, melt margarine in oven. Remove. Stir in next 5 ingredients. Arrange biscuits in syrup mixture. Bake 15 minutes or until biscuits are well browned. Let stand in pan 5 minutes. Invert onto serving plate. Yields 10 servings.

title: shrimp and scallop stew
directions: Slice leeks in half lengthwise and cut into 1/2-inch dice. In stockpot, heat oil over medium heat. Add leeks and garlic and saut, stirring until translucent, about 7 minutes. Add jalapeno peppers, carrots, spices and salt; lower heat to medium-low and cook until carrots are almost tender (4 or 5 minutes).
Add tomatoes, wine and 1 cup water.
Bring to a boil and then lower heat to medium.
Cook 5 minutes. Stir in shrimp and scallops. Cook until opaque, 4 to 6 minutes. Remove from heat. Add parsley and serve over rice or couscous pilaf. Serves 4.

title: steak marinated in wine
directions: Wipe meat with a damp paper towel.
Place meat in a roasting bag or deep dish.
Combine all ingredients and pour over meat. Tie roasting bag or cover dish.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Turn meat.

title: fudgy chocolate bars
directions: Combine dry ingredients and cut in butter until crumbly (mix will be dry).
Press on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: best pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: linguini salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Toss before serving.
Will keep about 6 days.

title: mushroom and onion soup
directions: Either in a food
processor
with coarse shredding disk coarsely grate mushrooms or knife chop coarsely, about 3 cups. In a medium saucepan melt butter,
add onions and cook gently, stirring often until golden brown
and
tender.
Add mushrooms and cook rapidly, stirring often until wilted.
Have heat high enough so mushrooms do not give
off
their
liquid.
Stir
in flour, salt and pepper.
Turn off
heat
and gradually stir in broth and milk, keeping smooth;
then over moderate heat, stir constantly. Cook until thickened.
Makes
3 1/2 cups.
Sprinkle with fresh parsley or chives.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix all together in large container.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Use as desired.
Bake in muffin tins at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: creamy broccoli casserole
directions: Beat eggs; add soup, mayo, pecans and onion.
Stir in broccoli.
Pour into greased 2-quart shallow pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken la' zucchini
directions: Place chicken in fryer with small amount of oil.
Cook slowly until chicken is tender.
Drain all oil from fryer.
Add all ingredients on top of chicken.
Simmer slowly until squash is very tender, about 1 hour.
Keep covered while simmering, stirring only when needed.
Serve from stove top!
Makes a meal in one, entree with vegetables.
Tastes great!
Feeds 4 to 8 persons.

title: bacca cobbler
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients in a mixer until foamy. Add by spoonfuls, the flour; spread 3/4 dough over bottom of pan. Add the cherry pie filling, spreading over batter. Drop rest of dough on top. Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: savory summer squash
directions: Fry bacon in
skillet
until crisp.
Drain on absorbent paper. Combine squash, salt, and pepper in bacon drippings in skillet. Cover and cook stirring occasionally for about 15 to 20 minutes, until
tender.
Just before serving, sprinkle with bacon and cheese.

title: strawberries and cream cake
directions: Cut cake into small cubes.
In a large bowl mix pudding and milk, add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Mix well and chill for 1 hour.
Wash and slice strawberries (sprinkle with sugar if desired).
Chill for 1 hour.
In a punch bowl, layer cake, cream and berries.
Repeat until all is used, ending with berries. Chill and serve.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Cream the sugar and oleo. Beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well. Add flour. Beat in extract and Seven-Up.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: In a separate pot, boil shrimp shells in 1-quart unseasoned water 25 minutes.
Add water to retain volume.
Strain through cheesecloth.
Retain liquid.
In a large heavy gumbo pot, add oil and flour to make a roux.
Cook until golden brown.
Add all seasonings.
Saute 5 to 10 minutes.
Add shrimp and saute 10 minutes.
Add hot water, 1-quart reserved liquid, tomatoes, lemon rind, bay leaves.
Stir well.
Add crab meat and salmon.
Cook 45 minutes.
Season to taste.
Serve over rice.
Garnish with parsley.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry hamburger all together. Stir while cooking. Drain. In casserole dish, stir meat, corn and soup together. Layer mashed potatoes on top. Be careful not to mix with meat, corn and soup. Heat until potatoes are brown on top.

title: pizza crust
