directions: Combine 1 cup of the flour, yeast and
salt
in
medium bowl. Add water and oil.	With mixer at low speed, beat until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Gradually
stir	in
remaining flour to make a firm dough.	On floured
surface
knead dough. Cover; let rise 15 minutes.
Shape and bake according to pizza recipe.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix Sweet 'N Low, cocoa and flour with a little cold milk until smooth.
Add remainder of milk.
Mix butter and egg yolks.
Add to mixture.
Cook until thickens.
Add vanilla and pour into pie crust.

title: party mix
directions: Combine chocolate, peanut butter, and margarine and melt over low heat.
Add Rice Chex and fold gently until all are coated. Add powdered sugar and fold until all are coated also.
Use hands to mix.
Spoon will break the Rice Chex up.
Store in a sealed glass jar.
Will keep for weeks.

title: caramel icing
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to boil.
Add remaining ingredients. Be ready to apply to cake because this gets hard fast.
It works best on pancakes and also makes good candy.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine butter, flour and sugar in mixer bowl; mix well. Blend in eggs.
Mix cocoa with enough water to make a paste.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Add to sugar mixture, mixing well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: ruby slipper cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, water and sour cream together well. Pour into greased
and
floured	Bundt
pan
of
batter. Sprinkle 1/2 of jello
over batter.	Spoon rest of batter over jello.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: giant cereal sunflowers
directions: Prepare oven to 350°.
In bowl, beat unsalted butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, unsifted flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and sunflower flakes.
Spoon onto baking sheet; bake for 10 minutes.
Makes 20 cookies.

title: baked dove or quail
directions: Preheat
oven
Place birds in casserole.
Mix remaining
ingredients
and
add to casserole.
Cover and cook for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, turning and basting birds frequently.

title: skinny chili
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix meat and onions. Saute until onions are done. Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Equals 3 proteins and 1 1/2 vegetables.

title: pizza burger
directions: Cook the burger by your preferred method. When it's almost done to your liking, top with pizza sauce, then Mozzarella. Cook until the cheese is melted and serve. Yield: 1 serving.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans well.
Spray a 9 inch pan with Pam.
Spread into
pan.
Bake at 300° until brown.
Cool.

title: easy apple dessert(health food)
directions: Put sliced apples in Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice or 1 tablespoon water.
Mix other ingredients and put on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple fritters
directions: Drop a spoonful at a time into hot fat and deep fry until browned.

title: baked stuffed potatoes
directions: Cut off the top third of the potato.
Remove the insides and mash.
Reserve shells.

title: coconut-date balls
directions: Stir
together dates, sugar, pecans and eggs in medium-size saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring 6 to 8 minutes or
until thickened and beginning to simmer. Remove from heat. Stir
in vanilla
and cereal until combined.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto
waxed paper.	Place coconut in small bowl. Roll
cookies into balls.
Roll in coconut, pressing to stick, if necessary. Chill before serving.

title: fettucini or linguine
directions: Keep all ingredients at room temperature 2 to 3 hours.
Cook bacon.
Cook linguini 15 minutes "al dente."
Beat egg and cream to blend.
Add all to linguini with bacon.
Toss well. Top with parsley.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix salmon, 1/2 cup cracker crumbs, pepper and eggs.
Make into balls about the size of an egg and roll in other half of crackers.
Cook in canola oil in skillet.

title: herb-grilled chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Pour over desired amount of chicken pieces to be grilled.
Secure in plastic bag or container.
Marinate for several hours, turning occasionally. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Transfer chicken to grill. Grill on low for another 30 minutes, basting with marinade.

title: fish stock
directions: Rub a deep saucepan very lightly with cooking oil.
Put in all the solid ingredients; cover the pan tightly and cook 15 to 20 minutes over very low heat.
Next, add liquids and salt to pan; bring to a boil.
Reduce to a simmer and cook 45 minutes with the pan uncovered.
Strain stock before putting into container with a well-fitting top for storage in refrigerator.
Stock will keep for about 8 weeks.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: chocolate candy cake
directions: Combine flour,
sugar and soda; mix well and set aside. Combine water,
butter and cocoa in a heavy saucepan; bring to a boil,
stirring
constantly.
Gradually
stir
into
flour mixture.
Stir
in
buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured
13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
While
warm,
prick surface at one-inch intervals with a meat fork; spread Chocolate Candy Frosting.

title: creole chicken
directions: In electric skillet, heated to medium, melt butter.
Chop peppers, celery, olives and chicken and add to melted butter. Slice onions into rings and tomatoes into 8 pieces.
Add to skillet. Smash garlic.
Remove skin.
Add to skillet.
Cook until onions are translucent and chicken is white.
Add sauce, bay leaf, pepper, hot sauce and oregano.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes until flavors have combined and mixture is bubbly.
Add rice and turn off.
Let sit 5 minutes.
Remove bay leaf and serve.
Serves 6.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apple pie filling into a 10-inch square casserole dish. Add apple pie spice and mix.

title: ripe tomato pickle relish
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until thick.
Takes about 1 hour cooking time.
Boil spices in bag so they can be thrown away after cooking.
Vegetables may be chopped in food processor before cooking.
Pour into twelve clean hot pint jars.
Seal immediately with hot boiled lids and rings.
Great with dried beans.

title: diet dessert
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients; mix well.
Add pineapple; fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate!

title: st.  joseph's cream puffs(sfinge di san giuseppe)
directions: Boil water and butter in a saucepan.
Add sifted flour and stir constantly until smooth.
Cook over medium flame until mixture leaves side of pan clean, about 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and allow to cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add grated rind and blend. Drop by tablespoons in ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart and bake in moderate oven at 350° until puffs are light, about 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and cut opening in the middle of top. Cool thoroughly and fill with filling.
Decorate the tops with candied or maraschino cherries.

title: hamburger relish
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
If necessary, add a little kraut juice to get the blender started, but no more than necessary.
Blend until all is chopped.
Store and use as desired.

title: quickmix
directions: In
a large bowl sift all dry ingredients.
Blend well. Cut in
shortening.
Put
in
airtight container.
Store in a cool dry place.
Use within 10 to 12 weeks.
This can be used inter-changeably with Bisquick.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Let cool 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Mix Jell-O as directed.
Make holes in cake with handle of spoon.
Dip the Jell-O by spoonfuls into the holes.
Top with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: barbecue sauce(great for chicken)
directions: Mix and heat all ingredients. Wash and dry meat. Coat meat in flour. Place skin side down on baking dish. Add 1/4 cup butter. Bake 30 minutes at 350° with no sauce. Then add sauce and bake another 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin butter
directions: Mix together very well.
Chill.
Serve on fresh bread, rolls, etc.

title: nurnbergers
directions: In saucepan, heat honey to boiling.
Cool thoroughly.
Stir in sugar, egg, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Mix in remaining ingredients (except almond halves and cherries).
Chill at least 8 hours.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Line pan with pastry.
Combine all ingredients and pour into pie tin.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add liquids.
Roll into balls.
Coat with the confectioners sugar.
Refrigerate in an airtight container.
Best when made the day before.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla until creamy. Add flour, salt, soda and blend.
Stir in oats.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: pecan crisps
directions: Cream butter. Add sugar. Beat until fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Mix in flour, soda, salt and vanilla, then nuts and chips. Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain, then set aside.
Mix together the tuna, salt and pepper to taste and cream of mushroom soup.
Top with either the crackers, crushed, or the bread cubes.
Top with butter, then bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick and easy chicken parmesan
directions: In a large casserole pan, place just enough sauce to cover bottom of pan.
Place chicken patties in pan one next to the other to cover bottom of pan.
Pour remaining sauce over patties. Sprinkle with mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until cheese is bubbly.

title: vegetable beef biscuit
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook beef until brown, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soups, water, mixed vegetables and Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon into 3-quart baking dish. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until bubbling.
Cut biscuits into quarters.

title: hot dogs in sauce
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in large pan.
Add hot dogs; simmer.
Cook 45 minutes.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Mix persimmon pulp and soda. Let stand. Cream shortening, sugar and egg until soft and well blended. Sift flour, salt and spices together. Add pulp mixture into creamed mixture. Gradually add dry mixture, then nuts and raisins. Mix well. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a tube pan (10 to 12 cup capacity).
Place oreo cookies on a cutting board.
With a sharp, heavy knife, cut them one at a time into quarters.
Set aside.

title: carrot cake(for everybody!)
directions: Beat eggs; add vegetable oil.
Sift together dry ingredients. Add dry ingredients to eggs and oil.
Add apple juice concentrate. Stir in carrots, raisins and 1/2 cup walnuts.
Spray an 8 1/2 x 11-inch baking pan with nonstick spray.
Pour batter into pan. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup walnuts over top.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Yield:
32 slices.
One slice equals 180 calories.

title: cheese cake
directions: Crust:
Melt 1 stick of butter and add 1/3 cup of sugar to the 1/2 box of graham cracker crumbs.
Mix all this together and then press into a large pie dish.

title: potato soup (crock-pot)
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot. Cover and cook on low for 4 to 6 hours, stirring occasionally.
Top with croutons.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Chop chocolate coarsely.
Combine with butter and boiling water in a large saucepan; heat over low heat, stirring constantly until chocolate is melted.
Add sugar and corn syrup.
Bring mixture slowly to boiling; lower heat.
Simmer gently 8 minutes, watching carefully, but do not stir.
Test on ice cream or ice cube until it is as firm as you like it.
Add vanilla.
Serve while warm.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease glass pan.
Dump can of cherries, pineapple and cake mix.
Pour melted butter in. Sprinkle with coconut and walnuts. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve in bowls with whipped cream.

title: caprice salad
directions: Arrange lettuce on an oval salad plate to act as a bed.
Slice tomatoes, peppers and cheese.
Arrange the sliced ingredients on the lettuce as follows:
1 slice cheese, 1 slice tomato, 1 slice bell pepper; repeat twice (should have 3 slices of each ingredient on each plate).
Top salad with fresh coarsely ground pepper. Dribble the Dressing over each salad.

title: deviled carrots
directions: Quarter the carrots lengthwise and cook until just tender. Saute partially cooked carrots in butter for 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and cook about 10 more minutes.

title: cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, egg yolk, sugar and vanilla. In a greased 9 x 13 pan, spread 1 can rolls.
Press seams together and brush with some of the egg white.
Spread with cream cheese filling.
Top with other rolls.
Brush with remainder of egg white.

title: crazy crust pizza
directions: Brown meat and season to taste.
Drain and set aside.
Make batter with first 6 ingredients.
Pour batter onto greased and floured pan.
Tilt the pan so the batter covers the entire pan. Arrange meat, onions and mushrooms on batter.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes on low rack.
Remove from oven; drizzle on sauce and cheese.
Bake again for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat to blend soup and cream cheese.
Dissolve Knox gelatine in 1/3 cup water and add to soup mixture.
Fold in onions, shrimp and mayonnaise.
Mold and chill.

title: orange glaze
directions: Open freezer.
Take out frozen dinner and cook in the microwave oven according to the directions on the box.
Eat. Variation of the recipe, pick up the phone and order a pizza.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix altogether.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie.
Bake slowly at 350°.

title: turtle cake
directions: Combine cake mix and
ounces
of evaporated milk and softened butter.
Spread half
of
cake mixture in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
(Mixture will be thick.) Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at
Melt caramels with remaining 4 ounces of evaporated milk.
Pour
this on top of cooked cake.
Spread nuts and chocolate chips on top of caramels.
Spread remainder of cake mixture on top
with
a
wet
spatula.
Bake
15 to 20 minutes. Lay Hershey bars on top of hot cake.
Spread to form icing.
Time of preparation: 50 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook the carrots, cauliflower and broccoli. Place in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cube 1/2 pound Velveeta cheese and mix with vegetables. Slice remaining 1/2 pound Velveeta cheese and place on top. Place the crackers on top. Melt oleo and drizzle over. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes (uncovered).

title: easy barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together until oil dissolves.
Ready to use or chill.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Beat into eggs.
Stir in rhubarb.
Line pie pan.
Fill with rhubarb mixture.
Dot with butter.
Cover with lattice top.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Fry meat lightly in oil, add mushrooms, green onion, rice and soya sauce.
Continue to cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Add egg. Cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
If darker color is wanted, add more soya sauce.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spiced tea
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine water, orange peel, lemon peel and spices.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 6 to 10 minutes or until boiling.
Remove from microwave; immediately add tea bags and steep for 3 to 5 minutes.
Strain.
Serve hot or chilled.
Yield:
4 cups.

title: danish dessert
directions: Heat to boiling; add 3 heaping tablespoonfuls Clear Jell.
Add 1 (6 ounce) package jello.
Cool and add fruit, as desired.

title: lemon cake
directions: Cream oleo, shortening and sugar; add salt, vanilla and egg yolks.
Add milk.
Add 1/2 cup flour and baking powder.
Add remaining flour; mix well.
Fold in egg whites after beating.
Bake at 350°.
Make 14 thin layers.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Peel, slice and boil potatoes.
In mixing bowl, combine potatoes, garlic seasoning, sour cream and cream cheese; blend with mixer on medium speed.
Spread in casserole dish.
Spread shredded cheese on top of mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream margarine, sugar, and egg.
Stir in flour.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place one inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: michele's finger lick'n fried chicken(oven baked)
directions: Combine all the dry ingredients in a doubled plastic food bag. Shake well.
Prepare a 10 X 15 X 3/4-inch pan with Pam or wipe it well with oil.
Run chicken under cold water.
Put in a colander and drain a few minutes. Dredge pieces in the flour mixture, one at a time, shaking and coating well.
Arrange the pieces on the prepared pan.
Melt 1/4 pound butter or margarine, and using a soft-bristled pastry brush, dab the melted margarine over the floured surface of each piece.
Bake, uncovered, without turning, at 375° for 20 to 45 minutes or until golden brown and tender. Serves 4 to 6.

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, salt, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 egg in
mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Spoon into pie shell.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Combine corn syrup, remaining 3 eggs, remaining 1/4 cup sugar and remaining 1 teaspoon vanilla in small bowl; mix well.
Pour over pecan layer.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a pan and boil for 5 minutes.
Roll out pie dough and cut into 4 squares.
Put apples in center of each and sprinkle with a little sugar and cinnamon. Fold up, seal and lay upside down in greased pan.
Pour warm mixture over the dumplings.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until tops are brown.

title: kenya's favorite peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, milk and butter to a boil.
Turn fire down, but continue to boil, stirring constantly for 3 minutes.
Take off heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until batter begins to lose shine. Pour into buttered pie plate and let cool.

title: economical pecan pie
directions: Add all ingredients to eggs.
Pour in shell.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Split rolls and spread mixture on both sides of roll.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, covered with foil. May be frozen; allow longer for baking if not completely thawed when placed in oven.
Makes enough for 40 to 60 rolls.
Great to have for holidays.

title: pineapple-cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Combine juice, sugar and flour in bowl, mixing well.
Stir in cheese and pineapple.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Combine margarine/butter and cracker crumbs in bowl, mixing well.
Sprinkle over pineapple mixture.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak bread in milk; mix with beef.
Add all ingredients, except tomato sauce.
Mix well.
Turn into loaf pan.
Cover with soup or sauce.
Put bacon slices on top, if desired.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Baste occasionally.

title: chicken casserole with stuffing(gloria)
directions: Butter baking dish; cover bottom with half of stuffing mix. Arrange chicken breasts.
Top each breast with salt and pepper, minced onion flakes, parsley flakes and one slice of Swiss cheese. Add half of blended soup mix, rest of stuffing and rest of soup mix.
Bake at 350° for one and one-half hours.

title: tomato pie
directions: Bake pie shell until almost done.
Place chopped tomatoes in pie crust.
Top with liberal amount of basil, oregano and pepper. Mix mayo, onion and cheese together; spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit soda, salt and baking powder.

title: three days ahead juicy coconut cake
directions: Prepare butter cake mix as directed on package.
Place batter in 8-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Bake as directed on package.
While cake is baking, mix together sugar and sour cream. After well mixed, place in refrigerator until well chilled.
Take cooked, cooled layers and slice in halves with thread.
(Wrap thread around cake in center and pull.)
Remove chilled sour cream mixture and add thawed coconut, saving 1 cup.
Place mixture between each layer, but not on top.
Mix reserved coconut mixture with Cool Whip and ice sides and top.
Refrigerate for three days.

title: creamy frozen yogurt(low sodium)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Stir in yogurt until well blended and smooth.
Fold in whipped topping. Pour into 9-inch square pan.
Freeze until firm, about 6 hours or overnight.
Scoop into individual dessert dishes.

title: short process sweet cucumber pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in lime water 24 hours.
Soak cucumbers in clear water 2 hours.
Drain 15 minutes.
Prepare syrup, using vinegar, sugar, salt and pickling spice.
Tie spice in bag to keep pickles clear.
Put cucumbers in hot, not boiling syrup.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours but do not boil.
Seal while hot.
Process 10 minutes at simmering temperature.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Pour pineapple in pan; pour blueberries on top of pineapple. Put sugar on that; top with a yellow butter cake mix and slice butter on top. Bake at 350° until gold and bubbly.

title: mommy and alyson's chippin dippin chicken
directions: Wash and remove the skin from the chicken legs.
Beat the eggs and milk in bowl.
Crush the potato chips and put on a flat plate. Take the chicken legs and dip into egg mixture, then into the potato chips.
Place chicken on a rack on a cookie sheet.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Children love it.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Bring sugars, butter and milk to a boil, stirring constantly, until a soft ball forms when dropped in cold water.
Remove from fire and add vanilla and pecans.
Heat until it begins to thicken. Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water as directed on package.
Drain in colander.
Put back in pot, add butter to macaroni, then add whipped eggs and milk.
Stir in cheese.
Place in a greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until liquid is firm, but not dry.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice. Add drained fruits and nuts. Mix with Cool Whip.

title: strawberry bavarian pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and plain gelatin in hot water.
Add sugar, dash of salt and lemon juice.
Chill until slightly thickened. Add crushed strawberries, then fold in whipped cream and place in baked pie shell.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with additional whipped cream and whole strawberries.
(All measurements are level.)

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken pieces in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer cheese slices on top.
Cover with soup and sprinkle stuffing mix over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove and cover; bake 20 more minutes.

title: pizza in a skillet
directions: Place tomatoes in a medium bowl.
Cover with hot water to a depth of 2-inches above the tomatoes; let stand 15 minutes. Drain; coarsely chop tomatoes and set aside.

title: quick pralines
directions: Cook all together to a soft boil stage. Remove from heat. Beat until it starts to get firm. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw strawberries and reserve 1/2 cup juice for making filling.
Mix flour, soda, cinnamon, sugar and salt.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Pour strawberries, oil and eggs into the hole.
Mix by hand until all ingredients are thoroughly combined.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes.

title: mushroom canapes
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter 5 to 7 minutes.
Soften cheese and add egg yolks and onion; mix well.
Add mushrooms and juice. Spread mixture on toasted bread rounds.
Broil 3 to 5 minutes.

title: best brownies
directions: Melt oleo in small cake pan. Sift dry ingredients, then add the rest and mix.
Add oleo.
Bake at 350° just until crusty on top, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: roode kool
directions: In a large pan, cook cabbage, apples, salt and pepper in a small amount of boiling water over medium-low heat, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes or until apples are tender.
Drain.
Return to saucepan. Add vinegar, butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Heat through. Stir to combine.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hot 'n sour soup
directions: In slow cooker, combine all ingredients, except green onions. Cover.
Cook on low 7 to 8 hours.
Garnish with green onion slices.
Makes 7 to 8 servings.

title: easy peanut candy
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients to hard crack or 300°.
Butter an 8-inch skillet.
Put in peanut butter.
Pour cooked syrup on top. Stir quickly into a ball.
Cut with scissors.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Mix well and form into balls.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine eggs, oil and biscuit mix.
Stir in chilies, onion, garlic and half of the cheese.
Stir in squash.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes; sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake 5 minutes more.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown meat and drain grease.
Add onion and brown.
Add barbecue sauce and sugar.
Mix well and let simmer 5 minutes.
Put biscuits in muffin pan.
Mash biscuits around cups of the pan. Spoon in meat mixture.
Put cheese over top and bake until biscuits are brown.
Preheat oven to 325°.

title: chocolate waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Add well-beaten egg yolks, butter, milk and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg whites into flour mixture.
Pour batter into hot waffle iron.
Bake until crisp.

title: sausage tomato soup
directions: In a large sauce pan, cook the sausage, onion and green pepper over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain.
Stir in tomatoes, broth, tomato sauce, picante sauce, sugar, basil and oregano.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 6.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a medium-large saucepan, pour half of milk, rice and cinnamon sticks.
Turn heat to high and cook until mixture starts to come to a low boil, stirring occasionally.
When mixture starts to boil, begin to stir very frequently (almost constantly), adding milk when necessary.
Cook for about 45 minutes, adding sugar to taste.
When rice is done and pudding is a pretty thick consistency, pour into bowl.
Let cool before putting into fridge. Excellent cold.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter large casserole dish.
Brown meat and season to taste (salt, pepper, chili powder and cumin). Add cream soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes; stir well and let cook about 30 minutes.
Tear each tortilla into 4 pieces; layer 1/2 the torn tortillas in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, then top with 1/2 the meat mixture and grated Velveeta cheese.
Repeat the layer, topping with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: anna juergen's millionaire pie
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy; add other ingredients except butter.
Dot unbaked pie shell with butter.
Bake in slow oven, 325° for 40 minutes or until pie filling sets.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix altogether.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with cracker crumbs or French fried onions.
Cook 10 minutes.
Very good.

title: olive puffs
directions: Drain olives.
Form a soft dough with margarine, cheese spread and flour.
Shape a small dough ball around each olive.
Bake on cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: fresh lemon ice cream
directions: In bowl combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Freeze in ice cream freezer as manufacturer directs.
Makes 12 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef and layer on the bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle cheese on top. Pour soup (don't dilute). Layer Tater Tots on top. Bake at 350°, covered, 40 minutes and then uncovered 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry cream salad
directions: Whip the cream.
Add the sugar, then the other ingredients. Pour into a loaf pan and freeze.

title: french fried sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Let cool. Peel potatoes and cut in finger size strips or 1/2-inch slices. Fry in hot oil until golden brown. Drain and sprinkle with salt or powdered sugar.

title: poor man's pie
directions: Break soda crackers rather coarsely into unbaked pie shell. Into a saucepan, put remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and pour over crackers.
Put top crust on and bake at 375° until done.

title: um-um chicken
directions: Boil chicken with salt.
Debone and skin.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken. Crush crackers.
Mix with poppy seed.
Pour over soup.
Melt butter.
Pour over top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry sauce
directions: Empty strawberries into a medium-sized saucepan.
Cook over medium-low heat 10 to 15 minutes, or until berries are thawed and can be broken apart.
Stir occasionally with a wooden spoon.
In a small bowl, combine the sugar and the cornstarch; mix well.
Pour the mixture into the pan with the berries; stir with wooden spoon. Continue cooking over medium-low heat until mixture comes to a boil, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Move pan from heat; add jam.
Let stand 1 minute, then mix.
Serve warm over ice cream or cake. Refrigerate leftover sauce in closed container.
Re-use over a few days.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chicken-broccoli
directions: Cook chicken in water with onion and celery seasoning.
Remove all bones.
Cook broccoli according to directions.
Arrange chicken and broccoli by layers in greased baking dish.
Place cheese on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle top with extra cheese and buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: norwegian soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease baking sheet.
Sift flour, soda and salt into large bowl.
Stir in sugar.
In medium bowl mix melted butter, buttermilk and egg.
Make a well in center of flour and pour liquid in.
Using spatula gradually draw in flour mixture into the liquid.
Mix well.
Transfer dough to floured board and knead lightly.
Divide in half and shape into 2 flat rounds. Should be 1/2-inch thick.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cookie cake
directions: Bring margarine, cocoa and milk to a boil.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Mix until smooth and creamy.
Ice cake while still very warm.

title: little round pizzas
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Sprinkle in spices.
Add catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Cut cheese in chunks and add to sausage. Heat on low heat until cheese is melted.
Put on party rye bread. (Can make ahead and freeze.)
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mom's best ever dressing
directions: Mix all together and serve with your favorite salad.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, cook onions in margarine until tender. Add remaining ingredients; stir over low heat until cheese is melted and mixture is hot.
Yields 4 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: candy bar freezer dessert
directions: In a large bowl, combine the cracker crumbs and butter. Pat 3/4 of the mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9 dish. Refrigerate.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Pour melted butter over pretzels.
Sprinkle sugar over mixture and bake for 8 minutes at 400°.
Remove and let cool.
Beat together cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip; mix well.
Spread over cooled pretzel mixture.
Make sure all edges and corners are covered.

title: chicken and tortilla casserole
directions: Place chicken in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover and cook at 350° about an hour; set aside to cool.
Mix 2 soups, milk and salsa and set aside.
After chicken has cooled, break into pieces leaving drippings in the pan.
Tear tortillas into strips.
Layer tortilla strips, chicken and sauce into pan.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Bring to boil and boil 5 minutes.
Good for ice cream or milkshakes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, sugar, cinnamon and baking powder together. Add the milk and melted butter to a well beaten egg.
Stir into the dry ingredients.
Bake in a greased 8-inch round layer pan in a 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle top with sugar and cinnamon.

title: 6 lemon lemonade
directions: Juice lemons in pitcher.
Add sugar.
Add warm water to pitcher and stir briskly until sugar is dissolved.
Refrigerate until cold.

title: huckabee's hot and happy cajun jambalaya
directions: Use no salt.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours or 250° for 6 hours (young deer) or for 8 hours (old deer).

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel and core apples.
Coarsely chop and measure 1 3/4 cups into large bowl.
Add sugar, let stand 10 minutes.
Sift flour, add soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Blend butter and egg into apple mixture.
Add flour, stirring just until well blended.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: rowdy brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix with melted margarine, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and chopped nuts.
Stir by hand.
Put 1/2 of dough into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over baked crust.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cut up chicken in small pieces and stir fry in pan with onions.

Mix together soup, sour cream and chilies, cover bottom of 9 x 13 pan with half of mixture, fill tortillas with chicken and roll up, place in dish and cover with remaining soup mixture. Top with cheese and bake at 350 degrees for 30 mins.

title: pork au poivre
directions: Stir together first 3 ingredients.
Lightly coat cutlets.
In large skillet, saute garlic in oil over medium-high heat for one minute.
Discard garlic. Add cutlets and cook 2 to 3 minutes, turning once, until slightly brown.
Remove and keep warm.
Stir in juice or wine.
Stir constantly for 2 to 3 minutes, until thickened and liquid reduces.
Stir in parsley.
Pour over cutlets.
Serve on a platter.

title: paciugo(tricolor parfait)
directions: Alternate scoops of vanilla, raspberry and chocolate ice cream into 6 tall glasses.
Drizzle the syrup over the top.

title: date squares
directions: Cook dates and sugar in water until thick.
Mix all other ingredients together (with your hands) until crumbly.
Put half of mixture evenly on a cookie sheet; pat down.
Spread date filling over this.
Crumble rest of mixture over filling.
(Nuts may be sprinkled on top if desired.)
Bake in 350° oven about 20 minutes until brown.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread on crescents. Top with vegetables and cheese -- broccoli, cauliflower, mushrooms.
